52 #define __ asm_.
53 
54 // It's important that we don't modify the LiftoffAssembler's cache state
55 // in conditionally-executed code paths. Creating these witnesses helps
56 // enforce that (using DCHECKs in the cache state).
57 // Conditional jump instructions require a witness to have been created (to
58 // make sure we don't forget); the witness should stay alive until the label
59 // is bound where regular control flow resumes. This implies that when we're
60 // jumping to a trap, the live range of the witness isn't important.
61 #define FREEZE_STATE(witness_name) FreezeCacheState witness_name(asm_)
62 
63 #define TRACE(...) \
64  do { \
65  if (v8_flags.trace_liftoff) PrintF("[liftoff] " __VA_ARGS__); \
66  } while (false)
67 
68 #define WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_FIELD_OFFSET(name) \
69  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTrustedInstanceData::k##name##Offset)
70 
71 template <int expected_size, int actual_size>
72 struct assert_field_size {
73  static_assert(expected_size == actual_size,
74  "field in WasmInstance does not have the expected size");
75  static constexpr int size = actual_size;
76 };
77 
78 #define WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_FIELD_SIZE(name) \
79  FIELD_SIZE(WasmTrustedInstanceData::k##name##Offset)
80 
81 #define LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(dst, name, load_size, pinned) \
82  __ LoadFromInstance( \
83  dst, LoadInstanceIntoRegister(pinned, dst), \
84  WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_FIELD_OFFSET(name), \
85  assert_field_size<WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_FIELD_SIZE(name), \
86  load_size>::size);
87 
88 #define LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(dst, name, pinned) \
89  static_assert( \
90  WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_FIELD_SIZE(name) == kTaggedSize, \
91  "field in WasmTrustedInstanceData does not have the expected size"); \
92  __ LoadTaggedPointerFromInstance( \
93  dst, LoadInstanceIntoRegister(pinned, dst), \
94  WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_FIELD_OFFSET(name));
95 
96 #define LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_FROM_INSTANCE(dst, name, instance) \
97  static_assert( \
98  WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_FIELD_SIZE(name) == kTaggedSize, \
99  "field in WasmTrustedInstanceData does not have the expected size"); \
100  __ LoadTaggedPointerFromInstance( \
101  dst, instance, WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_FIELD_OFFSET(name));
102 
103 #define LOAD_PROTECTED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(dst, name, pinned) \
104  static_assert( \
105  WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_FIELD_SIZE(Protected##name) == kTaggedSize, \
106  "field in WasmTrustedInstanceData does not have the expected size"); \
107  __ LoadProtectedPointer( \
108  dst, LoadInstanceIntoRegister(pinned, dst), \
109  WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_FIELD_OFFSET(Protected##name));

111 // Liftoff's code comments are intentionally without source location to keep
112 // readability up.
113 #ifdef V8_CODE_COMMENTS
114 #define CODE_COMMENT(str) __ RecordComment(str, SourceLocation{})
115 #define SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT(str) \
116  AssemblerBase::CodeComment CONCAT(scoped_comment_, __LINE__)( \
117  &asm_, str, SourceLocation{})
118 #else
119 #define CODE_COMMENT(str) ((void)0)
120 #define SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT(str) ((void)0)

123 // For fuzzing purposes, we count each instruction as one "step". Certain
124 // "bulk" type instructions (dealing with memories, tables, strings, arrays)
125 // can take much more time. For simplicity, we count them all as a fixed
126 // large number of steps.
127 constexpr int kHeavyInstructionSteps = 1000;

135 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
136 // On ARM64, the Assembler keeps track of pointers to Labels to resolve
137 // branches to distant targets. Moving labels would confuse the Assembler,
138 // thus store the label in the Zone.
139 class MovableLabel {
140  public:
141  MOVE_ONLY_NO_DEFAULT_CONSTRUCTOR(MovableLabel);
142  explicit MovableLabel(Zone* zone) : label_(zone->New<Label>()) {}
143 
144  Label* get() { return label_; }
145 
146  private:
147  Label* label_;
148 };
149 #else
150 // On all other platforms, just store the Label directly.
151 class MovableLabel {
152  public:
153  MOVE_ONLY_NO_DEFAULT_CONSTRUCTOR(MovableLabel);
154  explicit MovableLabel(Zone*) {}
155 
156  Label* get() { return &label_; }
157 
158  private:
159  Label label_;
160 };
161 #endif

163 compiler::CallDescriptor* GetLoweredCallDescriptor(
164  Zone* zone, compiler::CallDescriptor* call_desc) {
165  return kSystemPointerSize == 4
166  ? compiler::GetI32WasmCallDescriptor(zone, call_desc)
167  : call_desc;
168 }

170 constexpr Condition GetCompareCondition(WasmOpcode opcode) {
171  switch (opcode) {
172  case kExprI32Eq:
173  return kEqual;
174  case kExprI32Ne:
175  return kNotEqual;
176  case kExprI32LtS:
177  return kLessThan;
178  case kExprI32LtU:
179  return kUnsignedLessThan;
180  case kExprI32GtS:
181  return kGreaterThan;
182  case kExprI32GtU:
183  return kUnsignedGreaterThan;
184  case kExprI32LeS:
185  return kLessThanEqual;
186  case kExprI32LeU:
187  return kUnsignedLessThanEqual;
188  case kExprI32GeS:
189  return kGreaterThanEqual;
190  case kExprI32GeU:
191  return kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual;
192  default:
193  UNREACHABLE();
194  }
195 }

197 // Builds a {DebugSideTable}.
198 class DebugSideTableBuilder {
199  using Entry = DebugSideTable::Entry;
200  using Value = Entry::Value;
201 
202  public:
203  enum AssumeSpilling {
204  // All register values will be spilled before the pc covered by the debug
205  // side table entry. Register slots will be marked as stack slots in the
206  // generated debug side table entry.
207  kAssumeSpilling,
208  // Register slots will be written out as they are.
209  kAllowRegisters,
210  // Register slots cannot appear since we already spilled.
211  kDidSpill
212  };
213 
214  class EntryBuilder {
215  public:
216  explicit EntryBuilder(int pc_offset, int stack_height,
217  std::vector<Value> changed_values)
218  : pc_offset_(pc_offset),
219  stack_height_(stack_height),
220  changed_values_(std::move(changed_values)) {}
221 
222  Entry ToTableEntry() {
223  return Entry{pc_offset_, stack_height_, std::move(changed_values_)};
224  }
225 
226  void MinimizeBasedOnPreviousStack(const std::vector<Value>& last_values) {
227  auto dst = changed_values_.begin();
228  auto end = changed_values_.end();
229  for (auto src = dst; src != end; ++src) {
230  if (src->index < static_cast<int>(last_values.size()) &&
231  *src == last_values[src->index]) {
232  continue;
233  }
234  if (dst != src) *dst = *src;
235  ++dst;
236  }
237  changed_values_.erase(dst, end);
238  }
239 
240  int pc_offset() const { return pc_offset_; }
241  void set_pc_offset(int new_pc_offset) { pc_offset_ = new_pc_offset; }
242 
243  private:
244  int pc_offset_;
245  int stack_height_;
246  std::vector<Value> changed_values_;
247  };
248 
249  // Adds a new entry in regular code.
250  void NewEntry(int pc_offset,
251  base::Vector<DebugSideTable::Entry::Value> values) {
252  entries_.emplace_back(pc_offset, static_cast<int>(values.size()),
253  GetChangedStackValues(last_values_, values));
254  }
255 
256  // Adds a new entry for OOL code, and returns a pointer to a builder for
257  // modifying that entry.
258  EntryBuilder* NewOOLEntry(base::Vector<DebugSideTable::Entry::Value> values) {
259  constexpr int kNoPcOffsetYet = -1;
260  ool_entries_.emplace_back(kNoPcOffsetYet, static_cast<int>(values.size()),
261  GetChangedStackValues(last_ool_values_, values));
262  return &ool_entries_.back();
263  }
264 
265  void SetNumLocals(int num_locals) {
266  DCHECK_EQ(-1, num_locals_);
267  DCHECK_LE(0, num_locals);
268  num_locals_ = num_locals;
269  }
270 
271  std::unique_ptr<DebugSideTable> GenerateDebugSideTable() {
272  DCHECK_LE(0, num_locals_);
273 
274  // Connect {entries_} and {ool_entries_} by removing redundant stack
275  // information from the first {ool_entries_} entry (based on
276  // {last_values_}).
277  if (!entries_.empty() && !ool_entries_.empty()) {
278  ool_entries_.front().MinimizeBasedOnPreviousStack(last_values_);
279  }
280 
281  std::vector<Entry> entries;
282  entries.reserve(entries_.size() + ool_entries_.size());
283  for (auto& entry : entries_) entries.push_back(entry.ToTableEntry());
284  for (auto& entry : ool_entries_) entries.push_back(entry.ToTableEntry());
285  DCHECK(std::is_sorted(
286  entries.begin(), entries.end(),
287  [](Entry& a, Entry& b) { return a.pc_offset() < b.pc_offset(); }));
288  return std::make_unique<DebugSideTable>(num_locals_, std::move(entries));
289  }
290 
291  private:
292  static std::vector<Value> GetChangedStackValues(
293  std::vector<Value>& last_values, base::Vector<Value> values) {
294  std::vector<Value> changed_values;
295  int old_stack_size = static_cast<int>(last_values.size());
296  last_values.resize(values.size());
297 
298  int index = 0;
299  for (const auto& value : values) {
300  if (index >= old_stack_size || last_values[index] != value) {
301  changed_values.push_back(value);
302  last_values[index] = value;
303  }
304  ++index;
305  }
306  return changed_values;
307  }
308 
309  int num_locals_ = -1;
310  // Keep a snapshot of the stack of the last entry, to generate a delta to the
311  // next entry.
312  std::vector<Value> last_values_;
313  std::vector<EntryBuilder> entries_;
314  // Keep OOL code entries separate so we can do proper delta-encoding (more
315  // entries might be added between the existing {entries_} and the
316  // {ool_entries_}). Store the entries in a list so the pointer is not
317  // invalidated by adding more entries.
318  std::vector<Value> last_ool_values_;
319  std::list<EntryBuilder> ool_entries_;
320 };
321 
322 void CheckBailoutAllowed(LiftoffBailoutReason reason, const char* detail,
323  const CompilationEnv* env) {
324  // Decode errors are ok.
325  if (reason == kDecodeError) return;
326 
327  // --liftoff-only ensures that tests actually exercise the Liftoff path
328  // without bailing out. We also fail for missing CPU support, to avoid
329  // running any TurboFan code under --liftoff-only.
330  if (v8_flags.liftoff_only) {
331  FATAL("--liftoff-only: treating bailout as fatal error. Cause: %s", detail);
332  }
333 
334  // Missing CPU features are generally OK, except with --liftoff-only.
335  if (reason == kMissingCPUFeature) return;
336 
337  // If --enable-testing-opcode-in-wasm is set, we are expected to bailout with
338  // "testing opcode".
339  if (v8_flags.enable_testing_opcode_in_wasm &&
340  strcmp(detail, "testing opcode") == 0) {
341  return;
342  }
343 
344  // Some externally maintained architectures don't fully implement Liftoff yet.
345 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_MIPS64 || V8_TARGET_ARCH_S390X || V8_TARGET_ARCH_PPC64 || \
346  V8_TARGET_ARCH_LOONG64
347  return;
348 #endif
349 
350 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM
351  // Allow bailout for missing ARMv7 support.
352  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ARMv7) && reason == kUnsupportedArchitecture) {
353  return;
354  }
355 #endif
356 
357 #define LIST_FEATURE(name, ...) WasmEnabledFeature::name,
358  constexpr WasmEnabledFeatures kExperimentalFeatures{
359  FOREACH_WASM_EXPERIMENTAL_FEATURE_FLAG(LIST_FEATURE)};
360 #undef LIST_FEATURE
361 
362  // Bailout is allowed if any experimental feature is enabled.
363  if (env->enabled_features.contains_any(kExperimentalFeatures)) return;
364 
365  // Otherwise, bailout is not allowed.
366  FATAL("Liftoff bailout should not happen. Cause: %s\n", detail);
367 }
368 
369 class TempRegisterScope {
370  public:
371  LiftoffRegister Acquire(RegClass rc) {
372  LiftoffRegList candidates = free_temps_ & GetCacheRegList(rc);
373  DCHECK(!candidates.is_empty());
374  return free_temps_.clear(candidates.GetFirstRegSet());
375  }
376 
377  void Return(LiftoffRegister&& temp) {
378  DCHECK(!free_temps_.has(temp));
379  free_temps_.set(temp);
380  }
381 
382  void Return(Register&& temp) {
383  Return(LiftoffRegister{temp});
384  temp = no_reg;
385  }
386 
387  LiftoffRegList AddTempRegisters(int count, RegClass rc,
388  LiftoffAssembler* lasm,
389  LiftoffRegList pinned) {
390  LiftoffRegList temps;
391  pinned |= free_temps_;
392  for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
393  temps.set(lasm->GetUnusedRegister(rc, pinned | temps));
394  }
395  free_temps_ |= temps;
396  return temps;
397  }
398 
399  private:
400  LiftoffRegList free_temps_;
401 };
402 
403 class ScopedTempRegister {
404  public:
405  ScopedTempRegister(TempRegisterScope& temp_scope, RegClass rc)
406  : reg_(temp_scope.Acquire(rc)), temp_scope_(&temp_scope) {}
407 
408  ScopedTempRegister(const ScopedTempRegister&) = delete;
409 
410  ScopedTempRegister(ScopedTempRegister&& other) V8_NOEXCEPT
411  : reg_(other.reg_),
412  temp_scope_(other.temp_scope_) {
413  other.temp_scope_ = nullptr;
414  }
415 
416  ScopedTempRegister& operator=(const ScopedTempRegister&) = delete;
417 
418  ~ScopedTempRegister() {
419  if (temp_scope_) Reset();
420  }
421 
422  LiftoffRegister reg() const {
423  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(temp_scope_);
424  return reg_;
425  }
426 
427  Register gp_reg() const { return reg().gp(); }
428 
429  void Reset() {
430  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(temp_scope_);
431  temp_scope_->Return(std::move(reg_));
432  temp_scope_ = nullptr;
433  }
434 
435  private:
436  LiftoffRegister reg_;
437  TempRegisterScope* temp_scope_;
438 };

440 class LiftoffCompiler {
441  public:
442  using ValidationTag = Decoder::NoValidationTag;
443  using Value = ValueBase<ValidationTag>;
444  static constexpr bool kUsesPoppedArgs = false;
445 
446  // Some constants for tier-up checks.
447  // In general we use the number of executed machine code bytes as an estimate
448  // of how much time was spent in this function.
449  // - {kTierUpCostForCheck} is the cost for checking for the tier-up itself,
450  // which is added to the PC distance on every tier-up check. This cost is
451  // for loading the tiering budget, subtracting from one entry in the array,
452  // and the conditional branch if the value is negative.
453  // - {kTierUpCostForFunctionEntry} reflects the cost for calling the frame
454  // setup stub in the function prologue (the time is spent in another code
455  // object and hence not reflected in the PC distance).
456  static constexpr int kTierUpCostForCheck = 20;
457  static constexpr int kTierUpCostForFunctionEntry = 40;
458

462  LiftoffAssembler::CacheState state;
463  };

473  struct Control : public ControlBase<Value, ValidationTag> {
474  ElseState* else_state = nullptr;

490  using FullDecoder = WasmFullDecoder<ValidationTag, LiftoffCompiler>;
491  using ValueKindSig = LiftoffAssembler::ValueKindSig;
492 
493  class MostlySmallValueKindSig : public Signature<ValueKind> {
494  public:
495  MostlySmallValueKindSig(Zone* zone, const FunctionSig* sig)
496  : Signature<ValueKind>(sig->return_count(), sig->parameter_count(),
497  MakeKinds(inline_storage_, zone, sig)) {}
498 
499  private:
500  static constexpr size_t kInlineStorage = 8;
501 
502  static ValueKind* MakeKinds(ValueKind* storage, Zone* zone,
503  const FunctionSig* sig) {
504  const size_t size = sig->parameter_count() + sig->return_count();
505  if (V8_UNLIKELY(size > kInlineStorage)) {
506  storage = zone->AllocateArray<ValueKind>(size);
507  }
508  std::transform(sig->all().begin(), sig->all().end(), storage,
509  [](ValueType type) { return type.kind(); });
510  return storage;
511  }
512 
513  ValueKind inline_storage_[kInlineStorage];
514  };

536  struct OutOfLineCode {
537  MovableLabel label;
538  MovableLabel continuation;
539  Builtin builtin;
540  WasmCodePosition position;
541  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
542  Register cached_instance_data;
543  OutOfLineSafepointInfo* safepoint_info;
544  // These two pointers will only be used for debug code:
545  SpilledRegistersForInspection* spilled_registers;
546  DebugSideTableBuilder::EntryBuilder* debug_sidetable_entry_builder;
547 
548  // Named constructors:
549  static OutOfLineCode Trap(
550  Zone* zone, Builtin builtin, WasmCodePosition pos,
551  SpilledRegistersForInspection* spilled_registers,
552  OutOfLineSafepointInfo* safepoint_info,
553  DebugSideTableBuilder::EntryBuilder* debug_sidetable_entry_builder) {
554  DCHECK_LT(0, pos);
555  return {
556  MovableLabel{zone}, // label
557  MovableLabel{zone}, // continuation
558  builtin, // builtin
559  pos, // position
560  {}, // regs_to_save
561  no_reg, // cached_instance_data
562  safepoint_info, // safepoint_info
563  spilled_registers, // spilled_registers
564  debug_sidetable_entry_builder // debug_side_table_entry_builder
565  };
566  }
567  static OutOfLineCode StackCheck(
568  Zone* zone, WasmCodePosition pos, LiftoffRegList regs_to_save,
569  Register cached_instance_data,
570  SpilledRegistersForInspection* spilled_regs,
571  OutOfLineSafepointInfo* safepoint_info,
572  DebugSideTableBuilder::EntryBuilder* debug_sidetable_entry_builder) {
573  Builtin stack_guard = Builtin::kWasmStackGuard;
574  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
575  stack_guard = Builtin::kWasmGrowableStackGuard;
576  }
577  return {
578  MovableLabel{zone}, // label
579  MovableLabel{zone}, // continuation
580  stack_guard, // builtin
581  pos, // position
582  regs_to_save, // regs_to_save
583  cached_instance_data, // cached_instance_data
584  safepoint_info, // safepoint_info
585  spilled_regs, // spilled_registers
586  debug_sidetable_entry_builder // debug_side_table_entry_builder
587  };
588  }
589  static OutOfLineCode TierupCheck(
590  Zone* zone, WasmCodePosition pos, LiftoffRegList regs_to_save,
591  Register cached_instance_data,
592  SpilledRegistersForInspection* spilled_regs,
593  OutOfLineSafepointInfo* safepoint_info,
594  DebugSideTableBuilder::EntryBuilder* debug_sidetable_entry_builder) {
595  return {
596  MovableLabel{zone}, // label
597  MovableLabel{zone}, // continuation,
598  Builtin::kWasmTriggerTierUp, // builtin
599  pos, // position
600  regs_to_save, // regs_to_save
601  cached_instance_data, // cached_instance_data
602  safepoint_info, // safepoint_info
603  spilled_regs, // spilled_registers
604  debug_sidetable_entry_builder // debug_side_table_entry_builder
605  };
606  }
607  };

609  LiftoffCompiler(compiler::CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
610  CompilationEnv* env, Zone* zone,
611  std::unique_ptr<AssemblerBuffer> buffer,
612  DebugSideTableBuilder* debug_sidetable_builder,
613  const LiftoffOptions& options,
614  WasmFunctionCoverageData* coverage_data)
615  : asm_(zone, std::move(buffer)),
616  descriptor_(GetLoweredCallDescriptor(zone, call_descriptor)),
617  env_(env),
618  debug_sidetable_builder_(debug_sidetable_builder),
619  for_debugging_(options.for_debugging),
620  func_index_(options.func_index),
621  out_of_line_code_(zone),
622  source_position_table_builder_(zone),
623  protected_instructions_(zone),
624  zone_(zone),
625  safepoint_table_builder_(zone_),
626  next_breakpoint_ptr_(options.breakpoints.begin()),
627  next_breakpoint_end_(options.breakpoints.end()),
628  dead_breakpoint_(options.dead_breakpoint),
629  handlers_(zone),
630  max_steps_(options.max_steps),
631  detect_nondeterminism_(options.detect_nondeterminism),
632  deopt_info_bytecode_offset_(options.deopt_info_bytecode_offset),
633  deopt_location_kind_(options.deopt_location_kind) {
634  // We often see huge numbers of traps per function, so pre-reserve some
635  // space in that vector. 128 entries is enough for ~94% of functions on
636  // modern modules, as of 2022-06-03.
637  out_of_line_code_.reserve(128);
638 
639  DCHECK(options.is_initialized());
640  // If there are no breakpoints, both pointers should be nullptr.
641  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
642  next_breakpoint_ptr_ == next_breakpoint_end_,
643  next_breakpoint_ptr_ == nullptr && next_breakpoint_end_ == nullptr);
644  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!for_debugging_, debug_sidetable_builder_ == nullptr);
645 
646  if (v8_flags.wasm_code_coverage) {
647  DCHECK_EQ(for_debugging_, kForDebugging);
648  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(coverage_data);
649  coverage_code_ranges_ = coverage_data->code_ranges();
650  coverage_current_code_range_ = coverage_code_ranges_.begin();
651  coverage_count_array_addr_ =
652  reinterpret_cast<Address>(coverage_data->counters().data());
653  }
654  }
655 
656  bool did_bailout() const { return bailout_reason_ != kSuccess; }
657  LiftoffBailoutReason bailout_reason() const { return bailout_reason_; }
658 
659  void GetCode(CodeDesc* desc) {
660  asm_.GetCode(nullptr, desc, &safepoint_table_builder_,
661  handler_table_offset_);
662  }
663 
664  std::unique_ptr<AssemblerBuffer> ReleaseBuffer() {
665  return asm_.ReleaseBuffer();
666  }
667 
668  std::unique_ptr<LiftoffFrameDescriptionForDeopt> ReleaseFrameDescriptions() {
669  return std::move(frame_description_);
670  }
671 
672  base::OwnedVector<uint8_t> GetSourcePositionTable() {
673  return source_position_table_builder_.ToSourcePositionTableVector();
674  }
675 
676  base::OwnedVector<uint8_t> GetProtectedInstructionsData() const {
677  return base::OwnedCopyOf(base::Vector<const uint8_t>::cast(
678  base::VectorOf(protected_instructions_)));
679  }
680 
681  uint32_t GetTotalFrameSlotCountForGC() const {
682  return __ GetTotalFrameSlotCountForGC();
683  }
684 
685  uint32_t OolSpillCount() const { return __ OolSpillCount(); }
686 
687  void unsupported(FullDecoder* decoder, LiftoffBailoutReason reason,
688  const char* detail) {
689  DCHECK_NE(kSuccess, reason);
690  if (did_bailout()) return;
691  bailout_reason_ = reason;
692  TRACE("unsupported: %s\n", detail);
693  decoder->errorf(decoder->pc_offset(), "unsupported liftoff operation: %s",
694  detail);
695  UnuseLabels(decoder);
696  CheckBailoutAllowed(reason, detail, env_);
697  }
698 
699  bool DidAssemblerBailout(FullDecoder* decoder) {
700  if (decoder->failed() || !__ did_bailout()) return false;
701  unsupported(decoder, __ bailout_reason(), __ bailout_detail());
702  return true;
703  }
704 
705  V8_INLINE bool CheckSupportedType(FullDecoder* decoder, ValueKind kind,
706  const char* context) {
707  if (V8_LIKELY(supported_types_.contains(kind))) return true;
708  return MaybeBailoutForUnsupportedType(decoder, kind, context);
709  }
710 
711  V8_NOINLINE bool MaybeBailoutForUnsupportedType(FullDecoder* decoder,
712  ValueKind kind,
713  const char* context) {
714  DCHECK(!supported_types_.contains(kind));
715 
716  // Lazily update {supported_types_}; then check again.
717  if (CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128()) supported_types_.Add(kS128);
718  if (supported_types_.contains(kind)) return true;
719 
720  LiftoffBailoutReason bailout_reason;
721  switch (kind) {
722  case kS128:
723  bailout_reason = kSimd;
724  break;
725  default:
726  UNREACHABLE();
727  }
728  base::EmbeddedVector<char, 128> buffer;
729  SNPrintF(buffer, "%s %s", name(kind), context);
730  unsupported(decoder, bailout_reason, buffer.begin());
731  return false;
732  }
733 
734  void UnuseLabels(FullDecoder* decoder) {
735 #ifdef DEBUG
736  auto Unuse = [](Label* label) {
737  label->Unuse();
738  label->UnuseNear();
739  };
740  // Unuse all labels now, otherwise their destructor will fire a DCHECK error
741  // if they where referenced before.
742  uint32_t control_depth = decoder ? decoder->control_depth() : 0;
743  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < control_depth; ++i) {
744  Control* c = decoder->control_at(i);
745  Unuse(c->label.get());
746  if (c->else_state) Unuse(c->else_state->label.get());
747  if (c->try_info != nullptr) Unuse(&c->try_info->catch_label);
748  }
749  for (auto& ool : out_of_line_code_) Unuse(ool.label.get());
750 #endif
751  }
752 
753  void StartFunction(FullDecoder* decoder) {
754  if (v8_flags.trace_liftoff && !v8_flags.trace_wasm_decoder) {
755  StdoutStream{} << "hint: add --trace-wasm-decoder to also see the wasm "
756  "instructions being decoded\n";
757  }
758  int num_locals = decoder->num_locals();
759  __ set_num_locals(num_locals);
760  for (int i = 0; i < num_locals; ++i) {
761  ValueKind kind = decoder->local_type(i).kind();
762  __ set_local_kind(i, kind);
763  }
764  }
765 
766  class ParameterProcessor {
767  public:
768  ParameterProcessor(LiftoffCompiler* compiler, uint32_t num_params)
769  : compiler_(compiler), num_params_(num_params) {}
770 
771  void Process() {
772  // First pass: collect parameter registers.
773  while (NextParam()) {
774  MaybeCollectRegister();
775  if (needs_gp_pair_) {
776  NextLocation();
777  MaybeCollectRegister();
778  }
779  }
780  // Second pass: allocate parameters.
781  param_idx_ = 0;
782  input_idx_ = kFirstInputIdx;
783  while (NextParam()) {
784  LiftoffRegister reg = LoadToReg(param_regs_);
785  // The sandbox's function signature checks don't care to distinguish
786  // i32 and i64 primitives. That's usually fine, but in a few cases
787  // i32 parameters with non-zero upper halves can violate security-
788  // relevant invariants, so we explicitly clear them here.
789  // 'clear_i32_upper_half' is empty on LoongArch64, MIPS64 and riscv64,
790  // because they will explicitly zero-extend their lower halves before
791  // using them for memory accesses anyway.
792  // In addition, the generic js-to-wasm wrapper does a sign-extension
793  // of i32 parameters, so clearing the upper half is required for
794  // correctness in this case.
795 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
796  if (kind_ == kI32 && location_.IsRegister()) {
797  compiler_->asm_.clear_i32_upper_half(reg.gp());
798  }
799 #endif
800  if (needs_gp_pair_) {
801  NextLocation();
802  LiftoffRegister reg2 = LoadToReg(param_regs_ | LiftoffRegList{reg});
803  reg = LiftoffRegister::ForPair(reg.gp(), reg2.gp());
804  }
805  compiler_->asm_.PushRegister(kind_, reg);
806  }
807  }
808 
809  private:
810  bool NextParam() {
811  if (param_idx_ >= num_params_) {
812  DCHECK_EQ(input_idx_, compiler_->descriptor_->InputCount());
813  return false;
814  }
815  kind_ = compiler_->asm_.local_kind(param_idx_++);
816  needs_gp_pair_ = needs_gp_reg_pair(kind_);
817  reg_kind_ = needs_gp_pair_ ? kI32 : kind_;
818  rc_ = reg_class_for(reg_kind_);
819  NextLocation();
820  return true;
821  }
822 
823  void NextLocation() {
824  location_ = compiler_->descriptor_->GetInputLocation(input_idx_++);
825  }
826 
827  LiftoffRegister CurrentRegister() {
828  DCHECK(!location_.IsAnyRegister());
829  return LiftoffRegister::from_external_code(rc_, reg_kind_,
830  location_.AsRegister());
831  }
832 
833  void MaybeCollectRegister() {
834  if (!location_.IsRegister()) return;
835  DCHECK(!param_regs_.has(CurrentRegister()));
836  param_regs_.set(CurrentRegister());
837  }
838 
839  LiftoffRegister LoadToReg(LiftoffRegList pinned) {
840  if (location_.IsRegister()) {
841  LiftoffRegister reg = CurrentRegister();
842  DCHECK(compiler_->asm_.cache_state()->is_free(reg));
843  // Unpin the register, to avoid depending on the set of allocatable
844  // registers being larger than the set of parameter registers.
845  param_regs_.clear(reg);
846  return reg;
847  }
848  DCHECK(location_.IsCallerFrameSlot());
849  LiftoffRegister reg = compiler_->asm_.GetUnusedRegister(rc_, pinned);
850  compiler_->asm_.LoadCallerFrameSlot(reg, -location_.AsCallerFrameSlot(),
851  reg_kind_);
852  return reg;
853  }
854 
855  // Input 0 is the code target, 1 is the instance data.
856  static constexpr uint32_t kFirstInputIdx = 2;
857 
858  LiftoffCompiler* compiler_;
859  const uint32_t num_params_;
860  uint32_t param_idx_{0};
861  uint32_t input_idx_{kFirstInputIdx};
862  ValueKind kind_;
863  bool needs_gp_pair_;
864  ValueKind reg_kind_;
865  RegClass rc_;
866  LinkageLocation location_{LinkageLocation::ForAnyRegister()};
867  LiftoffRegList param_regs_;
868  };
869 
870  void StackCheck(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmCodePosition position) {
871  CODE_COMMENT("stack check");
872  if (!v8_flags.wasm_stack_checks) return;
873 
874  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save = __ cache_state()->used_registers;
875  // The cached instance data will be reloaded separately.
876  if (__ cache_state()->cached_instance_data != no_reg) {
877  DCHECK(regs_to_save.has(__ cache_state()->cached_instance_data));
878  regs_to_save.clear(__ cache_state()->cached_instance_data);
879  }
880  SpilledRegistersForInspection* spilled_regs = nullptr;
881 
882  OutOfLineSafepointInfo* safepoint_info =
883  zone_->New<OutOfLineSafepointInfo>(zone_);
884  __ cache_state()->GetTaggedSlotsForOOLCode(
885  &safepoint_info->slots, &safepoint_info->spills,
886  for_debugging_
887  ? LiftoffAssembler::CacheState::SpillLocation::kStackSlots
888  : LiftoffAssembler::CacheState::SpillLocation::kTopOfStack);
889  if (V8_UNLIKELY(for_debugging_)) {
890  // When debugging, we do not just push all registers to the stack, but we
891  // spill them to their proper stack locations such that we can inspect
892  // them.
893  // The only exception is the cached memory start, which we just push
894  // before the stack check and pop afterwards.
895  regs_to_save = {};
896  if (__ cache_state()->cached_mem_start != no_reg) {
897  regs_to_save.set(__ cache_state()->cached_mem_start);
898  }
899  spilled_regs = GetSpilledRegistersForInspection();
900  }
901  out_of_line_code_.push_back(OutOfLineCode::StackCheck(
902  zone_, position, regs_to_save, __ cache_state()->cached_instance_data,
903  spilled_regs, safepoint_info, RegisterOOLDebugSideTableEntry(decoder)));
904  OutOfLineCode& ool = out_of_line_code_.back();
905  __ StackCheck(ool.label.get());
906  __ bind(ool.continuation.get());
907  }
908 
909  void TierupCheck(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmCodePosition position,
910  int budget_used) {
911  if (for_debugging_ != kNotForDebugging) return;
912  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("tierup check");
913  budget_used += kTierUpCostForCheck;
914  // We never want to blow the entire budget at once.
915  const int max_budget_use = std::max(1, v8_flags.wasm_tiering_budget / 4);
916  if (budget_used > max_budget_use) budget_used = max_budget_use;
917 
918  // We should always decrement the budget, and we don't expect integer
919  // overflows in the budget calculation.
920  DCHECK_LE(1, budget_used);
921 
922  SpilledRegistersForInspection* spilled_regs = nullptr;
923 
924  OutOfLineSafepointInfo* safepoint_info =
925  zone_->New<OutOfLineSafepointInfo>(zone_);
926  __ cache_state()->GetTaggedSlotsForOOLCode(
927  &safepoint_info->slots, &safepoint_info->spills,
928  LiftoffAssembler::CacheState::SpillLocation::kTopOfStack);
929 
930  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save = __ cache_state()->used_registers;
931  // The cached instance will be reloaded separately.
932  if (__ cache_state()->cached_instance_data != no_reg) {
933  DCHECK(regs_to_save.has(__ cache_state()->cached_instance_data));
934  regs_to_save.clear(__ cache_state()->cached_instance_data);
935  }
936 
937  out_of_line_code_.push_back(OutOfLineCode::TierupCheck(
938  zone_, position, regs_to_save, __ cache_state()->cached_instance_data,
939  spilled_regs, safepoint_info, RegisterOOLDebugSideTableEntry(decoder)));
940  OutOfLineCode& ool = out_of_line_code_.back();
941 
942  FREEZE_STATE(tierup_check);
943  __ CheckTierUp(declared_function_index(env_->module, func_index_),
944  budget_used, ool.label.get(), tierup_check);
945 
946  __ bind(ool.continuation.get());
947  }
948 
949  bool SpillLocalsInitially(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t num_params) {
950  int actual_locals = __ num_locals() - num_params;
951  DCHECK_LE(0, actual_locals);
952  constexpr int kNumCacheRegisters = kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs.Count();
953  // If we have many locals, we put them on the stack initially. This avoids
954  // having to spill them on merge points. Use of these initial values should
955  // be rare anyway.
956  if (actual_locals > kNumCacheRegisters / 2) return true;
957  // If there are locals which are not i32 or i64, we also spill all locals,
958  // because other types cannot be initialized to constants.
959  for (uint32_t param_idx = num_params; param_idx < __ num_locals();
960  ++param_idx) {
961  ValueKind kind = __ local_kind(param_idx);
962  if (kind != kI32 && kind != kI64) return true;
963  }
964  return false;
965  }
966 
967  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void TraceFunctionEntry(FullDecoder* decoder) {
968  CODE_COMMENT("trace function entry");
969  __ SpillAllRegisters();
970  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
971  __ pc_offset(), SourcePosition(decoder->position()), false);
972  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmTraceEnter);
973  DefineSafepoint();
974  }
975 
976  bool dynamic_tiering() {
977  return v8_flags.wasm_dynamic_tiering &&
978  for_debugging_ == kNotForDebugging &&
979  (v8_flags.wasm_tier_up_filter == -1 ||
980  v8_flags.wasm_tier_up_filter == func_index_);
981  }
982 
983  void StartFunctionBody(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {
984  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < __ num_locals(); ++i) {
985  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, __ local_kind(i), "param")) return;
986  }
987 
988  // Parameter 0 is the instance data.
989  uint32_t num_params =
990  static_cast<uint32_t>(decoder->sig_->parameter_count());
991 
992  __ CodeEntry();
993 
994 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_HARDWARE_SUPPORT
995  // Wasm code should always execute in sandboxed mode.
996  __ AssertInSandboxedExecutionMode();
997 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_HARDWARE_SUPPORT
998 
999  if (v8_flags.wasm_inlining) {
1000  CODE_COMMENT("frame setup");
1001  int declared_func_index =
1002  func_index_ - env_->module->num_imported_functions;
1003  DCHECK_GE(declared_func_index, 0);
1004  __ CallFrameSetupStub(declared_func_index);
1005  } else {
1006  __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::WASM);
1007  }
1008  __ set_has_frame(true);
1009  pc_offset_stack_frame_construction_ = __ PrepareStackFrame();
1010  // {PrepareStackFrame} is the first platform-specific assembler method.
1011  // If this failed, we can bail out immediately, avoiding runtime overhead
1012  // and potential failures because of other unimplemented methods.
1013  // A platform implementing {PrepareStackFrame} must ensure that we can
1014  // finish compilation without errors even if we hit unimplemented
1015  // LiftoffAssembler methods.
1016  if (DidAssemblerBailout(decoder)) return;
1017 
1018  // Input 0 is the call target, the trusted instance data is at 1.
1019  [[maybe_unused]] constexpr int kInstanceDataParameterIndex = 1;
1020  // Check that {kWasmImplicitArgRegister} matches our call descriptor.
1021  DCHECK_EQ(kWasmImplicitArgRegister,
1022  Register::from_code(
1023  descriptor_->GetInputLocation(kInstanceDataParameterIndex)
1024  .AsRegister()));
1025  __ cache_state() -> SetInstanceCacheRegister(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
1026 
1027  if (num_params) {
1028  CODE_COMMENT("process parameters");
1029  ParameterProcessor processor(this, num_params);
1030  processor.Process();
1031  }
1032  int params_size = __ TopSpillOffset();
1033 
1034  // Initialize locals beyond parameters.
1035  if (num_params < __ num_locals()) CODE_COMMENT("init locals");
1036  if (SpillLocalsInitially(decoder, num_params)) {
1037  bool has_refs = false;
1038  for (uint32_t param_idx = num_params; param_idx < __ num_locals();
1039  ++param_idx) {
1040  ValueKind kind = __ local_kind(param_idx);
1041  has_refs |= is_reference(kind);
1042  __ PushStack(kind);
1043  }
1044  int spill_size = __ TopSpillOffset() - params_size;
1045  __ FillStackSlotsWithZero(params_size, spill_size);
1046 
1047  // Initialize all reference type locals with ref.null.
1048  if (has_refs) {
1049  LiftoffRegList pinned;
1050  Register null_ref_reg =
1051  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp());
1052  Register wasm_null_ref_reg =
1053  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp());
1054  LoadNullValue(null_ref_reg, kWasmExternRef);
1055  LoadNullValue(wasm_null_ref_reg, kWasmAnyRef);
1056  for (uint32_t local_index = num_params; local_index < __ num_locals();
1057  ++local_index) {
1058  ValueType type = decoder->local_types_[local_index];
1059  if (type.is_reference()) {
1060  __ Spill(__ cache_state()->stack_state[local_index].offset(),
1061  type.use_wasm_null() ? LiftoffRegister(wasm_null_ref_reg)
1062  : LiftoffRegister(null_ref_reg),
1063  type.kind());
1064  }
1065  }
1066  }
1067  } else {
1068  for (uint32_t param_idx = num_params; param_idx < __ num_locals();
1069  ++param_idx) {
1070  ValueKind kind = __ local_kind(param_idx);
1071  // Anything which is not i32 or i64 requires spilling.
1072  DCHECK(kind == kI32 || kind == kI64);
1073  __ PushConstant(kind, int32_t{0});
1074  }
1075  }
1076 
1077  DCHECK_EQ(__ num_locals(), __ cache_state()->stack_height());
1078 
1079  if (V8_UNLIKELY(debug_sidetable_builder_)) {
1080  debug_sidetable_builder_->SetNumLocals(__ num_locals());
1081  }
1082 
1083  if (V8_UNLIKELY(for_debugging_)) {
1084  __ ResetOSRTarget();
1085  if (V8_UNLIKELY(max_steps_)) {
1086  // Generate the single OOL code to jump to if {max_steps_} have been
1087  // executed.
1088  DCHECK_EQ(0, out_of_line_code_.size());
1089  // This trap is never intercepted (e.g. by a debugger), so we do not
1090  // need safepoint information (which would be difficult to compute if
1091  // the OOL code is shared).
1092  out_of_line_code_.push_back(OutOfLineCode::Trap(
1093  zone_, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapUnreachable, decoder->position(),
1094  nullptr, nullptr, nullptr));
1095 
1096  // Subtract 16 steps for the function call itself (including the
1097  // function prologue), plus 1 for each local (including parameters). Do
1098  // this only *after* setting up the frame completely, even though we
1099  // already executed the work then.
1100  CheckMaxSteps(decoder, 16 + __ num_locals());
1101  }
1102  } else {
1103  DCHECK(!max_steps_);
1104  }
1105 
1106  // If debug code is enabled, assert that the first parameter is a
1107  // WasmTrustedInstanceData.
1108  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
1109  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("Check instance data parameter type");
1110  LiftoffRegList pinned;
1111  Register scratch = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
1112  Register instance = pinned.set(LoadInstanceIntoRegister(pinned, scratch));
1113  // Load the map.
1114  __ LoadMap(scratch, instance);
1115  // Load the instance type.
1116  __ Load(LiftoffRegister{scratch}, scratch, no_reg,
1117  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(Map::kInstanceTypeOffset),
1118  LoadType::kI32Load16U);
1119  // If not WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_TYPE -> error.
1120  Label ok;
1121  FreezeCacheState frozen{asm_};
1122  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kEqual, &ok, scratch,
1123  WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_TYPE, frozen);
1124  __ AssertUnreachable(AbortReason::kUnexpectedInstanceType);
1125  __ bind(&ok);
1126  }
1127 
1128  // The function-prologue stack check is associated with position 0, which
1129  // is never a position of any instruction in the function.
1130  StackCheck(decoder, 0);
1131 
1132  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm)) TraceFunctionEntry(decoder);
1133  }
1134 
1135  void GenerateOutOfLineCode(OutOfLineCode* ool) {
1136  CODE_COMMENT((std::string("OOL: ") + Builtins::name(ool->builtin)).c_str());
1137  __ bind(ool->label.get());
1138  const bool is_stack_check =
1139  ool->builtin == Builtin::kWasmStackGuard ||
1140  ool->builtin == Builtin::kWasmGrowableStackGuard;
1141  const bool is_tierup = ool->builtin == Builtin::kWasmTriggerTierUp;
1142 
1143  if (!ool->regs_to_save.is_empty()) {
1144  __ PushRegisters(ool->regs_to_save);
1145  }
1146  if (V8_UNLIKELY(ool->spilled_registers != nullptr)) {
1147  for (auto& entry : ool->spilled_registers->entries) {
1148  // We should not push and spill the same register.
1149  DCHECK(!ool->regs_to_save.has(entry.reg));
1150  __ Spill(entry.offset, entry.reg, entry.kind);
1151  }
1152  }
1153 
1154  if (ool->builtin == Builtin::kWasmGrowableStackGuard) {
1155  WasmGrowableStackGuardDescriptor descriptor;
1156  DCHECK_EQ(0, descriptor.GetStackParameterCount());
1157  DCHECK_EQ(1, descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount());
1158  Register param_reg = descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(0);
1159  __ LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(param_reg),
1160  WasmValue::ForUintPtr(descriptor_->ParameterSlotCount() *
1161  kSystemPointerSize));
1162  }
1163 
1164  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
1165  __ pc_offset(), SourcePosition(ool->position), true);
1166  __ CallBuiltin(ool->builtin);
1167  // It is safe to not check for existing safepoint at this address since we
1168  // just emitted a call.
1169  auto safepoint = safepoint_table_builder_.DefineSafepoint(&asm_);
1170 
1171  if (ool->safepoint_info) {
1172  for (auto index : ool->safepoint_info->slots) {
1173  safepoint.DefineTaggedStackSlot(index);
1174  }
1175 
1176  int total_frame_size = __ GetTotalFrameSize();
1177  // {total_frame_size} is the highest offset from the FP that is used to
1178  // store a value. The offset of the first spill slot should therefore be
1179  // {(total_frame_size / kSystemPointerSize) + 1}. However, spill slots
1180  // don't start at offset '0' but at offset '-1' (or
1181  // {-kSystemPointerSize}). Therefore we have to add another '+ 1' to the
1182  // index of the first spill slot.
1183  int index = (total_frame_size / kSystemPointerSize) + 2;
1184 
1185  __ RecordSpillsInSafepoint(safepoint, ool->regs_to_save,
1186  ool->safepoint_info->spills, index);
1187  }
1188 
1189  DCHECK_EQ(!debug_sidetable_builder_, !ool->debug_sidetable_entry_builder);
1190  if (V8_UNLIKELY(ool->debug_sidetable_entry_builder)) {
1191  ool->debug_sidetable_entry_builder->set_pc_offset(__ pc_offset());
1192  }
1193  DCHECK_EQ(ool->continuation.get()->is_bound(), is_stack_check || is_tierup);
1194  if (is_stack_check) {
1195  MaybeOSR();
1196  }
1197  if (!ool->regs_to_save.is_empty()) __ PopRegisters(ool->regs_to_save);
1198  if (is_stack_check || is_tierup) {
1199  if (V8_UNLIKELY(ool->spilled_registers != nullptr)) {
1200  DCHECK(for_debugging_);
1201  for (auto& entry : ool->spilled_registers->entries) {
1202  __ Fill(entry.reg, entry.offset, entry.kind);
1203  }
1204  }
1205  if (ool->cached_instance_data != no_reg) {
1206  __ LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(ool->cached_instance_data);
1207  }
1208  __ emit_jump(ool->continuation.get());
1209  } else {
1210  __ AssertUnreachable(AbortReason::kUnexpectedReturnFromWasmTrap);
1211  }
1212  }
1213 
1214  void FinishFunction(FullDecoder* decoder) {
1215  if (DidAssemblerBailout(decoder)) return;
1216  __ AlignFrameSize();
1217 #if DEBUG
1218  int frame_size = __ GetTotalFrameSize();
1219 #endif
1220  for (OutOfLineCode& ool : out_of_line_code_) {
1221  GenerateOutOfLineCode(&ool);
1222  }
1223  DCHECK_EQ(frame_size, __ GetTotalFrameSize());
1224  __ PatchPrepareStackFrame(pc_offset_stack_frame_construction_,
1225  &safepoint_table_builder_, v8_flags.wasm_inlining,
1226  descriptor_->ParameterSlotCount());
1227  __ FinishCode();
1228  safepoint_table_builder_.Emit(&asm_, __ GetTotalFrameSlotCountForGC());
1229  // Emit the handler table.
1230  if (!handlers_.empty()) {
1231  handler_table_offset_ = HandlerTable::EmitReturnTableStart(&asm_);
1232  for (auto& handler : handlers_) {
1233  HandlerTable::EmitReturnEntry(&asm_, handler.pc_offset,
1234  handler.handler.get()->pos());
1235  }
1236  }
1237  __ MaybeEmitOutOfLineConstantPool();
1238  // The previous calls may have also generated a bailout.
1239  DidAssemblerBailout(decoder);
1240  DCHECK_EQ(num_exceptions_, 0);
1241 
1242  if (v8_flags.wasm_inlining && !encountered_call_instructions_.empty()) {
1243  // Update the call targets stored in the WasmModule.
1244  TypeFeedbackStorage& type_feedback = env_->module->type_feedback;
1245  base::MutexGuard mutex_guard(&type_feedback.mutex);
1246  FunctionTypeFeedback& function_feedback =
1247  type_feedback.feedback_for_function[func_index_];
1248  function_feedback.liftoff_frame_size = __ GetTotalFrameSize();
1249  base::OwnedVector<uint32_t>& call_targets =
1250  function_feedback.call_targets;
1251  if (call_targets.empty()) {
1252  call_targets = base::OwnedCopyOf(encountered_call_instructions_);
1253  } else {
1254  DCHECK_EQ(call_targets.as_vector(),
1255  base::VectorOf(encountered_call_instructions_));
1256  }
1257  }
1258 
1259  if (frame_description_) {
1260  frame_description_->total_frame_size = __ GetTotalFrameSize();
1261  }
1262  }
1263 
1264  void OnFirstError(FullDecoder* decoder) {
1265  if (!did_bailout()) bailout_reason_ = kDecodeError;
1266  UnuseLabels(decoder);
1267  asm_.AbortCompilation();
1268  }
1269 
1270  // Rule of thumb: an instruction is "heavy" when its runtime is linear in
1271  // some random variable that the fuzzer generates.
1272 #define FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION \
1273  do { \
1274  if (V8_UNLIKELY(max_steps_ != nullptr)) { \
1275  CheckMaxSteps(decoder, kHeavyInstructionSteps); \
1276  } \
1277  } while (false)
1278 
1279  V8_NOINLINE void CheckMaxSteps(FullDecoder* decoder, int steps_done = 1) {
1280  DCHECK_LE(1, steps_done);
1281  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("check max steps");
1282  LiftoffRegList pinned;
1283  LiftoffRegister max_steps = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {}));
1284  LiftoffRegister max_steps_addr =
1285  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
1286  {
1287  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
1288  __ LoadConstant(
1289  max_steps_addr,
1290  WasmValue::ForUintPtr(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(max_steps_)));
1291  __ Load(max_steps, max_steps_addr.gp(), no_reg, 0, LoadType::kI32Load);
1292  // Subtract first (and store the result), so the caller sees that
1293  // max_steps ran negative. Since we never subtract too much at once, we
1294  // cannot underflow.
1295  DCHECK_GE(kMaxInt / 16, steps_done); // An arbitrary limit.
1296  __ emit_i32_subi(max_steps.gp(), max_steps.gp(), steps_done);
1297  __ Store(max_steps_addr.gp(), no_reg, 0, max_steps, StoreType::kI32Store,
1298  pinned);
1299  // Abort if max steps have been executed.
1300  DCHECK_EQ(Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapUnreachable,
1301  out_of_line_code_.front().builtin);
1302  Label* trap_label = out_of_line_code_.front().label.get();
1303  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kLessThan, trap_label, max_steps.gp(), 0, frozen);
1304  }
1305  }
1306 
1307  V8_NOINLINE void EmitDebuggingInfo(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode) {
1308  DCHECK(for_debugging_);
1309 
1310  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.wasm_code_coverage && (opcode != kExprLoop))) {
1311  // Coverage instrumention for 'loop' instructions is emitted in Loop().
1312  EmitCoverageInstrumentationIfReachable(decoder, opcode);
1313  }
1314 
1315  // Snapshot the value types (from the decoder) here, for potentially
1316  // building a debug side table entry later. Arguments will have been popped
1317  // from the stack later (when we need them), and Liftoff does not keep
1318  // precise type information.
1319  stack_value_types_for_debugging_ = GetStackValueTypesForDebugging(decoder);
1320 
1321  if (!WasmOpcodes::IsBreakable(opcode)) return;
1322 
1323  bool has_breakpoint = false;
1324  if (next_breakpoint_ptr_) {
1325  if (*next_breakpoint_ptr_ == 0) {
1326  // A single breakpoint at offset 0 indicates stepping.
1327  DCHECK_EQ(next_breakpoint_ptr_ + 1, next_breakpoint_end_);
1328  has_breakpoint = true;
1329  } else {
1330  while (next_breakpoint_ptr_ != next_breakpoint_end_ &&
1331  *next_breakpoint_ptr_ < decoder->position()) {
1332  // Skip unreachable breakpoints.
1333  ++next_breakpoint_ptr_;
1334  }
1335  if (next_breakpoint_ptr_ == next_breakpoint_end_) {
1336  next_breakpoint_ptr_ = next_breakpoint_end_ = nullptr;
1337  } else if (*next_breakpoint_ptr_ == decoder->position()) {
1338  has_breakpoint = true;
1339  }
1340  }
1341  }
1342  if (has_breakpoint) {
1343  CODE_COMMENT("breakpoint");
1344  EmitBreakpoint(decoder);
1345  // Once we emitted an unconditional breakpoint, we don't need to check
1346  // function entry breaks any more.
1347  did_function_entry_break_checks_ = true;
1348  } else if (!did_function_entry_break_checks_) {
1349  did_function_entry_break_checks_ = true;
1350  CODE_COMMENT("check function entry break");
1351  Label do_break;
1352  Label no_break;
1353  Register flag = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {}).gp();
1354 
1355  // Check the "hook on function call" flag. If set, trigger a break.
1356  LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(flag, HookOnFunctionCallAddress, kSystemPointerSize,
1357  {});
1358  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
1359  __ Load(LiftoffRegister{flag}, flag, no_reg, 0, LoadType::kI32Load8U, {});
1360  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotZero, &do_break, kI32, flag, no_reg, frozen);
1361 
1362  // Check if we should stop on "script entry".
1363  LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(flag, BreakOnEntry, kUInt8Size, {});
1364  __ emit_cond_jump(kZero, &no_break, kI32, flag, no_reg, frozen);
1365 
1366  __ bind(&do_break);
1367  EmitBreakpoint(decoder);
1368  __ bind(&no_break);
1369  } else if (dead_breakpoint_ == decoder->position()) {
1370  DCHECK(!next_breakpoint_ptr_ ||
1371  *next_breakpoint_ptr_ != dead_breakpoint_);
1372  // The top frame is paused at this position, but the breakpoint was
1373  // removed. Adding a dead breakpoint here ensures that the source
1374  // position exists, and that the offset to the return address is the
1375  // same as in the old code.
1376  CODE_COMMENT("dead breakpoint");
1377  Label cont;
1378  __ emit_jump(&cont);
1379  EmitBreakpoint(decoder);
1380  __ bind(&cont);
1381  }
1382  if (V8_UNLIKELY(max_steps_ != nullptr)) {
1383  CheckMaxSteps(decoder);
1384  }
1385  }
1386 
1387  void EmitCoverageInstrumentationIfReachable(FullDecoder* decoder,
1388  WasmOpcode opcode) {
1389  if (!decoder->control_at(0)->reachable()) return;
1390 
1391  if (coverage_current_code_range_ == coverage_code_ranges_.end()) return;
1392 
1393  while (coverage_current_code_range_->end < decoder->position()) {
1394  ++coverage_current_code_range_;
1395  }
1396  if (coverage_current_code_range_->start <= decoder->position()) {
1397  // Emit code coverage instrumentation.
1398  __ emit_inc_i32_at(
1399  coverage_count_array_addr_ +
1400  (coverage_current_code_range_ - coverage_code_ranges_.begin()) *
1401  sizeof(uint32_t));
1402  ++coverage_current_code_range_;
1403  }
1404  }
1405 
1406  void NextInstruction(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode) {
1407  TraceCacheState(decoder);
1408  SLOW_DCHECK(__ ValidateCacheState());
1409  CODE_COMMENT(WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(
1410  WasmOpcodes::IsPrefixOpcode(opcode)
1411  ? decoder->read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(decoder->pc()).first
1412  : opcode));
1413 
1414  if (!has_outstanding_op() && decoder->control_at(0)->reachable()) {
1415  // Decoder stack and liftoff stack have to be in sync if current code
1416  // path is reachable.
1417  DCHECK_EQ(decoder->stack_size() + __ num_locals() + num_exceptions_,
1418  __ cache_state()->stack_state.size());
1419  }
1420 
1421  // Add a single check, so that the fast path can be inlined while
1422  // {EmitDebuggingInfo} stays outlined.
1423  if (V8_UNLIKELY(for_debugging_)) {
1424  EmitDebuggingInfo(decoder, opcode);
1425  }
1426  }
1427 
1428  void EmitBreakpoint(FullDecoder* decoder) {
1429  DCHECK(for_debugging_);
1430  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
1431  __ pc_offset(), SourcePosition(decoder->position()), true);
1432  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmDebugBreak);
1433  DefineSafepointWithCalleeSavedRegisters();
1434  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder,
1435  DebugSideTableBuilder::kAllowRegisters);
1436  MaybeOSR();
1437  }
1438 
1439  void PushControl(Control* block) {
1440  // The Liftoff stack includes implicit exception refs stored for catch
1441  // blocks, so that they can be rethrown.
1442  block->num_exceptions = num_exceptions_;
1443  }
1444 
1445  void Block(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) { PushControl(block); }
1446 
1447  void Loop(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* loop) {
1448  // Before entering a loop, spill all locals to the stack, in order to free
1449  // the cache registers, and to avoid unnecessarily reloading stack values
1450  // into registers at branches.
1451  // TODO(clemensb): Come up with a better strategy here, involving
1452  // pre-analysis of the function.
1453  __ SpillLocals();
1454 
1455  __ SpillLoopArgs(loop->start_merge.arity);
1456 
1457  // Loop labels bind at the beginning of the block.
1458  __ bind(loop->label.get());
1459 
1460  // Save the current cache state for the merge when jumping to this loop.
1461  loop->label_state.Split(*__ cache_state());
1462 
1463  PushControl(loop);
1464 
1465  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.wasm_code_coverage)) {
1466  EmitCoverageInstrumentationIfReachable(decoder, kExprLoop);
1467  }
1468 
1469  if (!dynamic_tiering()) {
1470  // When the budget-based tiering mechanism is enabled, use that to
1471  // check for interrupt requests; otherwise execute a stack check in the
1472  // loop header.
1473  StackCheck(decoder, decoder->position());
1474  }
1475  }
1476 
1477  void Try(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {
1478  block->try_info = zone_->New<TryInfo>(zone_);
1479  PushControl(block);
1480  }
1481 
1482  // Load the property in {kReturnRegister0}.
1483  LiftoffRegister GetExceptionProperty(const VarState& exception,
1484  RootIndex root_index) {
1485  DCHECK(root_index == RootIndex::kwasm_exception_tag_symbol ||
1486  root_index == RootIndex::kwasm_exception_values_symbol);
1487 
1488  LiftoffRegList pinned;
1489  LiftoffRegister tag_symbol_reg =
1490  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
1491  LoadExceptionSymbol(tag_symbol_reg.gp(), pinned, root_index);
1492  LiftoffRegister context_reg =
1493  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
1494  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(context_reg.gp(), NativeContext, pinned);
1495 
1496  VarState tag_symbol{kRef, tag_symbol_reg, 0};
1497  VarState context{kRef, context_reg, 0};
1498 
1499  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmGetOwnProperty,
1500  MakeSig::Returns(kRef).Params(kRef, kRef, kRef),
1501  {exception, tag_symbol, context}, kNoSourcePosition);
1502 
1503  return LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0);
1504  }
1505 
1506  void CatchException(FullDecoder* decoder, const TagIndexImmediate& imm,
1507  Control* block, base::Vector<Value> values) {
1508  DCHECK(block->is_try_catch());
1509  __ emit_jump(block->label.get());
1510 
1511  // This is the last use of this label. Reuse the field for the label of the
1512  // next catch block, and jump there if the tag does not match.
1513  __ bind(&block->try_info->catch_label);
1514  block->try_info->catch_label.Unuse();
1515  block->try_info->catch_label.UnuseNear();
1516 
1517  __ cache_state()->Split(block->try_info->catch_state);
1518 
1519  CODE_COMMENT("load caught exception tag");
1520  DCHECK_EQ(__ cache_state()->stack_state.back().kind(), kRef);
1521  LiftoffRegister caught_tag =
1522  GetExceptionProperty(__ cache_state()->stack_state.back(),
1523  RootIndex::kwasm_exception_tag_symbol);
1524  LiftoffRegList pinned;
1525  pinned.set(caught_tag);
1526 
1527  CODE_COMMENT("load expected exception tag");
1528  Register imm_tag = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
1529  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(imm_tag, TagsTable, pinned);
1530  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
1531  imm_tag, imm_tag, no_reg,
1532  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(imm.index));
1533 
1534  CODE_COMMENT("compare tags");
1535 
1536  if (imm.tag->sig->parameter_count() == 1 &&
1537  imm.tag->sig->GetParam(0) == kWasmExternRef) {
1538  // Check for the special case where the tag is WebAssembly.JSTag and the
1539  // exception is not a WebAssembly.Exception. In this case the exception is
1540  // caught and pushed on the operand stack.
1541  // Only perform this check if the tag signature is the same as
1542  // the JSTag signature, i.e. a single externref, otherwise we know
1543  // statically that it cannot be the JSTag.
1544  LiftoffRegister undefined =
1545  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
1546  __ LoadFullPointer(
1547  undefined.gp(), kRootRegister,
1548  IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
1549  LiftoffRegister js_tag = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
1550  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(js_tag.gp(), NativeContext, pinned);
1551  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
1552  js_tag.gp(), js_tag.gp(), no_reg,
1553  NativeContext::SlotOffset(Context::WASM_JS_TAG_INDEX));
1554  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
1555  js_tag.gp(), js_tag.gp(), no_reg,
1556  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTagObject::kTagOffset));
1557  {
1558  LiftoffAssembler::CacheState initial_state(zone_);
1559  LiftoffAssembler::CacheState end_state(zone_);
1560  Label js_exception;
1561  Label done;
1562  Label uncaught;
1563  initial_state.Split(*__ cache_state());
1564  {
1565  FREEZE_STATE(state_merged_explicitly);
1566  // If the tag is undefined, this is not a wasm exception. Go to a
1567  // different block to process the JS exception. Otherwise compare it
1568  // with the expected tag.
1569  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &js_exception, kRefNull, caught_tag.gp(),
1570  undefined.gp(), state_merged_explicitly);
1571  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &uncaught, kRefNull, imm_tag,
1572  caught_tag.gp(), state_merged_explicitly);
1573  }
1574  // Case 1: A wasm exception with a matching tag.
1575  GetExceptionValues(decoder, __ cache_state()->stack_state.back(),
1576  imm.tag);
1577  // GetExceptionValues modified the cache state. Remember the new state
1578  // to merge the end state of case 2 into it.
1579  end_state.Steal(*__ cache_state());
1580  __ emit_jump(&done);
1581 
1582  __ bind(&js_exception);
1583  __ cache_state()->Split(initial_state);
1584  {
1585  FREEZE_STATE(state_merged_explicitly);
1586  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &uncaught, kRefNull, imm_tag,
1587  js_tag.gp(), state_merged_explicitly);
1588  }
1589  // Case 2: A JS exception, and the expected tag is JSTag.
1590  // TODO(thibaudm): Can we avoid some state splitting/stealing by
1591  // reserving this register earlier and not modifying the state in this
1592  // block?
1593  LiftoffRegister exception = __ PeekToRegister(0, pinned);
1594  __ PushRegister(kRef, exception);
1595  // The exception is now on the stack twice: once as an implicit operand
1596  // for rethrow, and once as the "unpacked" value.
1597  __ MergeFullStackWith(end_state);
1598  __ emit_jump(&done);
1599 
1600  // Case 3: Either a wasm exception with a mismatching tag, or a JS
1601  // exception but the expected tag is not JSTag.
1602  __ bind(&uncaught);
1603  __ cache_state()->Steal(initial_state);
1604  __ MergeFullStackWith(block->try_info->catch_state);
1605  __ emit_jump(&block->try_info->catch_label);
1606 
1607  __ bind(&done);
1608  __ cache_state()->Steal(end_state);
1609  }
1610  } else {
1611  {
1612  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
1613  Label caught;
1614  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &caught, kRefNull, imm_tag, caught_tag.gp(),
1615  frozen);
1616  // The tags don't match, merge the current state into the catch state
1617  // and jump to the next handler.
1618  __ MergeFullStackWith(block->try_info->catch_state);
1619  __ emit_jump(&block->try_info->catch_label);
1620  __ bind(&caught);
1621  }
1622  GetExceptionValues(decoder, __ cache_state()->stack_state.back(),
1623  imm.tag);
1624  }
1625  if (!block->try_info->in_handler) {
1626  block->try_info->in_handler = true;
1627  num_exceptions_++;
1628  }
1629  }
1630 
1631  void Rethrow(FullDecoder* decoder, const VarState& exception) {
1632  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmRethrow, MakeSig::Params(kRef), {exception},
1633  decoder->position());
1634  }
1635 
1636  void Delegate(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t depth, Control* block) {
1637  DCHECK_EQ(block, decoder->control_at(0));
1638  Control* target = decoder->control_at(depth);
1639  DCHECK(block->is_incomplete_try());
1640  __ bind(&block->try_info->catch_label);
1641  if (block->try_info->catch_reached) {
1642  __ cache_state()->Steal(block->try_info->catch_state);
1643  if (depth == decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
1644  // Delegate to the caller, do not emit a landing pad.
1645  Rethrow(decoder, __ cache_state()->stack_state.back());
1646  MaybeOSR();
1647  } else {
1648  DCHECK(target->is_incomplete_try());
1649  if (target->try_info->catch_reached) {
1650  __ MergeStackWith(target->try_info->catch_state, 1,
1651  LiftoffAssembler::kForwardJump);
1652  } else {
1653  target->try_info->catch_state = __ MergeIntoNewState(
1654  __ num_locals(), 1, target->stack_depth + target->num_exceptions);
1655  target->try_info->catch_reached = true;
1656  }
1657  __ emit_jump(&target->try_info->catch_label);
1658  }
1659  }
1660  }
1661 
1662  void Rethrow(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* try_block) {
1663  int index = try_block->try_info->catch_state.stack_height() - 1;
1664  auto& exception = __ cache_state()->stack_state[index];
1665  Rethrow(decoder, exception);
1666  int pc_offset = __ pc_offset();
1667  MaybeOSR();
1668  EmitLandingPad(decoder, pc_offset);
1669  }
1670 
1671  void CatchAll(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {
1672  DCHECK(block->is_try_catchall() || block->is_try_catch());
1673  DCHECK_EQ(decoder->control_at(0), block);
1674  __ bind(&block->try_info->catch_label);
1675  __ cache_state()->Split(block->try_info->catch_state);
1676  if (!block->try_info->in_handler) {
1677  block->try_info->in_handler = true;
1678  num_exceptions_++;
1679  }
1680  }
1681 
1682  void TryTable(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {
1683  block->try_info = zone_->New<TryInfo>(zone_);
1684  PushControl(block);
1685  }
1686 
1687  void CatchCase(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block,
1688  const CatchCase& catch_case, base::Vector<Value> values) {
1689  DCHECK(block->is_try_table());
1690 
1691  // This is the last use of this label. Reuse the field for the label of the
1692  // next catch block, and jump there if the tag does not match.
1693  __ bind(&block->try_info->catch_label);
1694  block->try_info->catch_label.Unuse();
1695  block->try_info->catch_label.UnuseNear();
1696  __ cache_state()->Split(block->try_info->catch_state);
1697 
1698  if (catch_case.kind == kCatchAll || catch_case.kind == kCatchAllRef) {
1699  // The landing pad pushed the exception on the stack, so keep
1700  // it there for {kCatchAllRef}, and drop it for {kCatchAll}.
1701  if (catch_case.kind == kCatchAll) {
1702  __ DropValues(1);
1703  }
1704  BrOrRet(decoder, catch_case.br_imm.depth);
1705  return;
1706  }
1707 
1708  CODE_COMMENT("load caught exception tag");
1709  DCHECK_EQ(__ cache_state()->stack_state.back().kind(), kRef);
1710  LiftoffRegister caught_tag =
1711  GetExceptionProperty(__ cache_state()->stack_state.back(),
1712  RootIndex::kwasm_exception_tag_symbol);
1713  LiftoffRegList pinned;
1714  pinned.set(caught_tag);
1715 
1716  CODE_COMMENT("load expected exception tag");
1717  Register imm_tag = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
1718  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(imm_tag, TagsTable, pinned);
1719  __ LoadTaggedPointer(imm_tag, imm_tag, no_reg,
1720  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(
1721  catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.index));
1722 
1723  VarState exn = __ cache_state() -> stack_state.back();
1724 
1725  CODE_COMMENT("compare tags");
1726  if (catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.tag->sig->parameter_count() == 1 &&
1727  catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.tag->sig->GetParam(0) == kWasmExternRef) {
1728  // Check for the special case where the tag is WebAssembly.JSTag and the
1729  // exception is not a WebAssembly.Exception. In this case the exception is
1730  // caught and pushed on the operand stack.
1731  // Only perform this check if the tag signature is the same as
1732  // the JSTag signature, i.e. a single externref, otherwise we know
1733  // statically that it cannot be the JSTag.
1734  LiftoffRegister undefined =
1735  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
1736  __ LoadFullPointer(
1737  undefined.gp(), kRootRegister,
1738  IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
1739  LiftoffRegister js_tag = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
1740  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(js_tag.gp(), NativeContext, pinned);
1741  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
1742  js_tag.gp(), js_tag.gp(), no_reg,
1743  NativeContext::SlotOffset(Context::WASM_JS_TAG_INDEX));
1744  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
1745  js_tag.gp(), js_tag.gp(), no_reg,
1746  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTagObject::kTagOffset));
1747  {
1748  LiftoffAssembler::CacheState initial_state(zone_);
1749  LiftoffAssembler::CacheState end_state(zone_);
1750  Label js_exception;
1751  Label done;
1752  Label uncaught;
1753  initial_state.Split(*__ cache_state());
1754  {
1755  FREEZE_STATE(state_merged_explicitly);
1756  // If the tag is undefined, this is not a wasm exception. Go to a
1757  // different block to process the JS exception. Otherwise compare it
1758  // with the expected tag.
1759  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &js_exception, kRefNull, caught_tag.gp(),
1760  undefined.gp(), state_merged_explicitly);
1761  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &uncaught, kRefNull, imm_tag,
1762  caught_tag.gp(), state_merged_explicitly);
1763  }
1764  // Case 1: A wasm exception with a matching tag.
1765  CODE_COMMENT("unpack exception");
1766  GetExceptionValues(decoder, __ cache_state()->stack_state.back(),
1767  catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.tag);
1768  // GetExceptionValues modified the cache state. Remember the new state
1769  // to merge the end state of case 2 into it.
1770  end_state.Steal(*__ cache_state());
1771  __ emit_jump(&done);
1772 
1773  __ bind(&js_exception);
1774  __ cache_state() -> Split(initial_state);
1775  {
1776  FREEZE_STATE(state_merged_explicitly);
1777  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &uncaught, kRefNull, imm_tag,
1778  js_tag.gp(), state_merged_explicitly);
1779  }
1780  // Case 2: A JS exception, and the expected tag is JSTag.
1781  // TODO(thibaudm): Can we avoid some state splitting/stealing by
1782  // reserving this register earlier and not modifying the state in this
1783  // block?
1784  CODE_COMMENT("JS exception caught by JSTag");
1785  LiftoffRegister exception = __ PeekToRegister(0, pinned);
1786  __ PushRegister(kRefNull, exception);
1787  // The exception is now on the stack twice: once as an implicit operand
1788  // for rethrow, and once as the "unpacked" value.
1789  __ MergeFullStackWith(end_state);
1790  __ emit_jump(&done);
1791 
1792  // Case 3: Either a wasm exception with a mismatching tag, or a JS
1793  // exception but the expected tag is not JSTag.
1794  __ bind(&uncaught);
1795  __ cache_state() -> Steal(initial_state);
1796  __ MergeFullStackWith(block->try_info->catch_state);
1797  __ emit_jump(&block->try_info->catch_label);
1798 
1799  __ bind(&done);
1800  __ cache_state() -> Steal(end_state);
1801  }
1802  } else {
1803  {
1804  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
1805  Label caught;
1806  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &caught, kRefNull, imm_tag, caught_tag.gp(),
1807  frozen);
1808  // The tags don't match, merge the current state into the catch state
1809  // and jump to the next handler.
1810  __ MergeFullStackWith(block->try_info->catch_state);
1811  __ emit_jump(&block->try_info->catch_label);
1812  __ bind(&caught);
1813  }
1814 
1815  CODE_COMMENT("unpack exception");
1816  pinned = {};
1817  GetExceptionValues(decoder, __ cache_state()->stack_state.back(),
1818  catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.tag);
1819  }
1820 
1821  if (catch_case.kind == kCatchRef) {
1822  // Append the exception on the operand stack.
1823  DCHECK(exn.is_stack());
1824  auto rc = reg_class_for(kRefNull);
1825  LiftoffRegister reg = __ GetUnusedRegister(rc, pinned);
1826  __ Fill(reg, exn.offset(), kRefNull);
1827  __ PushRegister(kRefNull, reg);
1828  }
1829  // There is an extra copy of the exception at this point, below the unpacked
1830  // values (if any). It will be dropped in the branch below.
1831  BrOrRet(decoder, catch_case.br_imm.depth);
1832  bool is_last = &catch_case == &block->catch_cases.last();
1833  if (is_last && !decoder->HasCatchAll(block)) {
1834  __ bind(&block->try_info->catch_label);
1835  __ cache_state()->Steal(block->try_info->catch_state);
1836  ThrowRef(decoder, nullptr);
1837  }
1838  }
1839 
1840  void ThrowRef(FullDecoder* decoder, Value*) {
1841  // Like Rethrow, but pops the exception from the stack.
1842  VarState exn = __ PopVarState();
1843  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmThrowRef, MakeSig::Params(kRef), {exn},
1844  decoder->position());
1845  int pc_offset = __ pc_offset();
1846  MaybeOSR();
1847  EmitLandingPad(decoder, pc_offset);
1848  }

1885 
1886  // Before emitting the conditional branch, {will_freeze} will be initialized
1887  // to prevent cache state changes in conditionally executed code.
1888  void JumpIfFalse(FullDecoder* decoder, Label* false_dst,
1889  std::optional<FreezeCacheState>& will_freeze) {
1890  DCHECK(!will_freeze.has_value());
1891  Condition cond =
1892  test_and_reset_outstanding_op(kExprI32Eqz) ? kNotZero : kZero;
1893 
1894  if (!has_outstanding_op()) {
1895  // Unary comparison.
1896  Register value = __ PopToRegister().gp();
1897  will_freeze.emplace(asm_);
1898  __ emit_cond_jump(cond, false_dst, kI32, value, no_reg, *will_freeze);
1899  return;
1900  }
1901 
1902  // Binary comparison of i32 values.
1903  cond = Negate(GetCompareCondition(outstanding_op_));
1904  outstanding_op_ = kNoOutstandingOp;
1905  VarState rhs_slot = __ cache_state()->stack_state.back();
1906  if (rhs_slot.is_const()) {
1907  // Compare to a constant.
1908  int32_t rhs_imm = rhs_slot.i32_const();
1909  __ cache_state()->stack_state.pop_back();
1910  Register lhs = __ PopToRegister().gp();
1911  will_freeze.emplace(asm_);
1912  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(cond, false_dst, lhs, rhs_imm, *will_freeze);
1913  return;
1914  }
1915 
1916  Register rhs = __ PopToRegister().gp();
1917  VarState lhs_slot = __ cache_state()->stack_state.back();
1918  if (lhs_slot.is_const()) {
1919  // Compare a constant to an arbitrary value.
1920  int32_t lhs_imm = lhs_slot.i32_const();
1921  __ cache_state()->stack_state.pop_back();
1922  // Flip the condition, because {lhs} and {rhs} are swapped.
1923  will_freeze.emplace(asm_);
1924  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(Flip(cond), false_dst, rhs, lhs_imm, *will_freeze);
1925  return;
1926  }
1927 
1928  // Compare two arbitrary values.
1929  Register lhs = __ PopToRegister(LiftoffRegList{rhs}).gp();
1930  will_freeze.emplace(asm_);
1931  __ emit_cond_jump(cond, false_dst, kI32, lhs, rhs, *will_freeze);
1932  }
1933 
1934  void If(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& cond, Control* if_block) {
1935  DCHECK_EQ(if_block, decoder->control_at(0));
1936  DCHECK(if_block->is_if());
1937 
1938  // Allocate the else state.
1939  if_block->else_state = zone_->New<ElseState>(zone_);
1940 
1941  // Test the condition on the value stack, jump to else if zero.
1942  std::optional<FreezeCacheState> frozen;
1943  JumpIfFalse(decoder, if_block->else_state->label.get(), frozen);
1944  frozen.reset();
1945 
1946  // Store the state (after popping the value) for executing the else branch.
1947  if_block->else_state->state.Split(*__ cache_state());
1948 
1949  PushControl(if_block);
1950  }
1951 
1952  void FallThruTo(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* c) {
1953  DCHECK_IMPLIES(c->is_try_catchall(), !c->end_merge.reached);
1954  if (c->end_merge.reached) {
1955  __ MergeStackWith(c->label_state, c->br_merge()->arity,
1956  LiftoffAssembler::kForwardJump);
1957  } else {
1958  c->label_state = __ MergeIntoNewState(__ num_locals(), c->end_merge.arity,
1959  c->stack_depth + c->num_exceptions);
1960  }
1961  __ emit_jump(c->label.get());
1962  TraceCacheState(decoder);
1963  }
1964 
1965  void FinishOneArmedIf(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* c) {
1966  DCHECK(c->is_onearmed_if());
1967  if (c->end_merge.reached) {
1968  // Someone already merged to the end of the if. Merge both arms into that.
1969  if (c->reachable()) {
1970  // Merge the if state into the end state.
1971  __ MergeFullStackWith(c->label_state);
1972  __ emit_jump(c->label.get());
1973  }
1974  // Merge the else state into the end state. Set this state as the current
1975  // state first so helper functions know which registers are in use.
1976  __ bind(c->else_state->label.get());
1977  __ cache_state()->Steal(c->else_state->state);
1978  __ MergeFullStackWith(c->label_state);
1979  __ cache_state()->Steal(c->label_state);
1980  } else if (c->reachable()) {
1981  // No merge yet at the end of the if, but we need to create a merge for
1982  // the both arms of this if. Thus init the merge point from the current
1983  // state, then merge the else state into that.
1984  DCHECK_EQ(c->start_merge.arity, c->end_merge.arity);
1985  c->label_state =
1986  __ MergeIntoNewState(__ num_locals(), c->start_merge.arity,
1987  c->stack_depth + c->num_exceptions);
1988  __ emit_jump(c->label.get());
1989  // Merge the else state into the end state. Set this state as the current
1990  // state first so helper functions know which registers are in use.
1991  __ bind(c->else_state->label.get());
1992  __ cache_state()->Steal(c->else_state->state);
1993  __ MergeFullStackWith(c->label_state);
1994  __ cache_state()->Steal(c->label_state);
1995  } else {
1996  // No merge needed, just continue with the else state.
1997  __ bind(c->else_state->label.get());
1998  __ cache_state()->Steal(c->else_state->state);
1999  }
2000  }
2001 
2002  void FinishTry(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* c) {
2003  DCHECK(c->is_try_catch() || c->is_try_catchall() || c->is_try_table());
2004  if (!c->end_merge.reached) {
2005  if (c->try_info->catch_reached && !c->is_try_table()) {
2006  // Drop the implicit exception ref.
2007  __ DropExceptionValueAtOffset(__ num_locals() + c->stack_depth +
2008  c->num_exceptions);
2009  }
2010  // Else we did not enter the catch state, continue with the current state.
2011  } else {
2012  if (c->reachable()) {
2013  __ MergeStackWith(c->label_state, c->br_merge()->arity,
2014  LiftoffAssembler::kForwardJump);
2015  }
2016  __ cache_state()->Steal(c->label_state);
2017  }
2018  if (c->try_info->catch_reached && !c->is_try_table()) {
2019  num_exceptions_--;
2020  }
2021  }
2022 
2023  void PopControl(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* c) {
2024  if (c->is_loop()) return; // A loop just falls through.
2025  if (c->is_onearmed_if()) {
2026  // Special handling for one-armed ifs.
2027  FinishOneArmedIf(decoder, c);
2028  } else if (c->is_try_catch() || c->is_try_catchall() || c->is_try_table()) {
2029  FinishTry(decoder, c);
2030  } else if (c->end_merge.reached) {
2031  // There is a merge already. Merge our state into that, then continue with
2032  // that state.
2033  if (c->reachable()) {
2034  __ MergeFullStackWith(c->label_state);
2035  }
2036  __ cache_state()->Steal(c->label_state);
2037  } else {
2038  // No merge, just continue with our current state.
2039  }
2040 
2041  if (!c->label.get()->is_bound()) __ bind(c->label.get());
2042  }
2043 
2044  // Call a C function (with default C calling conventions). Returns the
2045  // register holding the result if any.
2046  LiftoffRegister GenerateCCall(ValueKind return_kind,
2047  const std::initializer_list<VarState> args,
2048  ExternalReference ext_ref) {
2049  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT(
2050  std::string{"Call extref: "} +
2051  ExternalReferenceTable::NameOfIsolateIndependentAddress(
2052  ext_ref.address(), IsolateGroup::current()->external_ref_table()));
2053  __ SpillAllRegisters();
2054  __ CallC(args, ext_ref);
2055  if (needs_gp_reg_pair(return_kind)) {
2056  return LiftoffRegister::ForPair(kReturnRegister0, kReturnRegister1);
2057  }
2058  return LiftoffRegister{kReturnRegister0};
2059  }
2060 
2061  void GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(const LiftoffRegister* result_regs,
2062  ValueKind return_kind,
2063  ValueKind out_argument_kind,
2064  const std::initializer_list<VarState> args,
2065  ExternalReference ext_ref) {
2066  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT(
2067  std::string{"Call extref: "} +
2068  ExternalReferenceTable::NameOfIsolateIndependentAddress(
2069  ext_ref.address(), IsolateGroup::current()->external_ref_table()));
2070 
2071  // Before making a call, spill all cache registers.
2072  __ SpillAllRegisters();
2073 
2074  // Store arguments on our stack, then align the stack for calling to C.
2075  int param_bytes = 0;
2076  for (const VarState& arg : args) {
2077  param_bytes += value_kind_size(arg.kind());
2078  }
2079  int out_arg_bytes =
2080  out_argument_kind == kVoid ? 0 : value_kind_size(out_argument_kind);
2081  int stack_bytes = std::max(param_bytes, out_arg_bytes);
2082  __ CallCWithStackBuffer(args, result_regs, return_kind, out_argument_kind,
2083  stack_bytes, ext_ref);
2084  }

2086  template <typename EmitFn, typename... Args>
2087  void CallEmitFn(EmitFn fn, Args... args)
2088  requires(!std::is_member_function_pointer_v<EmitFn>)
2089  {
2090  fn(args...);
2091  }
2092 
2093  template <typename EmitFn, typename... Args>
2094  void CallEmitFn(EmitFn fn, Args... args)
2095  requires std::is_member_function_pointer_v<EmitFn>
2096  {
2097  (asm_.*fn)(ConvertAssemblerArg(args)...);
2098  }

2100  // Wrap a {LiftoffRegister} with implicit conversions to {Register} and
2101  // {DoubleRegister}.
2102  struct AssemblerRegisterConverter {
2103  LiftoffRegister reg;
2104  operator LiftoffRegister() { return reg; }
2105  operator Register() { return reg.gp(); }
2106  operator DoubleRegister() { return reg.fp(); }
2107  };
2108 
2109  // Convert {LiftoffRegister} to {AssemblerRegisterConverter}, other types stay
2110  // unchanged.
2111  template <typename T>
2112  std::conditional_t<std::is_same_v<LiftoffRegister, T>,
2113  AssemblerRegisterConverter, T>
2114  ConvertAssemblerArg(T t) {
2115  return {t};
2116  }
