2118  template <typename EmitFn, typename ArgType>
2119  struct EmitFnWithFirstArg {
2120  EmitFn fn;
2121  ArgType first_arg;
2122  };
2123 
2124  template <typename EmitFn, typename ArgType>
2125  EmitFnWithFirstArg<EmitFn, ArgType> BindFirst(EmitFn fn, ArgType arg) {
2126  return {fn, arg};
2127  }
2128 
2129  template <typename EmitFn, typename T, typename... Args>
2130  void CallEmitFn(EmitFnWithFirstArg<EmitFn, T> bound_fn, Args... args) {
2131  CallEmitFn(bound_fn.fn, bound_fn.first_arg, ConvertAssemblerArg(args)...);
2132  }
2133 
2134  template <ValueKind src_kind, ValueKind result_kind,
2135  ValueKind result_lane_kind = kVoid, class EmitFn>
2136  void EmitUnOp(EmitFn fn) {
2137  constexpr RegClass src_rc = reg_class_for(src_kind);
2138  constexpr RegClass result_rc = reg_class_for(result_kind);
2139  LiftoffRegister src = __ PopToRegister();
2140  LiftoffRegister dst = src_rc == result_rc
2141  ? __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {src}, {})
2142  : __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {});
2143  CallEmitFn(fn, dst, src);
2144  if (V8_UNLIKELY(detect_nondeterminism_)) {
2145  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst};
2146  if (result_kind == ValueKind::kF32 || result_kind == ValueKind::kF64) {
2147  CheckNan(dst, pinned, result_kind);
2148  } else if (result_kind == ValueKind::kS128 &&
2149  (result_lane_kind == kF32 || result_lane_kind == kF64)) {
2150  // TODO(irezvov): Add NaN detection for F16.
2151  CheckS128Nan(dst, pinned, result_lane_kind);
2152  }
2153  }
2154  __ PushRegister(result_kind, dst);
2155  }
2156 
2157  template <ValueKind kind>
2158  void EmitFloatUnOpWithCFallback(
2159  bool (LiftoffAssembler::*emit_fn)(DoubleRegister, DoubleRegister),
2160  ExternalReference (*fallback_fn)()) {
2161  auto emit_with_c_fallback = [this, emit_fn, fallback_fn](
2162  LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2163  if ((asm_.*emit_fn)(dst.fp(), src.fp())) return;
2164  ExternalReference ext_ref = fallback_fn();
2165  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(&dst, kVoid, kind, {VarState{kind, src, 0}},
2166  ext_ref);
2167  };
2168  EmitUnOp<kind, kind>(emit_with_c_fallback);
2169  }
2170 
2171  enum TypeConversionTrapping : bool { kCanTrap = true, kNoTrap = false };
2172  template <ValueKind dst_kind, ValueKind src_kind,
2173  TypeConversionTrapping can_trap>
2174  void EmitTypeConversion(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode,
2175  ExternalReference (*fallback_fn)()) {
2176  static constexpr RegClass src_rc = reg_class_for(src_kind);
2177  static constexpr RegClass dst_rc = reg_class_for(dst_kind);
2178  LiftoffRegister src = __ PopToRegister();
2179  LiftoffRegister dst = src_rc == dst_rc
2180  ? __ GetUnusedRegister(dst_rc, {src}, {})
2181  : __ GetUnusedRegister(dst_rc, {});
2182  bool emitted = __ emit_type_conversion(
2183  opcode, dst, src,
2184  can_trap ? AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder,
2185  Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapFloatUnrepresentable)
2186  .label()
2187  : nullptr);
2188  if (!emitted) {
2189  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(fallback_fn);
2190  ExternalReference ext_ref = fallback_fn();
2191  if (can_trap) {
2192  // External references for potentially trapping conversions return int.
2193  LiftoffRegister ret_reg =
2194  __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst});
2195  LiftoffRegister dst_regs[] = {ret_reg, dst};
2196  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(dst_regs, kI32, dst_kind,
2197  {VarState{src_kind, src, 0}}, ext_ref);
2198  OolTrapLabel trap = AddOutOfLineTrap(
2199  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapFloatUnrepresentable);
2200  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, trap.label(), kI32, ret_reg.gp(), no_reg,
2201  trap.frozen());
2202  } else {
2203  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(&dst, kVoid, dst_kind,
2204  {VarState{src_kind, src, 0}}, ext_ref);
2205  }
2206  }
2207  __ PushRegister(dst_kind, dst);
2208  }
2209 
2210  void EmitIsNull(WasmOpcode opcode, ValueType type) {
2211  LiftoffRegList pinned;
2212  LiftoffRegister ref = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister());
2213  LiftoffRegister null = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
2214  LoadNullValueForCompare(null.gp(), pinned, type);
2215  // Prefer to overwrite one of the input registers with the result
2216  // of the comparison.
2217  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {ref, null}, {});
2218 #if defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS)
2219  // As the value in the {null} register is only the tagged pointer part,
2220  // we may only compare 32 bits, not the full pointer size.
2221  __ emit_i32_set_cond(opcode == kExprRefIsNull ? kEqual : kNotEqual,
2222  dst.gp(), ref.gp(), null.gp());
2223 #else
2224  __ emit_ptrsize_set_cond(opcode == kExprRefIsNull ? kEqual : kNotEqual,
2225  dst.gp(), ref, null);
2226 #endif
2227  __ PushRegister(kI32, dst);
2228  }
2229 
2230  void UnOp(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode, const Value& value,
2231  Value* result) {
2232 #define CASE_I32_UNOP(opcode, fn) \
2233  case kExpr##opcode: \
2234  return EmitUnOp<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_##fn);
2235 #define CASE_I64_UNOP(opcode, fn) \
2236  case kExpr##opcode: \
2237  return EmitUnOp<kI64, kI64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_##fn);
2238 #define CASE_FLOAT_UNOP(opcode, kind, fn) \
2239  case kExpr##opcode: \
2240  return EmitUnOp<k##kind, k##kind>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_##fn);
2241 #define CASE_FLOAT_UNOP_WITH_CFALLBACK(opcode, kind, fn) \
2242  case kExpr##opcode: \
2243  return EmitFloatUnOpWithCFallback<k##kind>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_##fn, \
2244  &ExternalReference::wasm_##fn);
2245 #define CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(opcode, dst_kind, src_kind, ext_ref, can_trap) \
2246  case kExpr##opcode: \
2247  return EmitTypeConversion<k##dst_kind, k##src_kind, can_trap>( \
2248  decoder, kExpr##opcode, ext_ref);
2249  switch (opcode) {
2250  CASE_I32_UNOP(I32Clz, i32_clz)
2251  CASE_I32_UNOP(I32Ctz, i32_ctz)
2252  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP(F32Abs, F32, f32_abs)
2253  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP(F32Neg, F32, f32_neg)
2254  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP_WITH_CFALLBACK(F32Ceil, F32, f32_ceil)
2255  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP_WITH_CFALLBACK(F32Floor, F32, f32_floor)
2256  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP_WITH_CFALLBACK(F32Trunc, F32, f32_trunc)
2257  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP_WITH_CFALLBACK(F32NearestInt, F32, f32_nearest_int)
2258  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP(F32Sqrt, F32, f32_sqrt)
2259  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP(F64Abs, F64, f64_abs)
2260  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP(F64Neg, F64, f64_neg)
2261  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP_WITH_CFALLBACK(F64Ceil, F64, f64_ceil)
2262  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP_WITH_CFALLBACK(F64Floor, F64, f64_floor)
2263  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP_WITH_CFALLBACK(F64Trunc, F64, f64_trunc)
2264  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP_WITH_CFALLBACK(F64NearestInt, F64, f64_nearest_int)
2265  CASE_FLOAT_UNOP(F64Sqrt, F64, f64_sqrt)
2266  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I32ConvertI64, I32, I64, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2267  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I32SConvertF32, I32, F32, nullptr, kCanTrap)
2268  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I32UConvertF32, I32, F32, nullptr, kCanTrap)
2269  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I32SConvertF64, I32, F64, nullptr, kCanTrap)
2270  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I32UConvertF64, I32, F64, nullptr, kCanTrap)
2271  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I32ReinterpretF32, I32, F32, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2272  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I64SConvertI32, I64, I32, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2273  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I64UConvertI32, I64, I32, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2274  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I64SConvertF32, I64, F32,
2275  &ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_int64, kCanTrap)
2276  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I64UConvertF32, I64, F32,
2277  &ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_uint64, kCanTrap)
2278  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I64SConvertF64, I64, F64,
2279  &ExternalReference::wasm_float64_to_int64, kCanTrap)
2280  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I64UConvertF64, I64, F64,
2281  &ExternalReference::wasm_float64_to_uint64, kCanTrap)
2282  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I64ReinterpretF64, I64, F64, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2283  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F32SConvertI32, F32, I32, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2284  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F32UConvertI32, F32, I32, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2285  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F32SConvertI64, F32, I64,
2286  &ExternalReference::wasm_int64_to_float32, kNoTrap)
2287  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F32UConvertI64, F32, I64,
2288  &ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_to_float32, kNoTrap)
2289  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F32ConvertF64, F32, F64, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2290  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F32ReinterpretI32, F32, I32, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2291  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F64SConvertI32, F64, I32, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2292  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F64UConvertI32, F64, I32, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2293  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F64SConvertI64, F64, I64,
2294  &ExternalReference::wasm_int64_to_float64, kNoTrap)
2295  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F64UConvertI64, F64, I64,
2296  &ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_to_float64, kNoTrap)
2297  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F64ConvertF32, F64, F32, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2298  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(F64ReinterpretI64, F64, I64, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2299  CASE_I32_UNOP(I32SExtendI8, i32_signextend_i8)
2300  CASE_I32_UNOP(I32SExtendI16, i32_signextend_i16)
2301  CASE_I64_UNOP(I64SExtendI8, i64_signextend_i8)
2302  CASE_I64_UNOP(I64SExtendI16, i64_signextend_i16)
2303  CASE_I64_UNOP(I64SExtendI32, i64_signextend_i32)
2304  CASE_I64_UNOP(I64Clz, i64_clz)
2305  CASE_I64_UNOP(I64Ctz, i64_ctz)
2306  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I32SConvertSatF32, I32, F32, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2307  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I32UConvertSatF32, I32, F32, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2308  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I32SConvertSatF64, I32, F64, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2309  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I32UConvertSatF64, I32, F64, nullptr, kNoTrap)
2310  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I64SConvertSatF32, I64, F32,
2311  &ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_int64_sat,
2312  kNoTrap)
2313  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I64UConvertSatF32, I64, F32,
2314  &ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_uint64_sat,
2315  kNoTrap)
2316  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I64SConvertSatF64, I64, F64,
2317  &ExternalReference::wasm_float64_to_int64_sat,
2318  kNoTrap)
2319  CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION(I64UConvertSatF64, I64, F64,
2320  &ExternalReference::wasm_float64_to_uint64_sat,
2321  kNoTrap)
2322  case kExprI32Eqz:
2323  DCHECK(decoder->lookahead(0, kExprI32Eqz));
2324  if ((decoder->lookahead(1, kExprBrIf) ||
2325  decoder->lookahead(1, kExprIf)) &&
2326  !for_debugging_) {
2327  DCHECK(!has_outstanding_op());
2328  outstanding_op_ = kExprI32Eqz;
2329  break;
2330  }
2331  return EmitUnOp<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_eqz);
2332  case kExprI64Eqz:
2333  return EmitUnOp<kI64, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_eqz);
2334  case kExprI32Popcnt:
2335  return EmitUnOp<kI32, kI32>(
2336  [this](LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2337  if (__ emit_i32_popcnt(dst.gp(), src.gp())) return;
2338  LiftoffRegister result =
2339  GenerateCCall(kI32, {VarState{kI32, src, 0}},
2340  ExternalReference::wasm_word32_popcnt());
2341  if (result != dst) __ Move(dst.gp(), result.gp(), kI32);
2342  });
2343  case kExprI64Popcnt:
2344  return EmitUnOp<kI64, kI64>(
2345  [this](LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2346  if (__ emit_i64_popcnt(dst, src)) return;
2347  // The c function returns i32. We will zero-extend later.
2348  LiftoffRegister result =
2349  GenerateCCall(kI32, {VarState{kI64, src, 0}},
2350  ExternalReference::wasm_word64_popcnt());
2351  // Now zero-extend the result to i64.
2352  __ emit_type_conversion(kExprI64UConvertI32, dst, result,
2353  nullptr);
2354  });
2355  case kExprRefIsNull:
2356  // We abuse ref.as_non_null, which isn't otherwise used in this switch, as
2357  // a sentinel for the negation of ref.is_null.
2358  case kExprRefAsNonNull:
2359  return EmitIsNull(opcode, value.type);
2360  case kExprAnyConvertExtern: {
2361  VarState input_state = __ cache_state()->stack_state.back();
2362  const bool is_shared = value.type.is_shared();
2363  CallBuiltin(is_shared ? Builtin::kWasmAnyConvertExternShared
2364  : Builtin::kWasmAnyConvertExtern,
2365  MakeSig::Returns(kRefNull).Params(kRefNull), {input_state},
2366  decoder->position());
2367  __ DropValues(1);
2368  __ PushRegister(kRef, LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0));
2369  return;
2370  }
2371  case kExprExternConvertAny: {
2372  LiftoffRegList pinned;
2373  LiftoffRegister ref = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
2374  LiftoffRegister null = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
2375  LoadNullValueForCompare(null.gp(), pinned, kWasmAnyRef);
2376  Label label;
2377  {
2378  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
2379  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &label, kRefNull, ref.gp(), null.gp(),
2380  frozen);
2381  LoadNullValue(ref.gp(), kWasmExternRef);
2382  __ bind(&label);
2383  }
2384  __ PushRegister(kRefNull, ref);
2385  return;
2386  }
2387  default:
2388  UNREACHABLE();
2389  }
2390 #undef CASE_I32_UNOP
2391 #undef CASE_I64_UNOP
2392 #undef CASE_FLOAT_UNOP
2393 #undef CASE_FLOAT_UNOP_WITH_CFALLBACK
2394 #undef CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION
2395  }
2396 
2397  template <ValueKind src_kind, ValueKind result_kind, typename EmitFn,
2398  typename EmitFnImm>
2399  void EmitBinOpImm(EmitFn fn, EmitFnImm fnImm) {
2400  static constexpr RegClass src_rc = reg_class_for(src_kind);
2401  static constexpr RegClass result_rc = reg_class_for(result_kind);
2402 
2403  VarState rhs_slot = __ cache_state()->stack_state.back();
2404  // Check if the RHS is an immediate.
2405  if (rhs_slot.is_const()) {
2406  __ cache_state()->stack_state.pop_back();
2407  int32_t imm = rhs_slot.i32_const();
2408 
2409  LiftoffRegister lhs = __ PopToRegister();
2410  // Either reuse {lhs} for {dst}, or choose a register (pair) which does
2411  // not overlap, for easier code generation.
2412  LiftoffRegList pinned{lhs};
2413  LiftoffRegister dst = src_rc == result_rc
2414  ? __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {lhs}, pinned)
2415  : __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, pinned);
2416 
2417  CallEmitFn(fnImm, dst, lhs, imm);
2418  static_assert(result_kind != kF32 && result_kind != kF64,
2419  "Unhandled nondeterminism for fuzzing.");
2420  __ PushRegister(result_kind, dst);
2421  } else {
2422  // The RHS was not an immediate.
2423  EmitBinOp<src_kind, result_kind>(fn);
2424  }
2425  }
2426 
2427  template <ValueKind src_kind, ValueKind result_kind,
2428  bool swap_lhs_rhs = false, ValueKind result_lane_kind = kVoid,
2429  typename EmitFn>
2430  void EmitBinOp(EmitFn fn) {
2431  static constexpr RegClass src_rc = reg_class_for(src_kind);
2432  static constexpr RegClass result_rc = reg_class_for(result_kind);
2433  LiftoffRegister rhs = __ PopToRegister();
2434  LiftoffRegister lhs = __ PopToRegister(LiftoffRegList{rhs});
2435  LiftoffRegister dst = src_rc == result_rc
2436  ? __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {lhs, rhs}, {})
2437  : __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {});
2438 
2439  if (swap_lhs_rhs) std::swap(lhs, rhs);
2440 
2441  CallEmitFn(fn, dst, lhs, rhs);
2442  if (V8_UNLIKELY(detect_nondeterminism_)) {
2443  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst};
2444  if (result_kind == ValueKind::kF32 || result_kind == ValueKind::kF64) {
2445  CheckNan(dst, pinned, result_kind);
2446  } else if (result_kind == ValueKind::kS128 &&
2447  (result_lane_kind == kF32 || result_lane_kind == kF64)) {
2448  CheckS128Nan(dst, pinned, result_lane_kind);
2449  }
2450  }
2451  __ PushRegister(result_kind, dst);
2452  }
2453 
2454  // We do not use EmitBinOp for Swizzle because in the no-avx case, we have the
2455  // additional constraint that dst does not alias the mask.
2456  void EmitI8x16Swizzle(bool relaxed) {
2457  static constexpr RegClass result_rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
2458  LiftoffRegister mask = __ PopToRegister();
2459  LiftoffRegister src = __ PopToRegister(LiftoffRegList{mask});
2460 #if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64)
2461  LiftoffRegister dst =
2462  CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)
2463  ? __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {src, mask}, {})
2464  : __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {src}, LiftoffRegList{mask});
2465 #else
2466  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {src, mask}, {});
2467 #endif
2468  if (relaxed) {
2469  __ emit_i8x16_relaxed_swizzle(dst, src, mask);
2470  } else {
2471  __ emit_i8x16_swizzle(dst, src, mask);
2472  }
2473  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
2474  }
2475 
2476  void EmitDivOrRem64CCall(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2477  LiftoffRegister rhs, ExternalReference ext_ref,
2478  Label* trap_by_zero,
2479  Label* trap_unrepresentable = nullptr) {
2480  // Cannot emit native instructions, build C call.
2481  LiftoffRegister ret = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst});
2482  LiftoffRegister result_regs[] = {ret, dst};
2483  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(result_regs, kI32, kI64,
2484  {{kI64, lhs, 0}, {kI64, rhs, 0}}, ext_ref);
2485  FREEZE_STATE(trapping);
2486  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kEqual, trap_by_zero, ret.gp(), 0, trapping);
2487  if (trap_unrepresentable) {
2488  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kEqual, trap_unrepresentable, ret.gp(), -1,
2489  trapping);
2490  }
2491  }

2493  template <WasmOpcode opcode>
2494  void EmitI32CmpOp(FullDecoder* decoder) {
2495  DCHECK(decoder->lookahead(0, opcode));
2496  if ((decoder->lookahead(1, kExprBrIf) || decoder->lookahead(1, kExprIf)) &&
2497  !for_debugging_) {
2498  DCHECK(!has_outstanding_op());
2499  outstanding_op_ = opcode;
2500  return;
2501  }
2502  return EmitBinOp<kI32, kI32>(BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_set_cond,
2503  GetCompareCondition(opcode)));
2504  }
2505 
2506  template <ValueKind kind, ExternalReference(ExtRefFn)()>
2507  void EmitBitRotationCCall() {
2508  EmitBinOp<kind, kind>([this](LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister input,
2509  LiftoffRegister shift) {
2510  // The shift is always passed as 32-bit value.
2511  if (needs_gp_reg_pair(kind)) shift = shift.low();
2512  LiftoffRegister result =
2513  GenerateCCall(kind, {{kind, input, 0}, {kI32, shift, 0}}, ExtRefFn());
2514  if (dst != result) __ Move(dst, result, kind);
2515  });
2516  }
2517 
2518  template <typename EmitFn, typename EmitFnImm>
2519  void EmitI64Shift(EmitFn fn, EmitFnImm fnImm) {
2520  return EmitBinOpImm<kI64, kI64>(
2521  [this, fn](LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src,
2522  LiftoffRegister amount) {
2523  CallEmitFn(fn, dst, src,
2524  amount.is_gp_pair() ? amount.low_gp() : amount.gp());
2525  },
2526  fnImm);
2527  }

2529  void BinOp(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode, const Value& lhs,
2530  const Value& rhs, Value* result) {
2531  switch (opcode) {
2532  case kExprI32Add:
2533  return EmitBinOpImm<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_add,
2534  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_addi);
2535  case kExprI32Sub:
2536  return EmitBinOp<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_sub);
2537  case kExprI32Mul:
2538  return EmitBinOp<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_mul);
2539  case kExprI32And:
2540  return EmitBinOpImm<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_and,
2541  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_andi);
2542  case kExprI32Ior:
2543  return EmitBinOpImm<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_or,
2544  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_ori);
2545  case kExprI32Xor:
2546  return EmitBinOpImm<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_xor,
2547  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_xori);
2548  case kExprI32Eq:
2549  return EmitI32CmpOp<kExprI32Eq>(decoder);
2550  case kExprI32Ne:
2551  return EmitI32CmpOp<kExprI32Ne>(decoder);
2552  case kExprI32LtS:
2553  return EmitI32CmpOp<kExprI32LtS>(decoder);
2554  case kExprI32LtU:
2555  return EmitI32CmpOp<kExprI32LtU>(decoder);
2556  case kExprI32GtS:
2557  return EmitI32CmpOp<kExprI32GtS>(decoder);
2558  case kExprI32GtU:
2559  return EmitI32CmpOp<kExprI32GtU>(decoder);
2560  case kExprI32LeS:
2561  return EmitI32CmpOp<kExprI32LeS>(decoder);
2562  case kExprI32LeU:
2563  return EmitI32CmpOp<kExprI32LeU>(decoder);
2564  case kExprI32GeS:
2565  return EmitI32CmpOp<kExprI32GeS>(decoder);
2566  case kExprI32GeU:
2567  return EmitI32CmpOp<kExprI32GeU>(decoder);
2568  case kExprI64Add:
2569  return EmitBinOpImm<kI64, kI64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_add,
2570  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_addi);
2571  case kExprI64Sub:
2572  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_sub);
2573  case kExprI64Mul:
2574  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_mul);
2575  case kExprI64And:
2576  return EmitBinOpImm<kI64, kI64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_and,
2577  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_andi);
2578  case kExprI64Ior:
2579  return EmitBinOpImm<kI64, kI64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_or,
2580  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_ori);
2581  case kExprI64Xor:
2582  return EmitBinOpImm<kI64, kI64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_xor,
2583  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_xori);
2584  case kExprI64Eq:
2585  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2586  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kEqual));
2587  case kExprI64Ne:
2588  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2589  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kNotEqual));
2590  case kExprI64LtS:
2591  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2592  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kLessThan));
2593  case kExprI64LtU:
2594  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2595  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThan));
2596  case kExprI64GtS:
2597  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2598  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kGreaterThan));
2599  case kExprI64GtU:
2600  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2601  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThan));
2602  case kExprI64LeS:
2603  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2604  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kLessThanEqual));
2605  case kExprI64LeU:
2606  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2607  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThanEqual));
2608  case kExprI64GeS:
2609  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2610  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kGreaterThanEqual));
2611  case kExprI64GeU:
2612  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2613  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual));
2614  case kExprF32Eq:
2615  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(
2616  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kEqual));
2617  case kExprF32Ne:
2618  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(
2619  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kNotEqual));
2620  case kExprF32Lt:
2621  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(
2622  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThan));
2623  case kExprF32Gt:
2624  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(BindFirst(
2625  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThan));
2626  case kExprF32Le:
2627  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(BindFirst(
2628  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThanEqual));
2629  case kExprF32Ge:
2630  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(BindFirst(
2631  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual));
2632  case kExprF64Eq:
2633  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(
2634  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kEqual));
2635  case kExprF64Ne:
2636  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(
2637  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kNotEqual));
2638  case kExprF64Lt:
2639  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(
2640  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThan));
2641  case kExprF64Gt:
2642  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2643  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThan));
2644  case kExprF64Le:
2645  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2646  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThanEqual));
2647  case kExprF64Ge:
2648  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2649  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual));
2650  case kExprI32Shl:
2651  return EmitBinOpImm<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_shl,
2652  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_shli);
2653  case kExprI32ShrS:
2654  return EmitBinOpImm<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_sar,
2655  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_sari);
2656  case kExprI32ShrU:
2657  return EmitBinOpImm<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_shr,
2658  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_shri);
2659  case kExprI32Rol:
2660  return EmitBitRotationCCall<kI32, ExternalReference::wasm_word32_rol>();
2661  case kExprI32Ror:
2662  return EmitBitRotationCCall<kI32, ExternalReference::wasm_word32_ror>();
2663  case kExprI64Shl:
2664  return EmitI64Shift(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_shl,
2665  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_shli);
2666  case kExprI64ShrS:
2667  return EmitI64Shift(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_sar,
2668  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_sari);
2669  case kExprI64ShrU:
2670  return EmitI64Shift(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_shr,
2671  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_shri);
2672  case kExprI64Rol:
2673  return EmitBitRotationCCall<kI64, ExternalReference::wasm_word64_rol>();
2674  case kExprI64Ror:
2675  return EmitBitRotationCCall<kI64, ExternalReference::wasm_word64_ror>();
2676  case kExprF32Add:
2677  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_add);
2678  case kExprF32Sub:
2679  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_sub);
2680  case kExprF32Mul:
2681  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_mul);
2682  case kExprF32Div:
2683  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_div);
2684  case kExprF32Min:
2685  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_min);
2686  case kExprF32Max:
2687  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_max);
2688  case kExprF32CopySign:
2689  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_copysign);
2690  case kExprF64Add:
2691  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_add);
2692  case kExprF64Sub:
2693  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_sub);
2694  case kExprF64Mul:
2695  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_mul);
2696  case kExprF64Div:
2697  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_div);
2698  case kExprF64Min:
2699  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_min);
2700  case kExprF64Max:
2701  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_max);
2702  case kExprF64CopySign:
2703  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_copysign);
2704  case kExprI32DivS:
2705  return EmitBinOp<kI32, kI32>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2706  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2707  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2708  AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivByZero);
2709  // Adding the second trap might invalidate the pointer returned for
2710  // the first one, thus get both pointers afterwards.
2711  AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(decoder,
2712  Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivUnrepresentable);
2713  Label* div_by_zero = out_of_line_code_.end()[-2].label.get();
2714  Label* div_unrepresentable = out_of_line_code_.end()[-1].label.get();
2715  __ emit_i32_divs(dst.gp(), lhs.gp(), rhs.gp(), div_by_zero,
2716  div_unrepresentable);
2717  });
2718  case kExprI32DivU:
2719  return EmitBinOp<kI32, kI32>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2720  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2721  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2722  Label* div_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2723  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivByZero);
2724  __ emit_i32_divu(dst.gp(), lhs.gp(), rhs.gp(), div_by_zero);
2725  });
2726  case kExprI32RemS:
2727  return EmitBinOp<kI32, kI32>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2728  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2729  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2730  Label* rem_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2731  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapRemByZero);
2732  __ emit_i32_rems(dst.gp(), lhs.gp(), rhs.gp(), rem_by_zero);
2733  });
2734  case kExprI32RemU:
2735  return EmitBinOp<kI32, kI32>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2736  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2737  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2738  Label* rem_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2739  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapRemByZero);
2740  __ emit_i32_remu(dst.gp(), lhs.gp(), rhs.gp(), rem_by_zero);
2741  });
2742  case kExprI64DivS:
2743  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI64>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2744  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2745  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2746  AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivByZero);
2747  // Adding the second trap might invalidate the pointer returned for
2748  // the first one, thus get both pointers afterwards.
2749  AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(decoder,
2750  Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivUnrepresentable);
2751  Label* div_by_zero = out_of_line_code_.end()[-2].label.get();
2752  Label* div_unrepresentable = out_of_line_code_.end()[-1].label.get();
2753  if (!__ emit_i64_divs(dst, lhs, rhs, div_by_zero,
2754  div_unrepresentable)) {
2755  ExternalReference ext_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_int64_div();
2756  EmitDivOrRem64CCall(dst, lhs, rhs, ext_ref, div_by_zero,
2757  div_unrepresentable);
2758  }
2759  });
2760  case kExprI64DivU:
2761  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI64>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2762  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2763  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2764  Label* div_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2765  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivByZero);
2766  if (!__ emit_i64_divu(dst, lhs, rhs, div_by_zero)) {
2767  ExternalReference ext_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_div();
2768  EmitDivOrRem64CCall(dst, lhs, rhs, ext_ref, div_by_zero);
2769  }
2770  });
2771  case kExprI64RemS:
2772  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI64>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2773  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2774  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2775  Label* rem_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2776  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapRemByZero);
2777  if (!__ emit_i64_rems(dst, lhs, rhs, rem_by_zero)) {
2778  ExternalReference ext_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_int64_mod();
2779  EmitDivOrRem64CCall(dst, lhs, rhs, ext_ref, rem_by_zero);
2780  }
2781  });
2782  case kExprI64RemU:
2783  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI64>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2784  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2785  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2786  Label* rem_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2787  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapRemByZero);
2788  if (!__ emit_i64_remu(dst, lhs, rhs, rem_by_zero)) {
2789  ExternalReference ext_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_mod();
2790  EmitDivOrRem64CCall(dst, lhs, rhs, ext_ref, rem_by_zero);
2791  }
2792  });
2793  case kExprRefEq: {
2794 #if defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS)
2795  // In pointer compression, we smi-corrupt (the upper bits of a
2796  // Smi are arbitrary). So, we should only compare the lower 32 bits.
2797  return EmitBinOp<kRefNull, kI32>(
2798  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_set_cond, kEqual));
2799 #else
2800  return EmitBinOp<kRefNull, kI32>(
2801  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_ptrsize_set_cond, kEqual));
2802 #endif
2803  }
2804 
2805  default:
2806  UNREACHABLE();
2807  }
2808  }

2811 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64
2812  __ emit_trace_instruction(markid);
2813 #endif
2814  }

2820  void I64Const(FullDecoder* decoder, Value* result, int64_t value) {
2821  // The {VarState} stores constant values as int32_t, thus we only store
2822  // 64-bit constants in this field if it fits in an int32_t. Larger values
2823  // cannot be used as immediate value anyway, so we can also just put them in
2824  // a register immediately.
2825  int32_t value_i32 = static_cast<int32_t>(value);
2826  if (value_i32 == value) {
2827  __ PushConstant(kI64, value_i32);
2828  } else {
2829  LiftoffRegister reg = __ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(kI64), {});
2830  __ LoadConstant(reg, WasmValue(value));
2831  __ PushRegister(kI64, reg);
2832  }
2833  }

2853  void RefFunc(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t function_index, Value* result) {
2854  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmRefFunc,
2855  MakeSig::Returns(kRef).Params(kI32, kI32),
2856  {VarState{kI32, static_cast<int>(function_index), 0},
2857  VarState{kI32, 0, 0}},
2858  decoder->position());
2859  __ PushRegister(kRef, LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0));
2860  }
2861 
2862  void RefAsNonNull(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& arg, Value* result) {
2863  // The decoder only calls this function if the type is nullable.
2864  DCHECK(arg.type.is_nullable());
2865  LiftoffRegList pinned;
2866  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
2867  if (null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit ||
2868  IsSubtypeOf(kWasmRefI31, arg.type.AsNonShared(), decoder->module_) ||
2869  !arg.type.use_wasm_null()) {
2870  // Use an explicit null check if
2871  // (1) we cannot use trap handler or
2872  // (2) the object might be a Smi or
2873  // (3) the object might be a JS object.
2874  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, obj.gp(), pinned, arg.type);
2875  } else if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_skip_null_checks) {
2876  // Otherwise, load the word after the map word.
2877  static_assert(WasmStruct::kHeaderSize > kTaggedSize);
2878  static_assert(WasmArray::kHeaderSize > kTaggedSize);
2879  static_assert(WasmInternalFunction::kHeaderSize > kTaggedSize);
2880  LiftoffRegister dst = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
2881  uint32_t protected_load_pc = 0;
2882  __ Load(dst, obj.gp(), no_reg, wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(kTaggedSize),
2883  LoadType::kI32Load, &protected_load_pc);
2884  RegisterProtectedInstruction(decoder, protected_load_pc);
2885  }
2886  __ PushRegister(kRef, obj);
2887  }

2889  void Drop(FullDecoder* decoder) { __ DropValues(1); }

2891  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void TraceFunctionExit(FullDecoder* decoder) {
2892  CODE_COMMENT("trace function exit");
2893  // Before making the runtime call, spill all cache registers.
2894  __ SpillAllRegisters();
2895 
2896  // Store the return value if there is exactly one. Multiple return values
2897  // are not handled yet.
2898  size_t num_returns = decoder->sig_->return_count();
2899  // Put the parameter in its place.
2900  WasmTraceExitDescriptor descriptor;
2901  DCHECK_EQ(0, descriptor.GetStackParameterCount());
2902  DCHECK_EQ(1, descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount());
2903  Register param_reg = descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(0);
2904  if (num_returns == 1) {
2905  auto& return_slot = __ cache_state()->stack_state.back();
2906  if (return_slot.is_const()) {
2907  __ Spill(&return_slot);
2908  }
2909  DCHECK(return_slot.is_stack());
2910  __ LoadSpillAddress(param_reg, return_slot.offset(), return_slot.kind());
2911  } else {
2912  // Make sure to pass a "valid" parameter (Smi::zero()).
2913  LoadSmi(LiftoffRegister{param_reg}, 0);
2914  }
2915 
2916  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
2917  __ pc_offset(), SourcePosition(decoder->position()), false);
2918  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmTraceExit);
2919  DefineSafepoint();
2920  }
2921 
2922  void TierupCheckOnTailCall(FullDecoder* decoder) {
2923  if (!dynamic_tiering()) return;
2924  TierupCheck(decoder, decoder->position(),
2925  __ pc_offset() + kTierUpCostForFunctionEntry);
2926  }
2927 
2928  void DoReturn(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t /* drop values */) {
2929  ReturnImpl(decoder);
2930  }
2931 
2932  void ReturnImpl(FullDecoder* decoder) {
2933  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm)) TraceFunctionExit(decoder);
2934  // A function returning an uninhabitable type can't ever actually reach
2935  // a {ret} instruction (it can only return by throwing or trapping). So
2936  // if we do get here, there must have been a bug. Crash to flush it out.
2937  base::Vector<const ValueType> returns = decoder->sig_->returns();
2938  if (V8_UNLIKELY(std::any_of(
2939  returns.begin(), returns.end(),
2940  [](const ValueType type) { return type.is_uninhabited(); }))) {
2941  __ Abort(AbortReason::kUninhabitableType);
2942  return;
2943  }
2944  if (dynamic_tiering()) {
2945  TierupCheck(decoder, decoder->position(),
2946  __ pc_offset() + kTierUpCostForFunctionEntry);
2947  }
2948  size_t num_returns = decoder->sig_->return_count();
2949  if (num_returns > 0) __ MoveToReturnLocations(decoder->sig_, descriptor_);
2950  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
2951  __ CheckStackShrink();
2952  }
2953  __ LeaveFrame(StackFrame::WASM);
2954  __ DropStackSlotsAndRet(
2955  static_cast<uint32_t>(descriptor_->ParameterSlotCount()));
2956  }
2957 
2958  void LocalGet(FullDecoder* decoder, Value* result,
2959  const IndexImmediate& imm) {
2960  auto local_slot = __ cache_state()->stack_state[imm.index];
2961  __ cache_state()->stack_state.emplace_back(
2962  local_slot.kind(), __ NextSpillOffset(local_slot.kind()));
2963  auto* slot = &__ cache_state()->stack_state.back();
2964  if (local_slot.is_reg()) {
2965  __ cache_state()->inc_used(local_slot.reg());
2966  slot->MakeRegister(local_slot.reg());
2967  } else if (local_slot.is_const()) {
2968  slot->MakeConstant(local_slot.i32_const());
2969  } else {
2970  DCHECK(local_slot.is_stack());
2971  auto rc = reg_class_for(local_slot.kind());
2972  LiftoffRegister reg = __ GetUnusedRegister(rc, {});
2973  __ cache_state()->inc_used(reg);
2974  slot->MakeRegister(reg);
2975  __ Fill(reg, local_slot.offset(), local_slot.kind());
2976  }
2977  }
2978 
2979  void LocalSetFromStackSlot(VarState* dst_slot, uint32_t local_index) {
2980  auto& state = *__ cache_state();
2981  auto& src_slot = state.stack_state.back();
2982  ValueKind kind = dst_slot->kind();
2983  if (dst_slot->is_reg()) {
2984  LiftoffRegister slot_reg = dst_slot->reg();
2985  if (state.get_use_count(slot_reg) == 1) {
2986  __ Fill(dst_slot->reg(), src_slot.offset(), kind);
2987  return;
2988  }
2989  state.dec_used(slot_reg);
2990  dst_slot->MakeStack();
2991  }
2992  DCHECK(CompatibleStackSlotTypes(kind, __ local_kind(local_index)));
2993  RegClass rc = reg_class_for(kind);
2994  LiftoffRegister dst_reg = __ GetUnusedRegister(rc, {});
2995  __ Fill(dst_reg, src_slot.offset(), kind);
2996  *dst_slot = VarState(kind, dst_reg, dst_slot->offset());
2997  __ cache_state()->inc_used(dst_reg);
2998  }
2999 
3000  void LocalSet(uint32_t local_index, bool is_tee) {
3001  auto& state = *__ cache_state();
3002  auto& source_slot = state.stack_state.back();
3003  auto& target_slot = state.stack_state[local_index];
3004  switch (source_slot.loc()) {
3005  case kRegister:
3006  if (target_slot.is_reg()) state.dec_used(target_slot.reg());
3007  target_slot.Copy(source_slot);
3008  if (is_tee) state.inc_used(target_slot.reg());
3009  break;
3010  case kIntConst:
3011  if (target_slot.is_reg()) state.dec_used(target_slot.reg());
3012  target_slot.Copy(source_slot);
3013  break;
3014  case kStack:
3015  LocalSetFromStackSlot(&target_slot, local_index);
3016  break;
3017  }
3018  if (!is_tee) __ cache_state()->stack_state.pop_back();
3019  }

3031  Register GetGlobalBaseAndOffset(const WasmGlobal* global,
3032  LiftoffRegList* pinned, uint32_t* offset) {
3033  Register addr = pinned->set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {})).gp();
3034  if (global->mutability && global->imported) {
3035  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(addr, ImportedMutableGlobals, *pinned);
3036  int field_offset =
3037  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedAddressArray(
3038  global->index);
3039  __ LoadFullPointer(addr, addr, field_offset);
3040  *offset = 0;
3041 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
3042  __ DecodeSandboxedPointer(addr);
3043 #endif
3044  } else {
3045  LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(addr, GlobalsStart, kSystemPointerSize, *pinned);
3046  *offset = global->offset;
3047  }
3048  return addr;
3049  }
3050 
3051  void GetBaseAndOffsetForImportedMutableExternRefGlobal(
3052  const WasmGlobal* global, LiftoffRegList* pinned, Register* base,
3053  Register* offset) {
3054  Register globals_buffer =
3055  pinned->set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, *pinned)).gp();
3056  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(globals_buffer,
3057  ImportedMutableGlobalsBuffers, *pinned);
3058  *base = globals_buffer;
3059  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
3060  *base, globals_buffer, no_reg,
3061  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(global->offset));
3062 
3063  // For the offset we need the index of the global in the buffer, and
3064  // then calculate the actual offset from the index. Load the index from
3065  // the ImportedMutableGlobals array of the instance.
3066  Register imported_mutable_globals =
3067  pinned->set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, *pinned)).gp();
3068 
3069  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(imported_mutable_globals,
3070  ImportedMutableGlobals, *pinned);
3071  *offset = imported_mutable_globals;
3072  int field_offset =
3073  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedAddressArray(
3074  global->index);
3075  __ Load(LiftoffRegister(*offset), imported_mutable_globals, no_reg,
3076  field_offset, LoadType::kI32Load);
3077  __ emit_i32_shli(*offset, *offset, kTaggedSizeLog2);
3078  __ emit_i32_addi(*offset, *offset,
3079  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(0));
3080  }
3081 
3082  void GlobalGet(FullDecoder* decoder, Value* result,
3083  const GlobalIndexImmediate& imm) {
3084  const auto* global = &env_->module->globals[imm.index];
3085  ValueKind kind = global->type.kind();
3086  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, kind, "global")) {
3087  return;
3088  }
3089 
3090  if (is_reference(kind)) {
3091  if (global->mutability && global->imported) {
3092  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3093  Register base = no_reg;
3094  Register offset = no_reg;
3095  GetBaseAndOffsetForImportedMutableExternRefGlobal(global, &pinned,
3096  &base, &offset);
3097  __ LoadTaggedPointer(base, base, offset, 0);
3098  __ PushRegister(kind, LiftoffRegister(base));
3099  return;
3100  }
3101 
3102  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3103  Register globals_buffer =
3104  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
3105  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(globals_buffer, TaggedGlobalsBuffer,
3106  pinned);
3107  Register value = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
3108  __ LoadTaggedPointer(value, globals_buffer, no_reg,
3109  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(
3110  imm.global->offset));
3111  __ PushRegister(kind, LiftoffRegister(value));
3112  return;
3113  }
3114  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3115  uint32_t offset = 0;
3116  Register addr = GetGlobalBaseAndOffset(global, &pinned, &offset);
3117  LiftoffRegister value =
3118  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(kind), pinned));
3119  LoadType type = LoadType::ForValueKind(kind);
3120  __ Load(value, addr, no_reg, offset, type, nullptr, false);
3121  __ PushRegister(kind, value);
3122  }

3124  void GlobalSet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value&,
3125  const GlobalIndexImmediate& imm) {
3126  auto* global = &env_->module->globals[imm.index];
3127  ValueKind kind = global->type.kind();
3128  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, kind, "global")) {
3129  return;
3130  }
3131 
3132  if (is_reference(kind)) {
3133  if (global->mutability && global->imported) {
3134  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3135  Register value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned)).gp();
3136  Register base = no_reg;
3137  Register offset = no_reg;
3138  GetBaseAndOffsetForImportedMutableExternRefGlobal(global, &pinned,
3139  &base, &offset);
3140  __ StoreTaggedPointer(base, offset, 0, value, pinned);
3141  return;
3142  }
3143 
3144  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3145  Register globals_buffer =
3146  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
3147  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(globals_buffer, TaggedGlobalsBuffer,
3148  pinned);
3149  Register value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned)).gp();
3150  __ StoreTaggedPointer(globals_buffer, no_reg,
3151  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(
3152  imm.global->offset),
3153  value, pinned);
3154  return;
3155  }
3156  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3157  uint32_t offset = 0;
3158  Register addr = GetGlobalBaseAndOffset(global, &pinned, &offset);
3159  LiftoffRegister reg = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
3160  StoreType type = StoreType::ForValueKind(kind);
3161  __ Store(addr, no_reg, offset, reg, type, {}, nullptr, false);
3162  }

3164  void TableGet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value&, Value*,
3165  const TableIndexImmediate& imm) {
3166  Register index_high_word = no_reg;
3167  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3168  VarState table_index{kI32, static_cast<int>(imm.index), 0};
3169 
3170  // Convert the index to the table to an intptr.
3171  VarState index = PopIndexToVarState(&index_high_word, &pinned);
3172  // Trap if any bit in the high word was set.
3173  CheckHighWordEmptyForTableType(decoder, index_high_word, &pinned);
3174 
3175  ValueType type = imm.table->type;
3176  bool is_funcref = IsSubtypeOf(type, kWasmFuncRef, env_->module);
3177  auto stub =
3178  is_funcref ? Builtin::kWasmTableGetFuncRef : Builtin::kWasmTableGet;
3179 
3180  CallBuiltin(stub, MakeSig::Returns(type.kind()).Params(kI32, kIntPtrKind),
3181  {table_index, index}, decoder->position());
3182 
3183  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
3184 
3185  __ PushRegister(type.kind(), LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0));
3186  }

3188  void TableSet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value&, const Value&,
3189  const TableIndexImmediate& imm) {
3190  Register index_high_word = no_reg;
3191  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3192  VarState table_index{kI32, static_cast<int>(imm.index), 0};
3193 
3194  VarState value = __ PopVarState();
3195  if (value.is_reg()) pinned.set(value.reg());
3196  // Convert the index to the table to an intptr.
3197  VarState index = PopIndexToVarState(&index_high_word, &pinned);
3198  // Trap if any bit in the high word was set.
3199  CheckHighWordEmptyForTableType(decoder, index_high_word, &pinned);
3200  VarState extract_shared_part{kI32, 0, 0};
3201 
3202  bool is_funcref = IsSubtypeOf(imm.table->type, kWasmFuncRef, env_->module);
3203  auto stub =
3204  is_funcref ? Builtin::kWasmTableSetFuncRef : Builtin::kWasmTableSet;
3205 
3206  CallBuiltin(stub, MakeSig::Params(kI32, kI32, kIntPtrKind, kRefNull),
3207  {table_index, extract_shared_part, index, value},
3208  decoder->position());
3209 
3210  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
3211  }

3213  Builtin GetBuiltinForTrapReason(TrapReason reason) {
3214  switch (reason) {
3215 #define RUNTIME_STUB_FOR_TRAP(trap_reason) \
3216  case k##trap_reason: \
3217  return Builtin::kThrowWasm##trap_reason;
3218 
3219  FOREACH_WASM_TRAPREASON(RUNTIME_STUB_FOR_TRAP)
3220 #undef RUNTIME_STUB_FOR_TRAP
3221  default:
3222  UNREACHABLE();
3223  }
3224  }

3228  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, GetBuiltinForTrapReason(reason));
3229  __ emit_jump(trap.label());
3230  __ AssertUnreachable(AbortReason::kUnexpectedReturnFromWasmTrap);
3231  }

3233  void AssertNullTypecheckImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& arg,
3234  Value* result, Condition cond) {
3235  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3236  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
3237  LiftoffRegister null = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
3238  LoadNullValueForCompare(null.gp(), pinned, arg.type);
3239  {
3240  OolTrapLabel trap =
3241  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapIllegalCast);
3242  __ emit_cond_jump(cond, trap.label(), kRefNull, obj.gp(), null.gp(),
3243  trap.frozen());
3244  }
3245  __ PushRegister(kRefNull, obj);
3246  }

3262  void Select(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& cond, const Value& fval,
3263  const Value& tval, Value* result) {
3264  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3265  Register condition = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister()).gp();
3266  ValueKind kind = __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1].kind();
3267  DCHECK(CompatibleStackSlotTypes(
3268  kind, __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-2].kind()));
3269  LiftoffRegister false_value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
3270  LiftoffRegister true_value = __ PopToRegister(pinned);
3271  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(true_value.reg_class(),
3272  {true_value, false_value}, {});
3273  if (!__ emit_select(dst, condition, true_value, false_value, kind)) {
3274  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
3275  // Emit generic code (using branches) instead.
3276  Label cont;
3277  Label case_false;
3278  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &case_false, kI32, condition, no_reg, frozen);
3279  if (dst != true_value) __ Move(dst, true_value, kind);
3280  __ emit_jump(&cont);
3281 
3282  __ bind(&case_false);
3283  if (dst != false_value) __ Move(dst, false_value, kind);
3284  __ bind(&cont);
3285  }
3286  __ PushRegister(kind, dst);
3287  }
3288 
3289  void BrImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* target) {
3290  if (dynamic_tiering()) {
3291  if (target->is_loop()) {
3292  DCHECK(target->label.get()->is_bound());
3293  int jump_distance = __ pc_offset() - target->label.get()->pos();
3294  TierupCheck(decoder, decoder->position(), jump_distance);
3295  } else {
3296  // To estimate time spent in this function more accurately, we could
3297  // increment the tiering budget on forward jumps. However, we don't
3298  // know the jump distance yet; using a blanket value has been tried
3299  // and found to not make a difference.
3300  }
3301  }
3302  if (target->br_merge()->reached) {
3303  __ MergeStackWith(target->label_state, target->br_merge()->arity,
3304  target->is_loop() ? LiftoffAssembler::kBackwardJump
3305  : LiftoffAssembler::kForwardJump);
3306  } else {
3307  target->label_state =
3308  __ MergeIntoNewState(__ num_locals(), target->br_merge()->arity,
3309  target->stack_depth + target->num_exceptions);
3310  }
3311  __ jmp(target->label.get());
3312  }
3313 
3314  bool NeedsTierupCheck(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t br_depth) {
3315  if (!dynamic_tiering()) return false;
3316  return br_depth == decoder->control_depth() - 1 ||
3317  decoder->control_at(br_depth)->is_loop();
3318  }
3319 
3320  void BrOrRet(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t depth) {
3321  if (depth == decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
3322  ReturnImpl(decoder);
3323  } else {
3324  BrImpl(decoder, decoder->control_at(depth));
3325  }
3326  }
3327 
3328  void BrIf(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& /* cond */, uint32_t depth) {
3329  // Avoid having sequences of branches do duplicate work.
3330  if (depth != decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
3331  __ PrepareForBranch(decoder->control_at(depth)->br_merge()->arity, {});
3332  }
3333 
3334  Label cont_false;
3335 
3336  // Test the condition on the value stack, jump to {cont_false} if zero.
3337  std::optional<FreezeCacheState> frozen;
3338  JumpIfFalse(decoder, &cont_false, frozen);
3339 
3340  BrOrRet(decoder, depth);
3341 
3342  __ bind(&cont_false);
3343  }
3344 
3345  // Generate a branch table case, potentially reusing previously generated
3346  // stack transfer code.
3347  void GenerateBrCase(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t br_depth,
3348  ZoneMap<uint32_t, MovableLabel>* br_targets) {
3349  auto [iterator, is_new_target] = br_targets->emplace(br_depth, zone_);
3350  Label* label = iterator->second.get();
3351  DCHECK_EQ(is_new_target, !label->is_bound());
3352  if (is_new_target) {
3353  __ bind(label);
3354  BrOrRet(decoder, br_depth);
3355  } else {
3356  __ jmp(label);
3357  }
3358  }
3359 
3360  // Generate a branch table for input in [min, max).
3361  // TODO(wasm): Generate a real branch table (like TF TableSwitch).
3362  void GenerateBrTable(FullDecoder* decoder, LiftoffRegister value,
3363  uint32_t min, uint32_t max,
3364  BranchTableIterator<ValidationTag>* table_iterator,
3365  ZoneMap<uint32_t, MovableLabel>* br_targets,
3366  const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
3367  DCHECK_LT(min, max);
3368  // Check base case.
3369  if (max == min + 1) {
3370  DCHECK_EQ(min, table_iterator->cur_index());
3371  GenerateBrCase(decoder, table_iterator->next(), br_targets);
3372  return;
3373  }
3374 
3375  uint32_t split = min + (max - min) / 2;
3376  Label upper_half;
3377  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, &upper_half, value.gp(),
3378  split, frozen);
3379  // Emit br table for lower half:
3380  GenerateBrTable(decoder, value, min, split, table_iterator, br_targets,
3381  frozen);
3382  __ bind(&upper_half);
3383  // table_iterator will trigger a DCHECK if we don't stop decoding now.
3384  if (did_bailout()) return;
3385  // Emit br table for upper half:
3386  GenerateBrTable(decoder, value, split, max, table_iterator, br_targets,
3387  frozen);
3388  }
3389 
3390  void BrTable(FullDecoder* decoder, const BranchTableImmediate& imm,
3391  const Value& key) {
3392  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3393  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister());
3394 
3395  {
3396  // All targets must have the same arity (checked by validation), so
3397  // we can just sample any of them to find that arity.
3398  auto [sample_depth, unused_length] =
3399  decoder->read_u32v<Decoder::NoValidationTag>(imm.table,
3400  "first depth");
3401  __ PrepareForBranch(decoder->control_at(sample_depth)->br_merge()->arity,
3402  pinned);
3403  }
3404 
3405  BranchTableIterator<ValidationTag> table_iterator{decoder, imm};
3406  ZoneMap<uint32_t, MovableLabel> br_targets{zone_};
3407 
3408  if (imm.table_count > 0) {
3409  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
3410  Label case_default;
3411  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, &case_default,
3412  value.gp(), imm.table_count, frozen);
3413 
3414  GenerateBrTable(decoder, value, 0, imm.table_count, &table_iterator,
3415  &br_targets, frozen);
3416 
3417  __ bind(&case_default);
3418  // table_iterator will trigger a DCHECK if we don't stop decoding now.
3419  if (did_bailout()) return;
3420  }
3421 
3422  // Generate the default case.
3423  GenerateBrCase(decoder, table_iterator.next(), &br_targets);
3424  DCHECK(!table_iterator.has_next());
3425  }
3426 
3427  void Else(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* c) {
3428  if (c->reachable()) {
3429  if (c->end_merge.reached) {
3430  __ MergeFullStackWith(c->label_state);
3431  } else {
3432  c->label_state =
3433  __ MergeIntoNewState(__ num_locals(), c->end_merge.arity,
3434  c->stack_depth + c->num_exceptions);
3435  }
3436  __ emit_jump(c->label.get());
3437  }
3438  __ bind(c->else_state->label.get());
3439  __ cache_state()->Steal(c->else_state->state);
3440  }
3441 
3442  SpilledRegistersForInspection* GetSpilledRegistersForInspection() {
3443  DCHECK(for_debugging_);
3444  // If we are generating debugging code, we really need to spill all
3445  // registers to make them inspectable when stopping at the trap.
3446  auto* spilled = zone_->New<SpilledRegistersForInspection>(zone_);
3447  for (uint32_t i = 0, e = __ cache_state()->stack_height(); i < e; ++i) {
3448  auto& slot = __ cache_state()->stack_state[i];
3449  if (!slot.is_reg()) continue;
3450  spilled->entries.push_back(SpilledRegistersForInspection::Entry{
3451  slot.offset(), slot.reg(), slot.kind()});
3452  __ RecordUsedSpillOffset(slot.offset());
3453  }
3454  return spilled;
3455  }
