3462  class OolTrapLabel {
3463  public:
3464  OolTrapLabel(LiftoffAssembler& assembler, Label* label)
3465  : label_(label), freeze_(assembler) {}
3466 
3467  Label* label() const { return label_; }
3468  const FreezeCacheState& frozen() const { return freeze_; }
3469 
3470  private:
3471  Label* label_;
3472  FreezeCacheState freeze_;
3473  };
3474 
3475  OolTrapLabel AddOutOfLineTrap(FullDecoder* decoder, Builtin builtin) {
3476  DCHECK_IMPLIES(builtin == Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapMemOutOfBounds,
3477  v8_flags.wasm_bounds_checks);
3478  OutOfLineSafepointInfo* safepoint_info = nullptr;
3479  // Execution does not return after a trap. Therefore we don't have to define
3480  // a safepoint for traps that would preserve references on the stack.
3481  // However, if this is debug code, then we have to preserve the references
3482  // so that they can be inspected.
3483  if (V8_UNLIKELY(for_debugging_)) {
3484  safepoint_info = zone_->New<OutOfLineSafepointInfo>(zone_);
3485  __ cache_state()->GetTaggedSlotsForOOLCode(
3486  &safepoint_info->slots, &safepoint_info->spills,
3487  LiftoffAssembler::CacheState::SpillLocation::kStackSlots);
3488  }
3489  out_of_line_code_.push_back(OutOfLineCode::Trap(
3490  zone_, builtin, decoder->position(),
3491  V8_UNLIKELY(for_debugging_) ? GetSpilledRegistersForInspection()
3492  : nullptr,
3493  safepoint_info, RegisterOOLDebugSideTableEntry(decoder)));
3494  return OolTrapLabel(asm_, out_of_line_code_.back().label.get());
3495  }
3496 
3497  enum ForceCheck : bool { kDoForceCheck = true, kDontForceCheck = false };
3498  enum AlignmentCheck : bool {
3499  kCheckAlignment = true,
3500  kDontCheckAlignment = false
3501  };
3502 
3503  // Returns the GP {index} register holding the ptrsized index.
3504  // Note that the {index} will typically not be pinned, but the returned
3505  // register will be pinned by the caller. This avoids one pinned register if
3506  // {full_index} is a pair.
3507  Register BoundsCheckMem(FullDecoder* decoder, const WasmMemory* memory,
3508  uint32_t access_size, uint64_t offset,
3509  LiftoffRegister index, LiftoffRegList pinned,
3510  ForceCheck force_check,
3511  AlignmentCheck check_alignment) {
3512  // The decoder ensures that the access is not statically OOB.
3513  DCHECK(base::IsInBounds<uintptr_t>(offset, access_size,
3514  memory->max_memory_size));
3515 
3516  wasm::BoundsCheckStrategy bounds_checks = memory->bounds_checks;
3517 
3518  // After bounds checking, we know that the index must be ptrsize, hence only
3519  // look at the lower word on 32-bit systems (the high word is bounds-checked
3520  // further down).
3521  Register index_ptrsize =
3522  kNeedI64RegPair && index.is_gp_pair() ? index.low_gp() : index.gp();
3523 
3524  if (check_alignment) {
3525  AlignmentCheckMem(decoder, access_size, offset, index_ptrsize,
3526  pinned | LiftoffRegList{index});
3527  }
3528 
3529  // Without bounds checks (testing only), just return the ptrsize index.
3530  if (V8_UNLIKELY(bounds_checks == kNoBoundsChecks)) {
3531  return index_ptrsize;
3532  }
3533 
3534  // We already checked that an access at `offset` is within max memory size.
3535  uintptr_t end_offset = offset + access_size - 1u;
3536  DCHECK_LT(end_offset, memory->max_memory_size);
3537 
3538  // Early return for trap handler.
3539  bool use_trap_handler = !force_check && bounds_checks == kTrapHandler;
3540 
3541  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
3542  memory->is_memory64() && !v8_flags.wasm_memory64_trap_handling,
3543  bounds_checks == kExplicitBoundsChecks);
3544 #if V8_TRAP_HANDLER_SUPPORTED
3545  if (use_trap_handler) {
3546 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64 || V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64
3547  if (memory->is_memory64()) {
3548  FREEZE_STATE(trapping);
3549  OolTrapLabel trap =
3550  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapMemOutOfBounds);
3551  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("bounds check memory");
3552  // Bounds check `index` against `max_mem_size - end_offset`, such that
3553  // at runtime `index + end_offset` will be < `max_mem_size`, where the
3554  // trap handler can handle out-of-bound accesses.
3555  __ set_trap_on_oob_mem64(index_ptrsize, kMaxMemory64Size - end_offset,
3556  trap.label());
3557  }
3558 #else
3559  CHECK(!memory->is_memory64());
3560 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64 || V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64
3561 
3562  // With trap handlers we should not have a register pair as input (we
3563  // would only return the lower half).
3564  DCHECK(index.is_gp());
3565  return index_ptrsize;
3566  }
3567 #else
3568  CHECK(!use_trap_handler);
3569 #endif // V8_TRAP_HANDLER_SUPPORTED
3570 
3571  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("bounds check memory");
3572 
3573  pinned.set(index_ptrsize);
3574  // Convert the index to ptrsize, bounds-checking the high word on 32-bit
3575  // systems for memory64.
3576  if (!memory->is_memory64()) {
3577  __ emit_u32_to_uintptr(index_ptrsize, index_ptrsize);
3578  } else if (kSystemPointerSize == kInt32Size) {
3579  DCHECK_GE(kMaxUInt32, memory->max_memory_size);
3580  OolTrapLabel trap =
3581  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapMemOutOfBounds);
3582  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotZero, trap.label(), kI32, index.high_gp(), no_reg,
3583  trap.frozen());
3584  }
3585 
3586  // Note that allocating the registers here before creating the trap label is
3587  // needed to prevent the tagged bits for the ool safe point to be
3588  // invalidated!
3589  LiftoffRegister end_offset_reg =
3590  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
3591  LiftoffRegister mem_size = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
3592 
3593  // TODO(13957): Clamp the loaded memory size to a safe value.
3594  if (memory->index == 0) {
3595  LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(mem_size.gp(), Memory0Size, kSystemPointerSize,
3596  pinned);
3597  } else {
3598  LOAD_PROTECTED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(mem_size.gp(), MemoryBasesAndSizes,
3599  pinned);
3600  int buffer_offset =
3601  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(ByteArray)) +
3602  kSystemPointerSize * (memory->index * 2 + 1);
3603  __ LoadFullPointer(mem_size.gp(), mem_size.gp(), buffer_offset);
3604  }
3605 
3606  // {for_debugging_} needs spill slots in out of line code.
3607  OolTrapLabel trap =
3608  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapMemOutOfBounds);
3609 
3610  __ LoadConstant(end_offset_reg, WasmValue::ForUintPtr(end_offset));
3611 
3612  // If the end offset is larger than the smallest memory, dynamically check
3613  // the end offset against the actual memory size, which is not known at
3614  // compile time. Otherwise, only one check is required (see below).
3615  if (end_offset > memory->min_memory_size) {
3616  __ emit_cond_jump(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, trap.label(), kIntPtrKind,
3617  end_offset_reg.gp(), mem_size.gp(), trap.frozen());
3618  }
3619 
3620  // Just reuse the end_offset register for computing the effective size
3621  // (which is >= 0 because of the check above).
3622  LiftoffRegister effective_size_reg = end_offset_reg;
3623  __ emit_ptrsize_sub(effective_size_reg.gp(), mem_size.gp(),
3624  end_offset_reg.gp());
3625 
3626  __ emit_cond_jump(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, trap.label(), kIntPtrKind,
3627  index_ptrsize, effective_size_reg.gp(), trap.frozen());
3628  return index_ptrsize;
3629  }
3630 
3631  void AlignmentCheckMem(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t access_size,
3632  uintptr_t offset, Register index,
3633  LiftoffRegList pinned) {
3634  DCHECK_NE(0, access_size);
3635  // For access_size 1 there is no minimum alignment.
3636  if (access_size == 1) return;
3637  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("alignment check");
3638  Register address = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
3639  OolTrapLabel trap =
3640  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapUnalignedAccess);
3641 
3642  const uint32_t align_mask = access_size - 1;
3643  if ((offset & align_mask) == 0) {
3644  // If {offset} is aligned, we can produce faster code.
3645 
3646  // TODO(ahaas): On Intel, the "test" instruction implicitly computes the
3647  // AND of two operands. We could introduce a new variant of
3648  // {emit_cond_jump} to use the "test" instruction without the "and" here.
3649  // Then we can also avoid using the temp register here.
3650  __ emit_i32_andi(address, index, align_mask);
3651  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, trap.label(), kI32, address, no_reg,
3652  trap.frozen());
3653  } else {
3654  // For alignment checks we only look at the lower 32-bits in {offset}.
3655  __ emit_i32_addi(address, index, static_cast<uint32_t>(offset));
3656  __ emit_i32_andi(address, address, align_mask);
3657  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, trap.label(), kI32, address, no_reg,
3658  trap.frozen());
3659  }
3660  }
3661 
3662  void TraceMemoryOperation(bool is_store, MachineRepresentation rep,
3663  Register index, uintptr_t offset,
3664  WasmCodePosition position) {
3665  // Before making the runtime call, spill all cache registers.
3666  __ SpillAllRegisters();
3667 
3668  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3669  if (index != no_reg) pinned.set(index);
3670  // Get one register for computing the effective offset (offset + index).
3671  LiftoffRegister effective_offset =
3672  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
3673  // TODO(14259): Support multiple memories.
3674  const WasmMemory* memory = env_->module->memories.data();
3675  if (memory->is_memory64() && !kNeedI64RegPair) {
3676  __ LoadConstant(effective_offset,
3677  WasmValue(static_cast<uint64_t>(offset)));
3678  if (index != no_reg) {
3679  __ emit_i64_add(effective_offset, effective_offset,
3680  LiftoffRegister(index));
3681  }
3682  } else {
3683  // The offset is actually a 32-bits number when 'kNeedI64RegPair'
3684  // is true, so we just do 32-bits operations on it under memory64.
3685  DCHECK_GE(kMaxUInt32, offset);
3686  __ LoadConstant(effective_offset,
3687  WasmValue(static_cast<uint32_t>(offset)));
3688  if (index != no_reg) {
3689  __ emit_i32_add(effective_offset.gp(), effective_offset.gp(), index);
3690  }
3691  }
3692 
3693  // Get a register to hold the stack slot for MemoryTracingInfo.
3694  LiftoffRegister info = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
3695  // Allocate stack slot for MemoryTracingInfo.
3696  __ AllocateStackSlot(info.gp(), sizeof(MemoryTracingInfo));
3697 
3698  // Reuse the {effective_offset} register for all information to be stored in
3699  // the MemoryTracingInfo struct.
3700  LiftoffRegister data = effective_offset;
3701 
3702  // Now store all information into the MemoryTracingInfo struct.
3703  if (kSystemPointerSize == 8 && !memory->is_memory64()) {
3704  // Zero-extend the effective offset to u64.
3705  CHECK(__ emit_type_conversion(kExprI64UConvertI32, data, effective_offset,
3706  nullptr));
3707  }
3708  __ Store(
3709  info.gp(), no_reg, offsetof(MemoryTracingInfo, offset), data,
3710  kSystemPointerSize == 8 ? StoreType::kI64Store : StoreType::kI32Store,
3711  pinned);
3712  __ LoadConstant(data, WasmValue(is_store ? 1 : 0));
3713  __ Store(info.gp(), no_reg, offsetof(MemoryTracingInfo, is_store), data,
3714  StoreType::kI32Store8, pinned);
3715  __ LoadConstant(data, WasmValue(static_cast<int>(rep)));
3716  __ Store(info.gp(), no_reg, offsetof(MemoryTracingInfo, mem_rep), data,
3717  StoreType::kI32Store8, pinned);
3718 
3719  WasmTraceMemoryDescriptor descriptor;
3720  DCHECK_EQ(0, descriptor.GetStackParameterCount());
3721  DCHECK_EQ(1, descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount());
3722  Register param_reg = descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(0);
3723  if (info.gp() != param_reg) {
3724  __ Move(param_reg, info.gp(), kIntPtrKind);
3725  }
3726 
3727  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(__ pc_offset(),
3728  SourcePosition(position), false);
3729  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmTraceMemory);
3730  DefineSafepoint();
3731 
3732  __ DeallocateStackSlot(sizeof(MemoryTracingInfo));
3733  }
3734 
3735  bool IndexStaticallyInBounds(const WasmMemory* memory,
3736  const VarState& index_slot, int access_size,
3737  uintptr_t* offset) {
3738  if (!index_slot.is_const()) return false;
3739 
3740  // memory64: Sign-extend to restore the original index value.
3741  // memory32: Zero-extend the 32 bit value.
3742  const uintptr_t index =
3743  memory->is_memory64()
3744  ? static_cast<uintptr_t>(intptr_t{index_slot.i32_const()})
3745  : uintptr_t{static_cast<uint32_t>(index_slot.i32_const())};
3746  const uintptr_t effective_offset = index + *offset;
3747 
3748  if (effective_offset < index // overflow
3749  || !base::IsInBounds<uintptr_t>(effective_offset, access_size,
3750  memory->min_memory_size)) {
3751  return false;
3752  }
3753 
3754  *offset = effective_offset;
3755  return true;
3756  }
3757 
3758  bool IndexStaticallyInBoundsAndAligned(const WasmMemory* memory,
3759  const VarState& index_slot,
3760  int access_size, uintptr_t* offset) {
3761  uintptr_t new_offset = *offset;
3762  if (IndexStaticallyInBounds(memory, index_slot, access_size, &new_offset) &&
3763  IsAligned(new_offset, access_size)) {
3764  *offset = new_offset;
3765  return true;
3766  }
3767  return false;
3768  }
3769 
3770  V8_INLINE Register GetMemoryStart(int memory_index, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
3771  if (memory_index == __ cache_state()->cached_mem_index) {
3772  Register memory_start = __ cache_state()->cached_mem_start;
3773  DCHECK_NE(no_reg, memory_start);
3774  return memory_start;
3775  }
3776  return GetMemoryStart_Slow(memory_index, pinned);
3777  }
3778 
3779  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST Register
3780  GetMemoryStart_Slow(int memory_index, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
3781  // This method should only be called if we cannot use the cached memory
3782  // start.
3783  DCHECK_NE(memory_index, __ cache_state()->cached_mem_index);
3784  __ cache_state()->ClearCachedMemStartRegister();
3785  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("load memory start");
3786  Register memory_start = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
3787  if (memory_index == 0) {
3788  LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(memory_start, Memory0Start, kSystemPointerSize,
3789  pinned);
3790  } else {
3791  LOAD_PROTECTED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(memory_start, MemoryBasesAndSizes,
3792  pinned);
3793  int buffer_offset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
3794  TrustedFixedAddressArray::OffsetOfElementAt(memory_index * 2));
3795  __ LoadFullPointer(memory_start, memory_start, buffer_offset);
3796  }
3797  __ cache_state()->SetMemStartCacheRegister(memory_start, memory_index);
3798  return memory_start;
3799  }
3800 
3801  void LoadMem(FullDecoder* decoder, LoadType type,
3802  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm, const Value& index_val,
3803  Value* result) {
3804  DCHECK_EQ(type.value_type().kind(), result->type.kind());
3805  bool needs_f16_to_f32_conv = false;
3806  if (type.value() == LoadType::kF32LoadF16 &&
3807  !asm_.supports_f16_mem_access()) {
3808  needs_f16_to_f32_conv = true;
3809  type = LoadType::kI32Load16U;
3810  }
3811  ValueKind kind = type.value_type().kind();
3812  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, kind, "load")) return;
3813 
3814  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
3815  Register index = no_reg;
3816  RegClass rc = reg_class_for(kind);
3817 
3818  // Only look at the slot, do not pop it yet (will happen in PopToRegister
3819  // below, if this is not a statically-in-bounds index).
3820  auto& index_slot = __ cache_state()->stack_state.back();
3821  DCHECK_EQ(index_val.type.kind(), index_slot.kind());
3822  bool i64_offset = imm.memory->is_memory64();
3823  DCHECK_EQ(i64_offset ? kI64 : kI32, index_slot.kind());
3824  if (IndexStaticallyInBounds(imm.memory, index_slot, type.size(), &offset)) {
3825  __ cache_state()->stack_state.pop_back();
3826  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("load from memory (constant offset)");
3827  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3828  Register mem = pinned.set(GetMemoryStart(imm.memory->index, pinned));
3829  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(rc, pinned));
3830  __ Load(value, mem, no_reg, offset, type, nullptr, true, i64_offset);
3831  if (needs_f16_to_f32_conv) {
3832  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, {});
3833  auto conv_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_float16_to_float32();
3834  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(&dst, kVoid, kF32,
3835  {VarState{kI16, value, 0}}, conv_ref);
3836  __ PushRegister(kF32, dst);
3837  } else {
3838  __ PushRegister(kind, value);
3839  }
3840  } else {
3841  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PopToRegister();
3842  index =
3843  BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, type.size(), offset, full_index,
3844  {}, kDontForceCheck, kDontCheckAlignment);
3845 
3846  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("load from memory");
3847  LiftoffRegList pinned{index};
3848 
3849  // Load the memory start address only now to reduce register pressure
3850  // (important on ia32).
3851  Register mem = pinned.set(GetMemoryStart(imm.memory->index, pinned));
3852  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(rc, pinned));
3853 
3854  uint32_t protected_load_pc = 0;
3855  __ Load(value, mem, index, offset, type, &protected_load_pc, true,
3856  i64_offset);
3857  if (imm.memory->bounds_checks == kTrapHandler) {
3858  RegisterProtectedInstruction(decoder, protected_load_pc);
3859  }
3860  if (needs_f16_to_f32_conv) {
3861  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, {});
3862  auto conv_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_float16_to_float32();
3863  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(&dst, kVoid, kF32,
3864  {VarState{kI16, value, 0}}, conv_ref);
3865  __ PushRegister(kF32, dst);
3866  } else {
3867  __ PushRegister(kind, value);
3868  }
3869  }
3870 
3871  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory)) {
3872  // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
3873  CHECK_EQ(0, imm.memory->index);
3874  TraceMemoryOperation(false, type.mem_type().representation(), index,
3875  offset, decoder->position());
3876  }
3877  }
3878 
3879  void LoadTransform(FullDecoder* decoder, LoadType type,
3880  LoadTransformationKind transform,
3881  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm, const Value& index_val,
3882  Value* result) {
3883  CHECK(CheckSupportedType(decoder, kS128, "LoadTransform"));
3884 
3885  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PopToRegister();
3886  // For load splats and load zero, LoadType is the size of the load, and for
3887  // load extends, LoadType is the size of the lane, and it always loads 8
3888  // bytes.
3889  uint32_t access_size =
3890  transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend ? 8 : type.size();
3891  Register index =
3892  BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, access_size, imm.offset, full_index,
3893  {}, kDontForceCheck, kDontCheckAlignment);
3894 
3895  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
3896  LiftoffRegList pinned{index};
3897  CODE_COMMENT("load with transformation");
3898  Register addr = GetMemoryStart(imm.mem_index, pinned);
3899  LiftoffRegister value = __ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(kS128), {});
3900  uint32_t protected_load_pc = 0;
3901  bool i64_offset = imm.memory->is_memory64();
3902  __ LoadTransform(value, addr, index, offset, type, transform,
3903  &protected_load_pc, i64_offset);
3904 
3905  if (imm.memory->bounds_checks == kTrapHandler) {
3906  protected_instructions_.emplace_back(
3907  trap_handler::ProtectedInstructionData{protected_load_pc});
3908  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
3909  protected_load_pc, SourcePosition(decoder->position()), true);
3910  if (for_debugging_) {
3911  DefineSafepoint(protected_load_pc);
3912  }
3913  }
3914  __ PushRegister(kS128, value);
3915 
3916  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory)) {
3917  // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
3918  CHECK_EQ(0, imm.memory->index);
3919  // Again load extend is different.
3920  MachineRepresentation mem_rep =
3921  transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend
3922  ? MachineRepresentation::kWord64
3923  : type.mem_type().representation();
3924  TraceMemoryOperation(false, mem_rep, index, offset, decoder->position());
3925  }
3926  }
3927 
3928  void LoadLane(FullDecoder* decoder, LoadType type, const Value& _value,
3929  const Value& _index, const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm,
3930  const uint8_t laneidx, Value* _result) {
3931  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, kS128, "LoadLane")) {
3932  return;
3933  }
3934 
3935  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3936  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister());
3937  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PopToRegister();
3938  Register index =
3939  BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, type.size(), imm.offset, full_index,
3940  pinned, kDontForceCheck, kDontCheckAlignment);
3941 
3942  bool i64_offset = imm.memory->is_memory64();
3943  DCHECK_EQ(i64_offset ? kI64 : kI32, _index.type.kind());
3944 
3945  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
3946  pinned.set(index);
3947  CODE_COMMENT("load lane");
3948  Register addr = GetMemoryStart(imm.mem_index, pinned);
3949  LiftoffRegister result = __ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(kS128), {});
3950  uint32_t protected_load_pc = 0;
3951  __ LoadLane(result, value, addr, index, offset, type, laneidx,
3952  &protected_load_pc, i64_offset);
3953  if (imm.memory->bounds_checks == kTrapHandler) {
3954  protected_instructions_.emplace_back(
3955  trap_handler::ProtectedInstructionData{protected_load_pc});
3956  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
3957  protected_load_pc, SourcePosition(decoder->position()), true);
3958  if (for_debugging_) {
3959  DefineSafepoint(protected_load_pc);
3960  }
3961  }
3962 
3963  __ PushRegister(kS128, result);
3964 
3965  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory)) {
3966  // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
3967  CHECK_EQ(0, imm.memory->index);
3968  TraceMemoryOperation(false, type.mem_type().representation(), index,
3969  offset, decoder->position());
3970  }
3971  }
3972 
3973  void StoreMem(FullDecoder* decoder, StoreType type,
3974  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm, const Value& index_val,
3975  const Value& value_val) {
3976  ValueKind kind = type.value_type().kind();
3977  DCHECK_EQ(kind, value_val.type.kind());
3978  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, kind, "store")) return;
3979 
3980  LiftoffRegList pinned;
3981  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister());
3982 
3983  if (type.value() == StoreType::kF32StoreF16 &&
3984  !asm_.supports_f16_mem_access()) {
3985  type = StoreType::kI32Store16;
3986  // {value} is always a float, so can't alias with {i16}.
3987  DCHECK_EQ(kF32, kind);
3988  LiftoffRegister i16 = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {}));
3989  auto conv_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_float16();
3990  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(&i16, kVoid, kI16,
3991  {VarState{kF32, value, 0}}, conv_ref);
3992  value = i16;
3993  }
3994 
3995  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
3996  Register index = no_reg;
3997 
3998  auto& index_slot = __ cache_state()->stack_state.back();
3999  DCHECK_EQ(index_val.type.kind(), index_slot.kind());
4000  bool i64_offset = imm.memory->is_memory64();
4001  DCHECK_EQ(i64_offset ? kI64 : kI32, index_val.type.kind());
4002  if (IndexStaticallyInBounds(imm.memory, index_slot, type.size(), &offset)) {
4003  __ cache_state()->stack_state.pop_back();
4004  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("store to memory (constant offset)");
4005  Register mem = pinned.set(GetMemoryStart(imm.memory->index, pinned));
4006  __ Store(mem, no_reg, offset, value, type, pinned, nullptr, true,
4007  i64_offset);
4008  } else {
4009  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PopToRegister(pinned);
4010  ForceCheck force_check = (kPartialOOBWritesAreNoops || type.size() == 1)
4011  ? kDontForceCheck
4012  : kDoForceCheck;
4013  index =
4014  BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, type.size(), imm.offset,
4015  full_index, pinned, force_check, kDontCheckAlignment);
4016 
4017  pinned.set(index);
4018  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("store to memory");
4019  uint32_t protected_store_pc = 0;
4020  // Load the memory start address only now to reduce register pressure
4021  // (important on ia32).
4022  Register mem = pinned.set(GetMemoryStart(imm.memory->index, pinned));
4023  LiftoffRegList outer_pinned;
4024  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory)) outer_pinned.set(index);
4025  __ Store(mem, index, offset, value, type, outer_pinned,
4026  &protected_store_pc, true, i64_offset);
4027  if (imm.memory->bounds_checks == kTrapHandler) {
4028  RegisterProtectedInstruction(decoder, protected_store_pc);
4029  }
4030  }
4031 
4032  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory)) {
4033  // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
4034  CHECK_EQ(0, imm.memory->index);
4035  TraceMemoryOperation(true, type.mem_rep(), index, offset,
4036  decoder->position());
4037  }
4038  }
4039 
4040  void StoreLane(FullDecoder* decoder, StoreType type,
4041  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm, const Value& _index,
4042  const Value& _value, const uint8_t lane) {
4043  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, kS128, "StoreLane")) return;
4044  LiftoffRegList pinned;
4045  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister());
4046  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PopToRegister(pinned);
4047  ForceCheck force_check = (kPartialOOBWritesAreNoops || type.size() == 1)
4048  ? kDontForceCheck
4049  : kDoForceCheck;
4050  Register index =
4051  BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, type.size(), imm.offset, full_index,
4052  pinned, force_check, kDontCheckAlignment);
4053 
4054  bool i64_offset = imm.memory->is_memory64();
4055  DCHECK_EQ(i64_offset ? kI64 : kI32, _index.type.kind());
4056 
4057  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
4058  pinned.set(index);
4059  CODE_COMMENT("store lane to memory");
4060  Register addr = pinned.set(GetMemoryStart(imm.mem_index, pinned));
4061  uint32_t protected_store_pc = 0;
4062  __ StoreLane(addr, index, offset, value, type, lane, &protected_store_pc,
4063  i64_offset);
4064  if (imm.memory->bounds_checks == kTrapHandler) {
4065  protected_instructions_.emplace_back(
4066  trap_handler::ProtectedInstructionData{protected_store_pc});
4067  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
4068  protected_store_pc, SourcePosition(decoder->position()), true);
4069  if (for_debugging_) {
4070  DefineSafepoint(protected_store_pc);
4071  }
4072  }
4073  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory)) {
4074  // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
4075  CHECK_EQ(0, imm.memory->index);
4076  TraceMemoryOperation(true, type.mem_rep(), index, offset,
4077  decoder->position());
4078  }
4079  }
4080 
4081  void CurrentMemoryPages(FullDecoder* /* decoder */,
4082  const MemoryIndexImmediate& imm,
4083  Value* /* result */) {
4084  LiftoffRegList pinned;
4085  LiftoffRegister mem_size = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
4086  if (imm.memory->index == 0) {
4087  LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(mem_size.gp(), Memory0Size, kSystemPointerSize,
4088  pinned);
4089  } else {
4090  LOAD_PROTECTED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(mem_size.gp(), MemoryBasesAndSizes,
4091  pinned);
4092  int buffer_offset =
4093  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(ByteArray)) +
4094  kSystemPointerSize * (imm.memory->index * 2 + 1);
4095  __ LoadFullPointer(mem_size.gp(), mem_size.gp(), buffer_offset);
4096  }
4097  // Convert bytes to pages.
4098  __ emit_ptrsize_shri(mem_size.gp(), mem_size.gp(), kWasmPageSizeLog2);
4099  if (imm.memory->is_memory64() && kNeedI64RegPair) {
4100  LiftoffRegister high_word =
4101  __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, LiftoffRegList{mem_size});
4102  // The high word is always 0 on 32-bit systems.
4103  __ LoadConstant(high_word, WasmValue{uint32_t{0}});
4104  mem_size = LiftoffRegister::ForPair(mem_size.gp(), high_word.gp());
4105  }
4106  __ PushRegister(imm.memory->is_memory64() ? kI64 : kI32, mem_size);
4107  }
4108 
4109  void MemoryGrow(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryIndexImmediate& imm,
4110  const Value& value, Value* result_val) {
4111  // Pop the input, then spill all cache registers to make the runtime call.
4112  LiftoffRegList pinned;
4113  LiftoffRegister num_pages = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister());
4114  __ SpillAllRegisters();
4115 
4116  LiftoffRegister result = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
4117 
4118  Label done;
4119 
4120  if (imm.memory->is_memory64()) {
4121  // If the high word is not 0, this will always fail (would grow by
4122  // >=256TB). The int32_t value will be sign-extended below.
4123  __ LoadConstant(result, WasmValue(int32_t{-1}));
4124  if (kNeedI64RegPair) {
4125  FREEZE_STATE(all_spilled_anyway);
4126  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &done, kI32, num_pages.high_gp(), no_reg,
4127  all_spilled_anyway);
4128  num_pages = num_pages.low();
4129  } else {
4130  LiftoffRegister high_word = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
4131  __ emit_i64_shri(high_word, num_pages, 32);
4132  FREEZE_STATE(all_spilled_anyway);
4133  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &done, kI32, high_word.gp(), no_reg,
4134  all_spilled_anyway);
4135  }
4136  }
4137 
4138  WasmMemoryGrowDescriptor descriptor;
4139  DCHECK_EQ(0, descriptor.GetStackParameterCount());
4140  DCHECK_EQ(2, descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount());
4141  DCHECK_EQ(machine_type(kI32), descriptor.GetParameterType(0));
4142  DCHECK_EQ(machine_type(kI32), descriptor.GetParameterType(1));
4143 
4144  Register num_pages_param_reg = descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(1);
4145  if (num_pages.gp() != num_pages_param_reg) {
4146  __ Move(num_pages_param_reg, num_pages.gp(), kI32);
4147  }
4148 
4149  // Load the constant after potentially moving the {num_pages} register to
4150  // avoid overwriting it.
4151  Register mem_index_param_reg = descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(0);
4152  __ LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister{mem_index_param_reg},
4153  WasmValue(imm.memory->index));
4154 
4155  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmMemoryGrow);
4156  DefineSafepoint();
4157  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
4158 
4159  if (kReturnRegister0 != result.gp()) {
4160  __ Move(result.gp(), kReturnRegister0, kI32);
4161  }
4162 
4163  __ bind(&done);
4164 
4165  // Note: The called runtime function will update the
4166  // {WasmEngine::had_nondeterminism_} flag if growing failed
4167  // nondeterministically. So we do not have to handle this here by looking at
4168  // the return value.
4169 
4170  if (imm.memory->is_memory64()) {
4171  LiftoffRegister result64 = result;
4172  if (kNeedI64RegPair) result64 = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpRegPair, pinned);
4173  __ emit_type_conversion(kExprI64SConvertI32, result64, result, nullptr);
4174  __ PushRegister(kI64, result64);
4175  } else {
4176  __ PushRegister(kI32, result);
4177  }
4178  }
4179 
4180  base::OwnedVector<ValueType> GetStackValueTypesForDebugging(
4181  FullDecoder* decoder) {
4182  DCHECK(for_debugging_);
4183  auto stack_value_types =
4184  base::OwnedVector<ValueType>::NewForOverwrite(decoder->stack_size());
4185 
4186  int depth = 0;
4187  for (ValueType& type : base::Reversed(stack_value_types)) {
4188  type = decoder->stack_value(++depth)->type;
4189  }
4190  return stack_value_types;
4191  }
4192 
4193  base::OwnedVector<DebugSideTable::Entry::Value>
4194  GetCurrentDebugSideTableEntries(
4195  FullDecoder* decoder,
4196  DebugSideTableBuilder::AssumeSpilling assume_spilling) {
4197  auto& stack_state = __ cache_state()->stack_state;
4198 
4199 #ifdef DEBUG
4200  // For value types, we use the cached {stack_value_types_for_debugging_}
4201  // vector (gathered in {NextInstruction}). This still includes call
4202  // arguments, which Liftoff has already popped at this point. Hence the size
4203  // of this vector can be larger than the Liftoff stack size. Just ignore
4204  // that and use the lower part only.
4205  size_t expected_value_stack_size =
4206  stack_state.size() - num_exceptions_ - __ num_locals();
4207  DCHECK_LE(expected_value_stack_size,
4208  stack_value_types_for_debugging_.size());
4209 #endif
4210 
4211  auto values =
4212  base::OwnedVector<DebugSideTable::Entry::Value>::NewForOverwrite(
4213  stack_state.size());
4214 
4215  int index = 0;
4216  ValueType* stack_value_type_ptr = stack_value_types_for_debugging_.begin();
4217  // Iterate the operand stack control block by control block, so that we can
4218  // handle the implicit exception value for try blocks.
4219  for (int j = decoder->control_depth() - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
4220  Control* control = decoder->control_at(j);
4221  Control* next_control = j > 0 ? decoder->control_at(j - 1) : nullptr;
4222  int end_index = next_control
4223  ? next_control->stack_depth + __ num_locals() +
4224  next_control->num_exceptions
4225  : __ cache_state()->stack_height();
4226  bool exception_on_stack =
4227  control->is_try_catch() || control->is_try_catchall();
4228  for (; index < end_index; ++index) {
4229  const LiftoffVarState& slot = stack_state[index];
4230  DebugSideTable::Entry::Value& value = values[index];
4231  value.module = decoder->module_;
4232  value.index = index;
4233  if (exception_on_stack) {
4234  value.type = kWasmAnyRef.AsNonNull();
4235  exception_on_stack = false;
4236  } else if (index < static_cast<int>(__ num_locals())) {
4237  value.type = decoder->local_type(index);
4238  } else {
4239  DCHECK_LT(stack_value_type_ptr,
4240  stack_value_types_for_debugging_.end());
4241  value.type = *stack_value_type_ptr++;
4242  }
4243  DCHECK(CompatibleStackSlotTypes(slot.kind(), value.type.kind()));
4244  switch (slot.loc()) {
4245  case kIntConst:
4246  value.storage = DebugSideTable::Entry::kConstant;
4247  value.i32_const = slot.i32_const();
4248  break;
4249  case kRegister:
4250  DCHECK_NE(DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill, assume_spilling);
4251  if (assume_spilling == DebugSideTableBuilder::kAllowRegisters) {
4252  value.storage = DebugSideTable::Entry::kRegister;
4253  value.reg_code = slot.reg().liftoff_code();
4254  break;
4255  }
4256  DCHECK_EQ(DebugSideTableBuilder::kAssumeSpilling, assume_spilling);
4257  [[fallthrough]];
4258  case kStack:
4259  value.storage = DebugSideTable::Entry::kStack;
4260  value.stack_offset = slot.offset();
4261  break;
4262  }
4263  }
4264  }
4265  DCHECK_EQ(values.size(), index);
4266  DCHECK_EQ(
4267  stack_value_types_for_debugging_.data() + expected_value_stack_size,
4268  stack_value_type_ptr);
4269  return values;
4270  }

4272  // Call this after emitting a runtime call that can show up in a stack trace
4273  // (e.g. because it can trap).
4274  void RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(
4275  FullDecoder* decoder,
4276  DebugSideTableBuilder::AssumeSpilling assume_spilling) {
4277  if (V8_LIKELY(!debug_sidetable_builder_)) return;
4278  debug_sidetable_builder_->NewEntry(
4279  __ pc_offset(),
4280  GetCurrentDebugSideTableEntries(decoder, assume_spilling).as_vector());
4281  }

4285  if (V8_LIKELY(!debug_sidetable_builder_)) return nullptr;
4286  return debug_sidetable_builder_->NewOOLEntry(
4287  GetCurrentDebugSideTableEntries(decoder,
4288  DebugSideTableBuilder::kAssumeSpilling)
4289  .as_vector());
4290  }

4326 
4327  void BrOnNull(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& ref_object, uint32_t depth,
4328  bool pass_null_along_branch,
4329  Value* /* result_on_fallthrough */) {
4330  // Avoid having sequences of branches do duplicate work.
4331  if (depth != decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
4332  __ PrepareForBranch(decoder->control_at(depth)->br_merge()->arity, {});
4333  }
4334 
4335  Label cont_false;
4336  LiftoffRegList pinned;
4337  LiftoffRegister ref =
4338  pinned.set(pass_null_along_branch ? __ PeekToRegister(0, pinned)
4339  : __ PopToRegister(pinned));
4340  Register null = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
4341  LoadNullValueForCompare(null, pinned, ref_object.type);
4342  {
4343  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
4344  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &cont_false, ref_object.type.kind(),
4345  ref.gp(), null, frozen);
4346  BrOrRet(decoder, depth);
4347  }
4348  __ bind(&cont_false);
4349  if (!pass_null_along_branch) {
4350  // We popped the value earlier, must push it back now.
4351  __ PushRegister(kRef, ref);
4352  }
4353  }
4354 
4355  void BrOnNonNull(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& ref_object,
4356  Value* /* result */, uint32_t depth,
4357  bool drop_null_on_fallthrough) {
4358  // Avoid having sequences of branches do duplicate work.
4359  if (depth != decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
4360  __ PrepareForBranch(decoder->control_at(depth)->br_merge()->arity, {});
4361  }
4362 
4363  Label cont_false;
4364  LiftoffRegList pinned;
4365  LiftoffRegister ref = pinned.set(__ PeekToRegister(0, pinned));
4366 
4367  Register null = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
4368  LoadNullValueForCompare(null, pinned, ref_object.type);
4369  {
4370  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
4371  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &cont_false, ref_object.type.kind(), ref.gp(),
4372  null, frozen);
4373 
4374  BrOrRet(decoder, depth);
4375  }
4376  // Drop the reference if we are not branching.
4377  if (drop_null_on_fallthrough) __ DropValues(1);
4378  __ bind(&cont_false);
4379  }

4381  template <ValueKind src_kind, ValueKind result_kind,
4382  ValueKind result_lane_kind = kVoid, typename EmitFn,
4383  typename... ExtraArgs>
4384  void EmitTerOp(EmitFn fn, LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src1,
4385  LiftoffRegister src2, LiftoffRegister src3,
4386  ExtraArgs... extra_args) {
4387  CallEmitFn(fn, dst, src1, src2, src3, extra_args...);
4388  if (V8_UNLIKELY(detect_nondeterminism_)) {
4389  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst};
4390  if (result_kind == ValueKind::kF32 || result_kind == ValueKind::kF64) {
4391  CheckNan(dst, pinned, result_kind);
4392  } else if (result_kind == ValueKind::kS128 &&
4393  (result_lane_kind == kF32 || result_lane_kind == kF64)) {
4394  CheckS128Nan(dst, LiftoffRegList{src1, src2, src3, dst},
4395  result_lane_kind);
4396  }
4397  }
4398  __ PushRegister(result_kind, dst);
4399  }
4400 
4401  template <ValueKind src_kind, ValueKind result_kind,
4402  ValueKind result_lane_kind = kVoid, typename EmitFn>
4403  void EmitTerOp(EmitFn fn) {
4404  LiftoffRegister src3 = __ PopToRegister();
4405  LiftoffRegister src2 = __ PopToRegister(LiftoffRegList{src3});
4406  LiftoffRegister src1 = __ PopToRegister(LiftoffRegList{src3, src2});
4407  static constexpr RegClass result_rc = reg_class_for(result_kind);
4408  // Reusing src1 and src2 will complicate codegen for select for some
4409  // backend, so we allow only reusing src3 (the mask), and pin src1 and src2.
4410  // Additionally, only reuse src3 if it does not alias src1/src2,
4411  // otherwise dst will also alias it src1/src2.
4412  LiftoffRegister dst =
4413  (src2 == src3 || src1 == src3)
4414  ? __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, LiftoffRegList{src1, src2})
4415  : __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {src3},
4416  LiftoffRegList{src1, src2});
4417  EmitTerOp<src_kind, result_kind, result_lane_kind, EmitFn>(fn, dst, src1,
4418  src2, src3);
4419  }
4420 
4421  void EmitRelaxedLaneSelect(int lane_width) {
4422  DCHECK(lane_width == 8 || lane_width == 32 || lane_width == 64);
4423 #if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64)
4424  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
4425 #if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32)
4426  // On ia32 xmm0 is not a cached register.
4427  LiftoffRegister mask = LiftoffRegister::from_uncached(xmm0);
4428 #else
4429  LiftoffRegister mask(xmm0);
4430 #endif
4431  __ PopToFixedRegister(mask);
4432  LiftoffRegister src2 = __ PopToModifiableRegister(LiftoffRegList{mask});
4433  LiftoffRegister src1 = __ PopToRegister(LiftoffRegList{src2, mask});
4434  EmitTerOp<kS128, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_relaxed_laneselect,
4435  src2, src1, src2, mask, lane_width);
4436  return;
4437  }
4438 #endif
4439  LiftoffRegList pinned;
4440  LiftoffRegister mask = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
4441  LiftoffRegister src2 = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
4442  LiftoffRegister src1 = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
4443  LiftoffRegister dst =
4444  __ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(kS128), {}, pinned);
4445  EmitTerOp<kS128, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_relaxed_laneselect,
4446  dst, src1, src2, mask, lane_width);
4447  }
4448 
4449  template <typename EmitFn, typename EmitFnImm>
4450  void EmitSimdShiftOp(EmitFn fn, EmitFnImm fnImm) {
4451  static constexpr RegClass result_rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
4452 
4453  VarState rhs_slot = __ cache_state()->stack_state.back();
4454  // Check if the RHS is an immediate.
4455  if (rhs_slot.is_const()) {
4456  __ cache_state()->stack_state.pop_back();
4457  int32_t imm = rhs_slot.i32_const();
4458 
4459  LiftoffRegister operand = __ PopToRegister();
4460  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {operand}, {});
4461 
4462  CallEmitFn(fnImm, dst, operand, imm);
4463  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
4464  } else {
4465  LiftoffRegister count = __ PopToRegister();
4466  LiftoffRegister operand = __ PopToRegister();
4467  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {operand}, {});
4468 
4469  CallEmitFn(fn, dst, operand, count);
4470  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
4471  }
4472  }

4474  template <ValueKind result_lane_kind>
4475  void EmitSimdFloatRoundingOpWithCFallback(
4476  bool (LiftoffAssembler::*emit_fn)(LiftoffRegister, LiftoffRegister),
4477  ExternalReference (*ext_ref)()) {
4478  static constexpr RegClass rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
4479  LiftoffRegister src = __ PopToRegister();
4480  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(rc, {src}, {});
4481  if (!(asm_.*emit_fn)(dst, src)) {
4482  // Return v128 via stack for ARM.
4483  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(&dst, kVoid, kS128,
4484  {VarState{kS128, src, 0}}, ext_ref());
4485  }
4486  if (V8_UNLIKELY(detect_nondeterminism_)) {
4487  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst};
4488  CheckS128Nan(dst, pinned, result_lane_kind);
4489  }
4490  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
4491  }

4493  template <ValueKind result_lane_kind, bool swap_lhs_rhs = false>
4494  void EmitSimdFloatBinOpWithCFallback(
4495  bool (LiftoffAssembler::*emit_fn)(LiftoffRegister, LiftoffRegister,
4496  LiftoffRegister),
4497  ExternalReference (*ext_ref)()) {
4498  static constexpr RegClass rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
4499  LiftoffRegister src2 = __ PopToRegister();
4500  LiftoffRegister src1 = __ PopToRegister(LiftoffRegList{src2});
4501  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(rc, {src1, src2}, {});
4502 
4503  if (swap_lhs_rhs) std::swap(src1, src2);
4504 
4505  if (!(asm_.*emit_fn)(dst, src1, src2)) {
4506  // Return v128 via stack for ARM.
4507  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(
4508  &dst, kVoid, kS128,
4509  {VarState{kS128, src1, 0}, VarState{kS128, src2, 0}}, ext_ref());
4510  }
4511  if (V8_UNLIKELY(detect_nondeterminism_)) {
4512  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst};
4513  CheckS128Nan(dst, pinned, result_lane_kind);
4514  }
4515  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
4516  }

4518  template <ValueKind result_lane_kind, typename EmitFn>
4519  void EmitSimdFmaOp(EmitFn emit_fn) {
4520  LiftoffRegList pinned;
4521  LiftoffRegister src3 = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
4522  LiftoffRegister src2 = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
4523  LiftoffRegister src1 = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
4524  RegClass dst_rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
4525  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(dst_rc, {});
4526  (asm_.*emit_fn)(dst, src1, src2, src3);
4527  if (V8_UNLIKELY(detect_nondeterminism_)) {
4528  LiftoffRegList pinned_inner{dst};
4529  CheckS128Nan(dst, pinned_inner, result_lane_kind);
4530  }
4531  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
4532  }

4534  template <ValueKind result_lane_kind, typename EmitFn>
4535  void EmitSimdFmaOpWithCFallback(EmitFn emit_fn,
4536  ExternalReference (*ext_ref)()) {
4537  LiftoffRegList pinned;
4538  LiftoffRegister src3 = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
4539  LiftoffRegister src2 = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
4540  LiftoffRegister src1 = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
4541  static constexpr RegClass dst_rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
4542  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(dst_rc, {});
4543  if (!(asm_.*emit_fn)(dst, src1, src2, src3)) {
4544  // Return v128 via stack for ARM.
4545  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(
4546  &dst, kVoid, kS128,
4547  {VarState{kS128, src1, 0}, VarState{kS128, src2, 0},
4548  VarState{kS128, src3, 0}},
4549  ext_ref());
4550  }
4551  if (V8_UNLIKELY(detect_nondeterminism_)) {
4552  LiftoffRegList pinned_inner{dst};
4553  CheckS128Nan(dst, pinned_inner, result_lane_kind);
4554  }
4555  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
4556  }

4558  void SimdOp(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode, const Value* /* args */,
4559  Value* /* result */) {
4560  CHECK(CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128());
4561  switch (opcode) {
4562  case wasm::kExprI8x16Swizzle:
4563  return EmitI8x16Swizzle(false);
4564  case wasm::kExprI8x16RelaxedSwizzle:
4565  return EmitI8x16Swizzle(true);
4566  case wasm::kExprI8x16Popcnt:
4567  return EmitUnOp<kS128, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_popcnt);
4568  case wasm::kExprI8x16Splat:
4569  return EmitUnOp<kI32, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_splat);
4570  case wasm::kExprI16x8Splat:
4571  return EmitUnOp<kI32, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i16x8_splat);
4572  case wasm::kExprI32x4Splat:
4573  return EmitUnOp<kI32, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_splat);
4574  case wasm::kExprI64x2Splat:
4575  return EmitUnOp<kI64, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64x2_splat);
4576  case wasm::kExprF16x8Splat: {
4577  auto emit_with_c_fallback = [this](LiftoffRegister dst,
4578  LiftoffRegister src) {
4579  if (asm_.emit_f16x8_splat(dst, src)) return;
4580  LiftoffRegister value = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {});
4581  auto conv_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_float16();
4582  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(&value, kVoid, kI16,
4583  {VarState{kF32, src, 0}}, conv_ref);
4584  __ emit_i16x8_splat(dst, value);
4585  };
4586  return EmitUnOp<kF32, kS128>(emit_with_c_fallback);
4587  }
4588  case wasm::kExprF32x4Splat:
4589  return EmitUnOp<kF32, kS128, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_splat);
4590  case wasm::kExprF64x2Splat:
4591  return EmitUnOp<kF64, kS128, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64x2_splat);
4592  case wasm::kExprI8x16Eq:
4593  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_eq);
4594  case wasm::kExprI8x16Ne:
4595  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_ne);
4596  case wasm::kExprI8x16LtS:
4597  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128, true>(
4598  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_gt_s);
4599  case wasm::kExprI8x16LtU:
4600  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128, true>(
4601  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_gt_u);
4602  case wasm::kExprI8x16GtS:
4603  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_gt_s);
4604  case wasm::kExprI8x16GtU:
4605  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_gt_u);
4606  case wasm::kExprI8x16LeS:
4607  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128, true>(
4608  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_ge_s);
4609  case wasm::kExprI8x16LeU:
4610  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128, true>(
4611  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_ge_u);
4612  case wasm::kExprI8x16GeS:
4613  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_ge_s);
4614  case wasm::kExprI8x16GeU:
4615  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_ge_u);

4620  case wasm::kExprI16x8LtS:
4621  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128, true>(
4622  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i16x8_gt_s);
4623  case wasm::kExprI16x8LtU:
4624  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128, true>(

5196  case wasm::kExprF64x2Qfms:
5197  return EmitSimdFmaOp<kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64x2_qfms);
5198  case wasm::kExprI16x8RelaxedLaneSelect:
5199  case wasm::kExprI8x16RelaxedLaneSelect:
5200  // There is no special hardware instruction for 16-bit wide lanes on
5201  // any of our platforms, so fall back to bytewise selection for i16x8.
5202  return EmitRelaxedLaneSelect(8);
5203  case wasm::kExprI32x4RelaxedLaneSelect:
5204  return EmitRelaxedLaneSelect(32);
5205  case wasm::kExprI64x2RelaxedLaneSelect:

5207  case wasm::kExprF32x4RelaxedMin:
