5209  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_relaxed_min);
5210  case wasm::kExprF32x4RelaxedMax:
5211  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128, false, kF32>(
5212  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_relaxed_max);
5213  case wasm::kExprF64x2RelaxedMin:
5214  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128, false, kF64>(
5215  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64x2_relaxed_min);
5216  case wasm::kExprF64x2RelaxedMax:
5217  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128, false, kF64>(
5218  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64x2_relaxed_max);
5219  case wasm::kExprI16x8RelaxedQ15MulRS:
5220  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128>(
5221  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i16x8_relaxed_q15mulr_s);
5222  case wasm::kExprI32x4RelaxedTruncF32x4S:
5223  return EmitUnOp<kS128, kS128>(
5224  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_relaxed_trunc_f32x4_s);
5225  case wasm::kExprI32x4RelaxedTruncF32x4U:
5226  return EmitUnOp<kS128, kS128>(
5227  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_relaxed_trunc_f32x4_u);
5228  case wasm::kExprI32x4RelaxedTruncF64x2SZero:
5229  return EmitUnOp<kS128, kS128>(
5230  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_relaxed_trunc_f64x2_s_zero);
5231  case wasm::kExprI32x4RelaxedTruncF64x2UZero:
5232  return EmitUnOp<kS128, kS128>(
5233  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_relaxed_trunc_f64x2_u_zero);
5234  case wasm::kExprI16x8DotI8x16I7x16S:
5235  return EmitBinOp<kS128, kS128>(
5236  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i16x8_dot_i8x16_i7x16_s);
5237  case wasm::kExprI32x4DotI8x16I7x16AddS: {
5238  // There is no helper for an instruction with 3 SIMD operands
5239  // and we do not expect to add any more, so inlining it here.
5240  static constexpr RegClass res_rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
5241  LiftoffRegList pinned;
5242  LiftoffRegister acc = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5243  LiftoffRegister rhs = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5244  LiftoffRegister lhs = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5245 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64 || V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
5246  // x86 platforms save a move when dst == acc, so prefer that.
5247  LiftoffRegister dst =
5248  __ GetUnusedRegister(res_rc, {acc}, LiftoffRegList{lhs, rhs});
5249 #else
5250  // On other platforms, for simplicity, we ensure that none of the
5251  // registers alias. (If we cared, it would probably be feasible to
5252  // allow {dst} to alias with {lhs} or {rhs}, but that'd be brittle.)
5253  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(res_rc, pinned);
5254 #endif
5255 
5256  __ emit_i32x4_dot_i8x16_i7x16_add_s(dst, lhs, rhs, acc);
5257  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
5258  return;
5259  }
5260  default:
5261  UNREACHABLE();
5262  }
5263  }
5264 
5265  template <ValueKind src_kind, ValueKind result_kind, typename EmitFn>
5266  void EmitSimdExtractLaneOp(EmitFn fn, const SimdLaneImmediate& imm) {
5267  static constexpr RegClass src_rc = reg_class_for(src_kind);
5268  static constexpr RegClass result_rc = reg_class_for(result_kind);
5269  LiftoffRegister lhs = __ PopToRegister();
5270  LiftoffRegister dst = src_rc == result_rc
5271  ? __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {lhs}, {})
5272  : __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {});
5273  fn(dst, lhs, imm.lane);
5274  __ PushRegister(result_kind, dst);
5275  }
5276 
5277  template <ValueKind src2_kind, typename EmitFn>
5278  void EmitSimdReplaceLaneOp(EmitFn fn, const SimdLaneImmediate& imm) {
5279  static constexpr RegClass src1_rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
5280  static constexpr RegClass src2_rc = reg_class_for(src2_kind);
5281  static constexpr RegClass result_rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
5282  // On backends which need fp pair, src1_rc and result_rc end up being
5283  // kFpRegPair, which is != kFpReg, but we still want to pin src2 when it is
5284  // kFpReg, since it can overlap with those pairs.
5285  static constexpr bool pin_src2 = kNeedS128RegPair && src2_rc == kFpReg;
5286 
5287  // Does not work for arm
5288  LiftoffRegister src2 = __ PopToRegister();
5289  LiftoffRegister src1 = (src1_rc == src2_rc || pin_src2)
5290  ? __ PopToRegister(LiftoffRegList{src2})
5291  : __
5292  PopToRegister();
5293  LiftoffRegister dst =
5294  (src2_rc == result_rc || pin_src2)
5295  ? __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {src1}, LiftoffRegList{src2})
5296  : __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {src1}, {});
5297  fn(dst, src1, src2, imm.lane);
5298  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
5299  }
5300 
5301  void SimdLaneOp(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode,
5302  const SimdLaneImmediate& imm,
5303  base::Vector<const Value> inputs, Value* result) {
5304  CHECK(CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128());
5305  switch (opcode) {
5306 #define CASE_SIMD_EXTRACT_LANE_OP(opcode, kind, fn) \
5307  case wasm::kExpr##opcode: \
5308  EmitSimdExtractLaneOp<kS128, k##kind>( \
5309  [this](LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs, \
5310  uint8_t imm_lane_idx) { \
5311  __ emit_##fn(dst, lhs, imm_lane_idx); \
5312  }, \
5313  imm); \
5314  break;
5315  CASE_SIMD_EXTRACT_LANE_OP(I8x16ExtractLaneS, I32, i8x16_extract_lane_s)
5316  CASE_SIMD_EXTRACT_LANE_OP(I8x16ExtractLaneU, I32, i8x16_extract_lane_u)
5317  CASE_SIMD_EXTRACT_LANE_OP(I16x8ExtractLaneS, I32, i16x8_extract_lane_s)
5318  CASE_SIMD_EXTRACT_LANE_OP(I16x8ExtractLaneU, I32, i16x8_extract_lane_u)
5319  CASE_SIMD_EXTRACT_LANE_OP(I32x4ExtractLane, I32, i32x4_extract_lane)
5320  CASE_SIMD_EXTRACT_LANE_OP(I64x2ExtractLane, I64, i64x2_extract_lane)
5321  CASE_SIMD_EXTRACT_LANE_OP(F32x4ExtractLane, F32, f32x4_extract_lane)
5322  CASE_SIMD_EXTRACT_LANE_OP(F64x2ExtractLane, F64, f64x2_extract_lane)
5323 #undef CASE_SIMD_EXTRACT_LANE_OP
5324  case wasm::kExprF16x8ExtractLane:
5325  EmitSimdExtractLaneOp<kS128, kF32>(
5326  [this](LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
5327  uint8_t imm_lane_idx) {
5328  if (asm_.emit_f16x8_extract_lane(dst, lhs, imm_lane_idx)) return;
5329  LiftoffRegister value = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {});
5330  __ emit_i16x8_extract_lane_u(value, lhs, imm_lane_idx);
5331  auto conv_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_float16_to_float32();
5332  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(
5333  &dst, kVoid, kF32, {VarState{kI16, value, 0}}, conv_ref);
5334  },
5335  imm);
5336  break;
5337 #define CASE_SIMD_REPLACE_LANE_OP(opcode, kind, fn) \
5338  case wasm::kExpr##opcode: \
5339  EmitSimdReplaceLaneOp<k##kind>( \
5340  [this](LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src1, \
5341  LiftoffRegister src2, uint8_t imm_lane_idx) { \
5342  __ emit_##fn(dst, src1, src2, imm_lane_idx); \
5343  }, \
5344  imm); \
5345  break;
5346  CASE_SIMD_REPLACE_LANE_OP(I8x16ReplaceLane, I32, i8x16_replace_lane)
5347  CASE_SIMD_REPLACE_LANE_OP(I16x8ReplaceLane, I32, i16x8_replace_lane)
5348  CASE_SIMD_REPLACE_LANE_OP(I32x4ReplaceLane, I32, i32x4_replace_lane)
5349  CASE_SIMD_REPLACE_LANE_OP(I64x2ReplaceLane, I64, i64x2_replace_lane)
5350  CASE_SIMD_REPLACE_LANE_OP(F32x4ReplaceLane, F32, f32x4_replace_lane)
5351  CASE_SIMD_REPLACE_LANE_OP(F64x2ReplaceLane, F64, f64x2_replace_lane)
5352 #undef CASE_SIMD_REPLACE_LANE_OP
5353  case wasm::kExprF16x8ReplaceLane: {
5354  EmitSimdReplaceLaneOp<kI32>(
5355  [this](LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src1,
5356  LiftoffRegister src2, uint8_t imm_lane_idx) {
5357  if (asm_.emit_f16x8_replace_lane(dst, src1, src2, imm_lane_idx)) {
5358  return;
5359  }
5360  __ PushRegister(kS128, src1);
5361  LiftoffRegister value = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {});
5362  auto conv_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_float16();
5363  GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer(&value, kVoid, kI16,
5364  {VarState{kF32, src2, 0}}, conv_ref);
5365  __ PopToFixedRegister(src1);
5366  __ emit_i16x8_replace_lane(dst, src1, value, imm_lane_idx);
5367  },
5368  imm);
5369  break;
5370  }
5371  default:
5372  UNREACHABLE();
5373  }
5374  }
5375 
5376  void S128Const(FullDecoder* decoder, const Simd128Immediate& imm,
5377  Value* result) {
5378  CHECK(CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128());
5379  constexpr RegClass result_rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
5380  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {});
5381  bool all_zeroes = std::all_of(std::begin(imm.value), std::end(imm.value),
5382  [](uint8_t v) { return v == 0; });
5383  bool all_ones = std::all_of(std::begin(imm.value), std::end(imm.value),
5384  [](uint8_t v) { return v == 0xff; });
5385  if (all_zeroes) {
5386  __ LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_xor(dst, dst, dst);
5387  } else if (all_ones) {
5388  // Any SIMD eq will work, i32x4 is efficient on all archs.
5389  __ LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_eq(dst, dst, dst);
5390  } else {
5391  __ LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_const(dst, imm.value);
5392  }
5393  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
5394  }
5395 
5396  void Simd8x16ShuffleOp(FullDecoder* decoder, const Simd128Immediate& imm,
5397  const Value& input0, const Value& input1,
5398  Value* result) {
5399  CHECK(CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128());
5400  static constexpr RegClass result_rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
5401  LiftoffRegList pinned;
5402  LiftoffRegister rhs = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5403  LiftoffRegister lhs = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5404  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(result_rc, {lhs, rhs}, {});
5405 
5406  uint8_t shuffle[kSimd128Size];
5407  memcpy(shuffle, imm.value, sizeof(shuffle));
5408  bool is_swizzle;
5409  bool needs_swap;
5410  wasm::SimdShuffle::CanonicalizeShuffle(lhs == rhs, shuffle, &needs_swap,
5411  &is_swizzle);
5412  if (needs_swap) {
5413  std::swap(lhs, rhs);
5414  }
5415  __ LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_shuffle(dst, lhs, rhs, shuffle, is_swizzle);
5416  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
5417  }
5418 
5419  void ToSmi(Register reg) {
5420  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL || kSystemPointerSize == 4) {
5421  __ emit_i32_shli(reg, reg, kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize);
5422  } else {
5423  __ emit_i64_shli(LiftoffRegister{reg}, LiftoffRegister{reg},
5424  kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize);
5425  }
5426  }
5427 
5428  void Store32BitExceptionValue(Register values_array, int* index_in_array,
5429  Register value, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
5430  Register tmp_reg = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
5431  // Get the lower half word into tmp_reg and extend to a Smi.
5432  --*index_in_array;
5433  __ emit_i32_andi(tmp_reg, value, 0xffff);
5434  ToSmi(tmp_reg);
5435  __ StoreTaggedPointer(
5436  values_array, no_reg,
5437  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(*index_in_array),
5438  tmp_reg, pinned, nullptr, LiftoffAssembler::kSkipWriteBarrier);
5439 
5440  // Get the upper half word into tmp_reg and extend to a Smi.
5441  --*index_in_array;
5442  __ emit_i32_shri(tmp_reg, value, 16);
5443  ToSmi(tmp_reg);
5444  __ StoreTaggedPointer(
5445  values_array, no_reg,
5446  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(*index_in_array),
5447  tmp_reg, pinned, nullptr, LiftoffAssembler::kSkipWriteBarrier);
5448  }
5449 
5450  void Store64BitExceptionValue(Register values_array, int* index_in_array,
5451  LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
5452  if (kNeedI64RegPair) {
5453  Store32BitExceptionValue(values_array, index_in_array, value.low_gp(),
5454  pinned);
5455  Store32BitExceptionValue(values_array, index_in_array, value.high_gp(),
5456  pinned);
5457  } else {
5458  Store32BitExceptionValue(values_array, index_in_array, value.gp(),
5459  pinned);
5460  __ emit_i64_shri(value, value, 32);
5461  Store32BitExceptionValue(values_array, index_in_array, value.gp(),
5462  pinned);
5463  }
5464  }
5465 
5466  void Load16BitExceptionValue(LiftoffRegister dst,
5467  LiftoffRegister values_array, uint32_t* index,
5468  LiftoffRegList pinned) {
5469  __ LoadSmiAsInt32(
5470  dst, values_array.gp(),
5471  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(*index));
5472  (*index)++;
5473  }
5474 
5475  void Load32BitExceptionValue(Register dst, LiftoffRegister values_array,
5476  uint32_t* index, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
5477  LiftoffRegister upper = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
5478  Load16BitExceptionValue(upper, values_array, index, pinned);
5479  __ emit_i32_shli(upper.gp(), upper.gp(), 16);
5480  Load16BitExceptionValue(LiftoffRegister(dst), values_array, index, pinned);
5481  __ emit_i32_or(dst, upper.gp(), dst);
5482  }
5483 
5484  void Load64BitExceptionValue(LiftoffRegister dst,
5485  LiftoffRegister values_array, uint32_t* index,
5486  LiftoffRegList pinned) {
5487  if (kNeedI64RegPair) {
5488  Load32BitExceptionValue(dst.high_gp(), values_array, index, pinned);
5489  Load32BitExceptionValue(dst.low_gp(), values_array, index, pinned);
5490  } else {
5491  Load16BitExceptionValue(dst, values_array, index, pinned);
5492  __ emit_i64_shli(dst, dst, 48);
5493  LiftoffRegister tmp_reg =
5494  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
5495  Load16BitExceptionValue(tmp_reg, values_array, index, pinned);
5496  __ emit_i64_shli(tmp_reg, tmp_reg, 32);
5497  __ emit_i64_or(dst, tmp_reg, dst);
5498  Load16BitExceptionValue(tmp_reg, values_array, index, pinned);
5499  __ emit_i64_shli(tmp_reg, tmp_reg, 16);
5500  __ emit_i64_or(dst, tmp_reg, dst);
5501  Load16BitExceptionValue(tmp_reg, values_array, index, pinned);
5502  __ emit_i64_or(dst, tmp_reg, dst);
5503  }
5504  }
5505 
5506  void StoreExceptionValue(ValueType type, Register values_array,
5507  int* index_in_array, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
5508  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5509  switch (type.kind()) {
5510  case kI32:
5511  Store32BitExceptionValue(values_array, index_in_array, value.gp(),
5512  pinned);
5513  break;
5514  case kF32: {
5515  LiftoffRegister gp_reg =
5516  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
5517  __ emit_type_conversion(kExprI32ReinterpretF32, gp_reg, value, nullptr);
5518  Store32BitExceptionValue(values_array, index_in_array, gp_reg.gp(),
5519  pinned);
5520  break;
5521  }
5522  case kI64:
5523  Store64BitExceptionValue(values_array, index_in_array, value, pinned);
5524  break;
5525  case kF64: {
5526  LiftoffRegister tmp_reg =
5527  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(kI64), pinned));
5528  __ emit_type_conversion(kExprI64ReinterpretF64, tmp_reg, value,
5529  nullptr);
5530  Store64BitExceptionValue(values_array, index_in_array, tmp_reg, pinned);
5531  break;
5532  }
5533  case kS128: {
5534  LiftoffRegister tmp_reg =
5535  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
5536  for (int i : {3, 2, 1, 0}) {
5537  __ emit_i32x4_extract_lane(tmp_reg, value, i);
5538  Store32BitExceptionValue(values_array, index_in_array, tmp_reg.gp(),
5539  pinned);
5540  }
5541  break;
5542  }
5543  case wasm::kRef:
5544  case wasm::kRefNull: {
5545  --(*index_in_array);
5546  __ StoreTaggedPointer(
5547  values_array, no_reg,
5548  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(
5549  *index_in_array),
5550  value.gp(), pinned);
5551  break;
5552  }
5553  case wasm::kI8:
5554  case wasm::kI16:
5555  case wasm::kF16:
5556  case wasm::kVoid:
5557  case wasm::kTop:
5558  case wasm::kBottom:
5559  UNREACHABLE();
5560  }
5561  }
5562 
5563  void LoadExceptionValue(ValueKind kind, LiftoffRegister values_array,
5564  uint32_t* index, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
5565  RegClass rc = reg_class_for(kind);
5566  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(rc, pinned));
5567  switch (kind) {
5568  case kI32:
5569  Load32BitExceptionValue(value.gp(), values_array, index, pinned);
5570  break;
5571  case kF32: {
5572  LiftoffRegister tmp_reg =
5573  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
5574  Load32BitExceptionValue(tmp_reg.gp(), values_array, index, pinned);
5575  __ emit_type_conversion(kExprF32ReinterpretI32, value, tmp_reg,
5576  nullptr);
5577  break;
5578  }
5579  case kI64:
5580  Load64BitExceptionValue(value, values_array, index, pinned);
5581  break;
5582  case kF64: {
5583  RegClass rc_i64 = reg_class_for(kI64);
5584  LiftoffRegister tmp_reg =
5585  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(rc_i64, pinned));
5586  Load64BitExceptionValue(tmp_reg, values_array, index, pinned);
5587  __ emit_type_conversion(kExprF64ReinterpretI64, value, tmp_reg,
5588  nullptr);
5589  break;
5590  }
5591  case kS128: {
5592  LiftoffRegister tmp_reg =
5593  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
5594  Load32BitExceptionValue(tmp_reg.gp(), values_array, index, pinned);
5595  __ emit_i32x4_splat(value, tmp_reg);
5596  for (int lane : {1, 2, 3}) {
5597  Load32BitExceptionValue(tmp_reg.gp(), values_array, index, pinned);
5598  __ emit_i32x4_replace_lane(value, value, tmp_reg, lane);
5599  }
5600  break;
5601  }
5602  case wasm::kRef:
5603  case wasm::kRefNull: {
5604  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
5605  value.gp(), values_array.gp(), no_reg,
5606  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(*index));
5607  (*index)++;
5608  break;
5609  }
5610  case wasm::kI8:
5611  case wasm::kI16:
5612  case wasm::kF16:
5613  case wasm::kVoid:
5614  case wasm::kTop:
5615  case wasm::kBottom:
5616  UNREACHABLE();
5617  }
5618  __ PushRegister(kind, value);
5619  }
5620 
5621  void GetExceptionValues(FullDecoder* decoder, const VarState& exception_var,
5622  const WasmTag* tag) {
5623  LiftoffRegList pinned;
5624  CODE_COMMENT("get exception values");
5625  LiftoffRegister values_array = GetExceptionProperty(
5626  exception_var, RootIndex::kwasm_exception_values_symbol);
5627  pinned.set(values_array);
5628  uint32_t index = 0;
5629  const WasmTagSig* sig = tag->sig;
5630  for (ValueType param : sig->parameters()) {
5631  LoadExceptionValue(param.kind(), values_array, &index, pinned);
5632  }
5633  DCHECK_EQ(index, WasmExceptionPackage::GetEncodedSize(tag));
5634  }
5635 
5636  void EmitLandingPad(FullDecoder* decoder, int handler_offset) {
5637  if (decoder->current_catch() == -1) return;
5638  MovableLabel handler{zone_};
5639 
5640  // If we return from the throwing code normally, just skip over the handler.
5641  Label skip_handler;
5642  __ emit_jump(&skip_handler);
5643 
5644  // Handler: merge into the catch state, and jump to the catch body.
5645  CODE_COMMENT("-- landing pad --");
5646  __ bind(handler.get());
5647  __ ExceptionHandler();
5648  __ PushException();
5649  handlers_.push_back({std::move(handler), handler_offset});
5650  Control* current_try =
5651  decoder->control_at(decoder->control_depth_of_current_catch());
5652  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_try->try_info);
5653  if (current_try->try_info->catch_reached) {
5654  __ MergeStackWith(current_try->try_info->catch_state, 1,
5655  LiftoffAssembler::kForwardJump);
5656  } else {
5657  current_try->try_info->catch_state = __ MergeIntoNewState(
5658  __ num_locals(), 1,
5659  current_try->stack_depth + current_try->num_exceptions);
5660  current_try->try_info->catch_reached = true;
5661  }
5662  __ emit_jump(&current_try->try_info->catch_label);
5663 
5664  __ bind(&skip_handler);
5665  // Drop the exception.
5666  __ DropValues(1);
5667  }
5668 
5669  void Throw(FullDecoder* decoder, const TagIndexImmediate& imm,
5670  const Value* /* args */) {
5671  LiftoffRegList pinned;
5672 
5673  // Load the encoded size in a register for the builtin call.
5674  int encoded_size = WasmExceptionPackage::GetEncodedSize(imm.tag);
5675  LiftoffRegister encoded_size_reg =
5676  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
5677  __ LoadConstant(encoded_size_reg, WasmValue::ForUintPtr(encoded_size));
5678 
5679  // Call the WasmAllocateFixedArray builtin to create the values array.
5680  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmAllocateFixedArray,
5681  MakeSig::Returns(kIntPtrKind).Params(kIntPtrKind),
5682  {VarState{kIntPtrKind, LiftoffRegister{encoded_size_reg}, 0}},
5683  decoder->position());
5684  MaybeOSR();
5685 
5686  // The FixedArray for the exception values is now in the first gp return
5687  // register.
5688  LiftoffRegister values_array{kReturnRegister0};
5689  pinned.set(values_array);
5690 
5691  // Now store the exception values in the FixedArray. Do this from last to
5692  // first value, such that we can just pop them from the value stack.
5693  CODE_COMMENT("fill values array");
5694  int index = encoded_size;
5695  auto* sig = imm.tag->sig;
5696  for (size_t param_idx = sig->parameter_count(); param_idx > 0;
5697  --param_idx) {
5698  ValueType type = sig->GetParam(param_idx - 1);
5699  StoreExceptionValue(type, values_array.gp(), &index, pinned);
5700  }
5701  DCHECK_EQ(0, index);
5702 
5703  // Load the exception tag.
5704  CODE_COMMENT("load exception tag");
5705  LiftoffRegister exception_tag =
5706  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
5707  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(exception_tag.gp(), TagsTable, pinned);
5708  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
5709  exception_tag.gp(), exception_tag.gp(), no_reg,
5710  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(imm.index));
5711 
5712  // Finally, call WasmThrow.
5713  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmThrow, MakeSig::Params(kIntPtrKind, kIntPtrKind),
5714  {VarState{kIntPtrKind, exception_tag, 0},
5715  VarState{kIntPtrKind, values_array, 0}},
5716  decoder->position());
5717 
5718  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
5719 
5720  int pc_offset = __ pc_offset();
5721  MaybeOSR();
5722  EmitLandingPad(decoder, pc_offset);
5723  }
5724 
5725  void AtomicStoreMem(FullDecoder* decoder, StoreType type,
5726  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm) {
5727  LiftoffRegList pinned;
5728  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister());
5729  bool i64_offset = imm.memory->is_memory64();
5730  auto& index_slot = __ cache_state() -> stack_state.back();
5731  DCHECK_EQ(i64_offset ? kI64 : kI32, index_slot.kind());
5732  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
5733  LiftoffRegList outer_pinned;
5734  Register index = no_reg;
5735 
5736  if (IndexStaticallyInBoundsAndAligned(imm.memory, index_slot, type.size(),
5737  &offset)) {
5738  __ cache_state() -> stack_state.pop_back(); // Pop index.
5739  CODE_COMMENT("atomic store (constant offset)");
5740  } else {
5741  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PopToRegister(pinned);
5742  index =
5743  BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, type.size(), imm.offset,
5744  full_index, pinned, kDoForceCheck, kCheckAlignment);
5745  pinned.set(index);
5746  CODE_COMMENT("atomic store");
5747  }
5748  Register addr = pinned.set(GetMemoryStart(imm.mem_index, pinned));
5749  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory) && index != no_reg) {
5750  outer_pinned.set(index);
5751  }
5752  __ AtomicStore(addr, index, offset, value, type, outer_pinned, i64_offset);
5753  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory)) {
5754  // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
5755  CHECK_EQ(0, imm.memory->index);
5756  TraceMemoryOperation(true, type.mem_rep(), index, offset,
5757  decoder->position());
5758  }
5759  }
5760 
5761  void AtomicLoadMem(FullDecoder* decoder, LoadType type,
5762  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm) {
5763  ValueKind kind = type.value_type().kind();
5764  bool i64_offset = imm.memory->is_memory64();
5765  auto& index_slot = __ cache_state() -> stack_state.back();
5766  DCHECK_EQ(i64_offset ? kI64 : kI32, index_slot.kind());
5767  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
5768  Register index = no_reg;
5769  LiftoffRegList pinned;
5770 
5771  if (IndexStaticallyInBoundsAndAligned(imm.memory, index_slot, type.size(),
5772  &offset)) {
5773  __ cache_state() -> stack_state.pop_back(); // Pop index.
5774  CODE_COMMENT("atomic load (constant offset)");
5775  } else {
5776  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PopToRegister();
5777  index = BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, type.size(), imm.offset,
5778  full_index, {}, kDoForceCheck, kCheckAlignment);
5779  pinned.set(index);
5780  CODE_COMMENT("atomic load");
5781  }
5782 
5783  Register addr = pinned.set(GetMemoryStart(imm.mem_index, pinned));
5784  RegClass rc = reg_class_for(kind);
5785  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(rc, pinned));
5786  __ AtomicLoad(value, addr, index, offset, type, pinned, i64_offset);
5787  __ PushRegister(kind, value);
5788 
5789  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory)) {
5790  // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
5791  CHECK_EQ(0, imm.memory->index);
5792  TraceMemoryOperation(false, type.mem_type().representation(), index,
5793  offset, decoder->position());
5794  }
5795  }
5796 
5797  void AtomicBinop(FullDecoder* decoder, StoreType type,
5798  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm,
5799  void (LiftoffAssembler::*emit_fn)(Register, Register,
5800  uintptr_t, LiftoffRegister,
5801  LiftoffRegister, StoreType,
5802  bool)) {
5803  ValueKind result_kind = type.value_type().kind();
5804  LiftoffRegList pinned;
5805  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister());
5806 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
5807  // We have to reuse the value register as the result register so that we
5808  // don't run out of registers on ia32. For this we use the value register as
5809  // the result register if it has no other uses. Otherwise we allocate a new
5810  // register and let go of the value register to get spilled.
5811  LiftoffRegister result = value;
5812  if (__ cache_state()->is_used(value)) {
5813  result = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(value.reg_class(), pinned));
5814  __ Move(result, value, result_kind);
5815  pinned.clear(value);
5816  value = result;
5817  }
5818 #else
5819  LiftoffRegister result =
5820  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(value.reg_class(), pinned));
5821 #endif
5822  auto& index_slot = __ cache_state() -> stack_state.back();
5823  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
5824  bool i64_offset = imm.memory->is_memory64();
5825  DCHECK_EQ(i64_offset ? kI64 : kI32, index_slot.kind());
5826  Register index = no_reg;
5827 
5828  if (IndexStaticallyInBoundsAndAligned(imm.memory, index_slot, type.size(),
5829  &offset)) {
5830  __ cache_state() -> stack_state.pop_back(); // Pop index.
5831  CODE_COMMENT("atomic binop (constant offset)");
5832  } else {
5833  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PopToRegister(pinned);
5834  index =
5835  BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, type.size(), imm.offset,
5836  full_index, pinned, kDoForceCheck, kCheckAlignment);
5837 
5838  pinned.set(index);
5839  CODE_COMMENT("atomic binop");
5840  }
5841 
5842  Register addr = pinned.set(GetMemoryStart(imm.mem_index, pinned));
5843  (asm_.*emit_fn)(addr, index, offset, value, result, type, i64_offset);
5844  __ PushRegister(result_kind, result);
5845  }
5846 
5847  void AtomicCompareExchange(FullDecoder* decoder, StoreType type,
5848  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm) {
5849 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
5850  // On ia32 we don't have enough registers to first pop all the values off
5851  // the stack and then start with the code generation. Instead we do the
5852  // complete address calculation first, so that the address only needs a
5853  // single register. Afterwards we load all remaining values into the
5854  // other registers.
5855  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PeekToRegister(2, {});
5856 
5857  Register index =
5858  BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, type.size(), imm.offset, full_index,
5859  {}, kDoForceCheck, kCheckAlignment);
5860  LiftoffRegList pinned{index};
5861 
5862  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
5863  Register addr = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
5864  if (imm.memory->index == 0) {
5865  LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(addr, Memory0Start, kSystemPointerSize, pinned);
5866  } else {
5867  LOAD_PROTECTED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(addr, MemoryBasesAndSizes, pinned);
5868  int buffer_offset =
5869  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(ByteArray)) +
5870  kSystemPointerSize * imm.memory->index * 2;
5871  __ LoadFullPointer(addr, addr, buffer_offset);
5872  }
5873  __ emit_i32_add(addr, addr, index);
5874  pinned.clear(LiftoffRegister(index));
5875  LiftoffRegister new_value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5876  LiftoffRegister expected = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5877 
5878  // Pop the index from the stack.
5879  bool i64_offset = imm.memory->is_memory64();
5880  DCHECK_EQ(i64_offset ? kI64 : kI32,
5881  __ cache_state()->stack_state.back().kind());
5882  __ DropValues(1);
5883 
5884  LiftoffRegister result = expected;
5885  if (__ cache_state()->is_used(result)) __ SpillRegister(result);
5886 
5887  // We already added the index to addr, so we can just pass no_reg to the
5888  // assembler now.
5889  __ AtomicCompareExchange(addr, no_reg, offset, expected, new_value, result,
5890  type, i64_offset);
5891  __ PushRegister(type.value_type().kind(), result);
5892  return;
5893 #else
5894  ValueKind result_kind = type.value_type().kind();
5895  LiftoffRegList pinned;
5896  LiftoffRegister new_value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5897  LiftoffRegister expected = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5898  LiftoffRegister result =
5899  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(result_kind), pinned));
5900 
5901  auto& index_slot = __ cache_state() -> stack_state.back();
5902  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
5903  bool i64_offset = imm.memory->is_memory64();
5904  DCHECK_EQ(i64_offset ? kI64 : kI32, index_slot.kind());
5905  Register index = no_reg;
5906 
5907  if (IndexStaticallyInBoundsAndAligned(imm.memory, index_slot, type.size(),
5908  &offset)) {
5909  __ cache_state() -> stack_state.pop_back(); // Pop index.
5910  CODE_COMMENT("atomic cmpxchg (constant offset)");
5911  } else {
5912  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PopToRegister(pinned);
5913  index =
5914  BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, type.size(), imm.offset,
5915  full_index, pinned, kDoForceCheck, kCheckAlignment);
5916  pinned.set(index);
5917  CODE_COMMENT("atomic cmpxchg");
5918  }
5919 
5920  Register addr = pinned.set(GetMemoryStart(imm.mem_index, pinned));
5921  __ AtomicCompareExchange(addr, index, offset, expected, new_value, result,
5922  type, i64_offset);
5923  __ PushRegister(result_kind, result);
5924 #endif
5925  }
5926 
5927  void CallBuiltin(Builtin builtin, const ValueKindSig& sig,
5928  std::initializer_list<VarState> params, int position) {
5929  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT(
5930  (std::string{"Call builtin: "} + Builtins::name(builtin)));
5931  auto interface_descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin);
5932  auto* call_descriptor = compiler::Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
5933  zone_, // zone
5934  interface_descriptor, // descriptor
5935  interface_descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(), // stack parameter count
5936  compiler::CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, // flags
5937  compiler::Operator::kNoProperties, // properties
5938  StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub); // stub call mode
5939 
5940  __ PrepareBuiltinCall(&sig, call_descriptor, params);
5941  if (position != kNoSourcePosition) {
5942  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
5943  __ pc_offset(), SourcePosition(position), true);
5944  }
5945  __ CallBuiltin(builtin);
5946  DefineSafepoint();
5947  }
5948 
5949  void AtomicWait(FullDecoder* decoder, ValueKind kind,
5950  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm) {
5951  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
5952  ValueKind index_kind;
5953  {
5954  LiftoffRegList pinned;
5955  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PeekToRegister(2, pinned);
5956 
5957  Register index_reg =
5958  BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, value_kind_size(kind), imm.offset,
5959  full_index, pinned, kDoForceCheck, kCheckAlignment);
5960  pinned.set(index_reg);
5961 
5962  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
5963  Register index_plus_offset = index_reg;
5964 
5965  if (__ cache_state()->is_used(LiftoffRegister(index_reg))) {
5966  index_plus_offset =
5967  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
5968  __ Move(index_plus_offset, index_reg, kIntPtrKind);
5969  }
5970  if (offset) {
5971  __ emit_ptrsize_addi(index_plus_offset, index_plus_offset, offset);
5972  }
5973 
5974  VarState& index = __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-3];
5975 
5976  // We replace the index on the value stack with the `index_plus_offset`
5977  // calculated above. Thereby the BigInt allocation below does not
5978  // overwrite the calculated value by accident.
5979  // The kind of `index_plus_offset has to be the same or smaller than the
5980  // original kind of `index`. The kind of index is kI32 for memory32, and
5981  // kI64 for memory64. On 64-bit platforms we can use in both cases the
5982  // kind of `index` also for `index_plus_offset`. Note that
5983  // `index_plus_offset` fits into a kI32 because we do a bounds check
5984  // first.
5985  // On 32-bit platforms, we have to use an kI32 also for memory64, because
5986  // `index_plus_offset` does not exist in a register pair.
5987  __ cache_state()->inc_used(LiftoffRegister(index_plus_offset));
5988  if (index.is_reg()) __ cache_state()->dec_used(index.reg());
5989  index_kind = index.kind() == kI32 ? kI32 : kIntPtrKind;
5990 
5991  index = VarState{index_kind, LiftoffRegister{index_plus_offset},
5992  index.offset()};
5993  }
5994  {
5995  // Convert the top value of the stack (the timeout) from I64 to a BigInt,
5996  // which we can then pass to the atomic.wait builtin.
5997  VarState i64_timeout = __ cache_state()->stack_state.back();
5998  CallBuiltin(
5999  kNeedI64RegPair ? Builtin::kI32PairToBigInt : Builtin::kI64ToBigInt,
6000  MakeSig::Returns(kRef).Params(kI64), {i64_timeout},
6001  decoder->position());
6002  __ DropValues(1);
6003  // We put the result on the value stack so that it gets preserved across
6004  // a potential GC that may get triggered by the BigInt allocation below.
6005  __ PushRegister(kRef, LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0));
6006  }
6007 
6008  Register expected = no_reg;
6009  if (kind == kI32) {
6010  expected = __ PeekToRegister(1, {}).gp();
6011  } else {
6012  VarState i64_expected = __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-2];
6013  CallBuiltin(
6014  kNeedI64RegPair ? Builtin::kI32PairToBigInt : Builtin::kI64ToBigInt,
6015  MakeSig::Returns(kRef).Params(kI64), {i64_expected},
6016  decoder->position());
6017  expected = kReturnRegister0;
6018  }
6019  ValueKind expected_kind = kind == kI32 ? kI32 : kRef;
6020 
6021  VarState timeout = __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1];
6022  VarState index = __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-3];
6023 
6024  auto target = kind == kI32 ? Builtin::kWasmI32AtomicWait
6025  : Builtin::kWasmI64AtomicWait;
6026 
6027  // The type of {index} can either by i32 or intptr, depending on whether
6028  // memory32 or memory64 is used. This is okay because both values get passed
6029  // by register.
6030  CallBuiltin(target, MakeSig::Params(kI32, index_kind, expected_kind, kRef),
6031  {{kI32, static_cast<int32_t>(imm.memory->index), 0},
6032  index,
6033  {expected_kind, LiftoffRegister{expected}, 0},
6034  timeout},
6035  decoder->position());
6036  // Pop parameters from the value stack.
6037  __ DropValues(3);
6038 
6039  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
6040 
6041  __ PushRegister(kI32, LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0));
6042  }
6043 
6044  void AtomicNotify(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm) {
6045  LiftoffRegList pinned;
6046  LiftoffRegister num_waiters_to_wake = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6047  LiftoffRegister full_index = __ PopToRegister(pinned);
6048  Register index_reg =
6049  BoundsCheckMem(decoder, imm.memory, kInt32Size, imm.offset, full_index,
6050  pinned, kDoForceCheck, kCheckAlignment);
6051  pinned.set(index_reg);
6052 
6053  uintptr_t offset = imm.offset;
6054  Register addr = index_reg;
6055  if (__ cache_state()->is_used(LiftoffRegister(index_reg))) {
6056  addr = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
6057  __ Move(addr, index_reg, kIntPtrKind);
6058  }
6059  if (offset) {
6060  __ emit_ptrsize_addi(addr, addr, offset);
6061  }
6062 
6063  Register mem_start = GetMemoryStart(imm.memory->index, pinned);
6064  __ emit_ptrsize_add(addr, addr, mem_start);
6065 
6066  LiftoffRegister result =
6067  GenerateCCall(kI32,
6068  {{kIntPtrKind, LiftoffRegister{addr}, 0},
6069  {kI32, num_waiters_to_wake, 0}},
6070  ExternalReference::wasm_atomic_notify());
6071 
6072  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
6073 
6074  __ PushRegister(kI32, result);
6075  }
6076
