6148  void AtomicOp(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode, const Value args[],
6149  const size_t argc, const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm,
6150  Value* result) {
6151  switch (opcode) {
6152 #define ATOMIC_STORE_OP(name, type) \
6153  case wasm::kExpr##name: \
6154  AtomicStoreMem(decoder, StoreType::type, imm); \
6155  break;
6156 
6157  ATOMIC_STORE_LIST(ATOMIC_STORE_OP)
6158 #undef ATOMIC_STORE_OP
6159 
6160 #define ATOMIC_LOAD_OP(name, type) \
6161  case wasm::kExpr##name: \
6162  AtomicLoadMem(decoder, LoadType::type, imm); \
6163  break;
6164 
6165  ATOMIC_LOAD_LIST(ATOMIC_LOAD_OP)
6166 #undef ATOMIC_LOAD_OP
6167 
6168 #define ATOMIC_BINOP_OP(op, name, type) \
6169  case wasm::kExpr##name: \
6170  AtomicBinop(decoder, StoreType::type, imm, &LiftoffAssembler::Atomic##op); \
6171  break;
6172 
6173  ATOMIC_BINOP_INSTRUCTION_LIST(ATOMIC_BINOP_OP)
6174 #undef ATOMIC_BINOP_OP
6175 
6176 #define ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_OP(name, type) \
6177  case wasm::kExpr##name: \
6178  AtomicCompareExchange(decoder, StoreType::type, imm); \
6179  break;
6180 
6181  ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_LIST(ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_OP)
6182 #undef ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_OP
6183 
6184  case kExprI32AtomicWait:
6185  AtomicWait(decoder, kI32, imm);
6186  break;
6187  case kExprI64AtomicWait:
6188  AtomicWait(decoder, kI64, imm);
6189  break;
6190  case kExprAtomicNotify:
6191  AtomicNotify(decoder, imm);
6192  break;
6193  default:
6194  UNREACHABLE();
6195  }
6196  }
6197 
6198 #undef ATOMIC_STORE_LIST
6199 #undef ATOMIC_LOAD_LIST
6200 #undef ATOMIC_BINOP_INSTRUCTION_LIST
6201 #undef ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_LIST
6202 
6203  void AtomicFence(FullDecoder* decoder) { __ AtomicFence(); }
6204 
6205  void StructAtomicRMW(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode,
6206  const Value& struct_object, const FieldImmediate& field,
6207  const Value& field_value, AtomicMemoryOrder order,
6208  Value* result) {
6209  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
6210  ValueKind field_kind = struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index).kind();
6211  int offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, field.field_imm.index);
6212  LiftoffRegList pinned;
6213  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6214  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6215 
6216  auto [explicit_check, implicit_check] =
6217  null_checks_for_struct_op(struct_object.type, field.field_imm.index);
6218  if (implicit_check) {
6219  // TODO(mliedtke): Support implicit null checks for atomic operations.
6220  // Note that we can't do implicit null checks for i64 due to WasmNull not
6221  // being 8-byte-aligned!
6222  implicit_check = false;
6223  explicit_check = true;
6224  }
6225 
6226  if (explicit_check) {
6227  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, obj.gp(), pinned, struct_object.type);
6228  }
6229 
6230 // Skip the non-atomic implementation special case on ia32 as it is not needed
6231 // (ia32 doesn't require any alignment for these operation) and there are only
6232 // painfully few registers available on ia32.
6233 #if !V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6234  if (!field.struct_imm.shared) {
6235  // On some architectures atomic operations require aligned accesses while
6236  // unshared objects don't have the required alignment. For simplicity we
6237  // do the same on all platforms and for all rmw operations (even though
6238  // only 64 bit operations should run into alignment problems).
6239  // TODO(mliedtke): Reconsider this if atomic operations on unshared
6240  // objects remain part of the spec proposal.
6241  LiftoffRegister result_reg =
6242  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(field_kind), pinned));
6243  LoadObjectField(decoder, result_reg, obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, field_kind,
6244  false, implicit_check, pinned);
6245  LiftoffRegister new_value = opcode == kExprStructAtomicExchange
6246  ? value
6247  : pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(
6248  reg_class_for(field_kind), pinned));
6249 
6250  if (field_kind == ValueKind::kI32) {
6251  switch (opcode) {
6252  case kExprStructAtomicAdd:
6253  __ emit_i32_add(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6254  break;
6255  case kExprStructAtomicSub:
6256  __ emit_i32_sub(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6257  break;
6258  case kExprStructAtomicAnd:
6259  __ emit_i32_and(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6260  break;
6261  case kExprStructAtomicOr:
6262  __ emit_i32_or(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6263  break;
6264  case kExprStructAtomicXor:
6265  __ emit_i32_xor(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6266  break;
6267  case kExprStructAtomicExchange:
6268  break;
6269  default:
6270  UNREACHABLE();
6271  }
6272  } else if (field_kind == ValueKind::kI64) {
6273  switch (opcode) {
6274  case kExprStructAtomicAdd:
6275  __ emit_i64_add(new_value, result_reg, value);
6276  break;
6277  case kExprStructAtomicSub:
6278  __ emit_i64_sub(new_value, result_reg, value);
6279  break;
6280  case kExprStructAtomicAnd:
6281  __ emit_i64_and(new_value, result_reg, value);
6282  break;
6283  case kExprStructAtomicOr:
6284  __ emit_i64_or(new_value, result_reg, value);
6285  break;
6286  case kExprStructAtomicXor:
6287  __ emit_i64_xor(new_value, result_reg, value);
6288  break;
6289  case kExprStructAtomicExchange:
6290  break;
6291  default:
6292  UNREACHABLE();
6293  }
6294  } else {
6295  CHECK(is_reference(field_kind));
6296  CHECK_EQ(opcode, kExprStructAtomicExchange);
6297  // Nothing to be done here.
6298  }
6299  __ PushRegister(field_kind, result_reg);
6300  StoreObjectField(decoder, obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, new_value, false,
6301  pinned, field_kind);
6302  return;
6303  }
6304 #endif // !V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6305 
6306 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6307  // The tagged atomic exchange needs the value register for the write
6308  // barrier.
6309  LiftoffRegister result_reg = value;
6310  if (opcode != kExprStructAtomicExchange || !is_reference(field_kind)) {
6311  // We have to reuse the value register as the result register so that we
6312  // don't run out of registers on ia32. For this we use the value register
6313  // as the result register if it has no other uses. Otherwise we allocate a
6314  // new register and let go of the value register to get spilled.
6315  if (__ cache_state()->is_used(value)) {
6316  result_reg =
6317  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(field_kind), pinned));
6318  __ Move(result_reg, value, field_kind);
6319  pinned.clear(value);
6320  value = result_reg;
6321  }
6322  } else {
6323  result_reg =
6324  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(field_kind), pinned));
6325  }
6326 #else
6327  LiftoffRegister result_reg =
6328  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(field_kind), pinned));
6329 #endif
6330  switch (opcode) {
6331  case kExprStructAtomicAdd:
6332  __ AtomicAdd(obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, value, result_reg,
6333  StoreType::ForValueKind(field_kind), false);
6334  break;
6335  case kExprStructAtomicSub:
6336  __ AtomicSub(obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, value, result_reg,
6337  StoreType::ForValueKind(field_kind), false);
6338  break;
6339  case kExprStructAtomicAnd:
6340  __ AtomicAnd(obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, value, result_reg,
6341  StoreType::ForValueKind(field_kind), false);
6342  break;
6343  case kExprStructAtomicOr:
6344  __ AtomicOr(obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, value, result_reg,
6345  StoreType::ForValueKind(field_kind), false);
6346  break;
6347  case kExprStructAtomicXor:
6348  __ AtomicXor(obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, value, result_reg,
6349  StoreType::ForValueKind(field_kind), false);
6350  break;
6351  case kExprStructAtomicExchange:
6352  if (is_reference(field_kind)) {
6353  __ AtomicExchangeTaggedPointer(obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, value,
6354  result_reg, pinned);
6355  break;
6356  }
6357  __ AtomicExchange(obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, value, result_reg,
6358  StoreType::ForValueKind(field_kind), false);
6359  break;
6360  default:
6361  UNREACHABLE();
6362  }
6363  __ PushRegister(field_kind, result_reg);
6364  }
6365 
6366  void StructAtomicCompareExchange(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode,
6367  const Value& struct_object,
6368  const FieldImmediate& field,
6369  const Value& expected_val,
6370  const Value& new_val,
6371  AtomicMemoryOrder order, Value* result) {
6372  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
6373  ValueKind field_kind = struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index).kind();
6374  int offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, field.field_imm.index);
6375  auto [explicit_check, implicit_check] =
6376  null_checks_for_struct_op(struct_object.type, field.field_imm.index);
6377 
6378 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6379  DCHECK(!implicit_check); // No trap handler on 32-bit.
6380  // Instead of first popping all inputs into registers, emit an early null
6381  // check on ia32 (as the null check requires yet another register which
6382  // isn't available otherwise.)
6383  if (explicit_check) {
6384  LiftoffRegList pinned;
6385  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PeekToRegister(2, pinned));
6386  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, obj.gp(), pinned, struct_object.type);
6387  }
6388 
6389  LiftoffRegList pinned;
6390  LiftoffRegister new_value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6391  LiftoffRegister expected_value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6392  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6393 
6394  LiftoffRegister result_reg = expected_value;
6395  if (__ cache_state()->is_used(result_reg)) {
6396  __ SpillRegister(result_reg);
6397  }
6398 #else // V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6399 
6400  LiftoffRegList pinned;
6401  LiftoffRegister new_value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6402  LiftoffRegister expected_value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6403  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6404 
6405  if (implicit_check) {
6406  // TODO(mliedtke): Support implicit null checks for atomic operations.
6407  // Note that we can't do implicit null checks for i64 due to WasmNull not
6408  // being 8-byte-aligned!
6409  implicit_check = false;
6410  explicit_check = true;
6411  }
6412 
6413  if (explicit_check) {
6414  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, obj.gp(), pinned, struct_object.type);
6415  }
6416 
6417  // Special implementation for unshared objects which don't guarantee aligned
6418  // i64 values.
6419  if (!field.struct_imm.shared && field_kind == ValueKind::kI64) {
6420  LiftoffRegister result_reg =
6421  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(field_kind), pinned));
6422  LoadObjectField(decoder, result_reg, obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, field_kind,
6423  false, implicit_check, pinned);
6424  {
6425  Label end;
6426  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
6427  if constexpr (Is64()) {
6428  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &end, field_kind, result_reg.gp(),
6429  expected_value.gp(), frozen);
6430  } else {
6431  DCHECK(result_reg.is_gp_pair());
6432  DCHECK(expected_value.is_gp_pair());
6433  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &end, kI32, result_reg.high_gp(),
6434  expected_value.high_gp(), frozen);
6435  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &end, kI32, result_reg.low_gp(),
6436  expected_value.low_gp(), frozen);
6437  }
6438  StoreObjectField(decoder, obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, new_value, false,
6439  pinned, field_kind);
6440  __ bind(&end);
6441  }
6442  __ PushRegister(field_kind, result_reg);
6443  return;
6444  }
6445 
6446  LiftoffRegister result_reg =
6447  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(field_kind), pinned));
6448 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6449 
6450  if (is_reference(field_kind)) {
6451  UNIMPLEMENTED();
6452  } else {
6453  __ AtomicCompareExchange(obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, expected_value,
6454  new_value, result_reg,
6455  StoreType::ForValueKind(field_kind), false);
6456  __ PushRegister(field_kind, result_reg);
6457  }
6458  }
6459 
6460  void ArrayAtomicRMW(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode,
6461  const Value& array_obj, const ArrayIndexImmediate& imm,
6462  const Value& index_val, const Value& value_val,
6463  AtomicMemoryOrder order, Value* result) {
6464  LiftoffRegList pinned;
6465 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6466  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
6467 #else
6468  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6469 #endif
6470  LiftoffRegister index = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
6471  LiftoffRegister array = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6472  if (null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit) {
6473  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, array.gp(), pinned, array_obj.type);
6474  }
6475  bool implicit_null_check =
6476  array_obj.type.is_nullable() &&
6477  null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler;
6478  BoundsCheckArray(decoder, implicit_null_check, array, index, pinned);
6479  ValueKind elem_kind = imm.array_type->element_type().kind();
6480  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, elem_kind, "array load")) return;
6481  int elem_size_shift = value_kind_size_log2(elem_kind);
6482  if (elem_size_shift != 0) {
6483  __ emit_i32_shli(index.gp(), index.gp(), elem_size_shift);
6484  }
6485 
6486  // Skip the non-atomic implementation special case on ia32 as it is not
6487  // needed (ia32 doesn't require any alignment for these operation) and there
6488  // are only painfully few registers available on ia32.
6489 #if !V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6490  if (!array_obj.type.is_shared()) {
6491  // On some architectures atomic operations require aligned accesses while
6492  // unshared objects don't have the required alignment. For simplicity we
6493  // do the same on all platforms and for all rmw operations (even though
6494  // only 64 bit operations should run into alignment problems).
6495  // TODO(mliedtke): Reconsider this if atomic operations on unshared
6496  // objects remain part of the spec proposal.
6497  LiftoffRegister result_reg =
6498  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(elem_kind), pinned));
6499  LoadObjectField(decoder, result_reg, array.gp(), index.gp(),
6500  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize),
6501  elem_kind, true, false, pinned);
6502  LiftoffRegister new_value = opcode == kExprArrayAtomicExchange
6503  ? value
6504  : pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(
6505  reg_class_for(elem_kind), pinned));
6506 
6507  if (elem_kind == ValueKind::kI32) {
6508  switch (opcode) {
6509  case kExprArrayAtomicAdd:
6510  __ emit_i32_add(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6511  break;
6512  case kExprArrayAtomicSub:
6513  __ emit_i32_sub(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6514  break;
6515  case kExprArrayAtomicAnd:
6516  __ emit_i32_and(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6517  break;
6518  case kExprArrayAtomicOr:
6519  __ emit_i32_or(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6520  break;
6521  case kExprArrayAtomicXor:
6522  __ emit_i32_xor(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6523  break;
6524  case kExprArrayAtomicExchange:
6525  break;
6526  default:
6527  UNREACHABLE();
6528  }
6529  } else if (elem_kind == ValueKind::kI64) {
6530  switch (opcode) {
6531  case kExprArrayAtomicAdd:
6532  __ emit_i64_add(new_value, result_reg, value);
6533  break;
6534  case kExprArrayAtomicSub:
6535  __ emit_i64_sub(new_value, result_reg, value);
6536  break;
6537  case kExprArrayAtomicAnd:
6538  __ emit_i64_and(new_value, result_reg, value);
6539  break;
6540  case kExprArrayAtomicOr:
6541  __ emit_i64_or(new_value, result_reg, value);
6542  break;
6543  case kExprArrayAtomicXor:
6544  __ emit_i64_xor(new_value, result_reg, value);
6545  break;
6546  case kExprArrayAtomicExchange:
6547  break;
6548  default:
6549  UNREACHABLE();
6550  }
6551  } else {
6552  CHECK(is_reference(elem_kind));
6553  CHECK_EQ(opcode, kExprArrayAtomicExchange);
6554  // Nothing to be done here.
6555  }
6556  __ PushRegister(elem_kind, result_reg);
6557  StoreObjectField(decoder, array.gp(), index.gp(),
6558  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize),
6559  new_value, false, pinned, elem_kind);
6560  return;
6561  }
6562 #endif // !V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6563 
6564 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6565  // The tagged atomic exchange needs the value register for the write
6566  // barrier.
6567  const bool preserve_value_reg =
6568  opcode == kExprArrayAtomicExchange && is_reference(elem_kind);
6569  LiftoffRegister result_reg =
6570  preserve_value_reg
6571  ? pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(elem_kind), pinned))
6572  : value;
6573 #else
6574  LiftoffRegister result_reg =
6575  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(elem_kind), pinned));
6576 #endif
6577  const int offset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize);
6578  switch (opcode) {
6579  case kExprArrayAtomicAdd:
6580  __ AtomicAdd(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6581  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6582  break;
6583  case kExprArrayAtomicSub:
6584  __ AtomicSub(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6585  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6586  break;
6587  case kExprArrayAtomicAnd:
6588  __ AtomicAnd(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6589  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6590  break;
6591  case kExprArrayAtomicOr:
6592  __ AtomicOr(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6593  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6594  break;
6595  case kExprArrayAtomicXor:
6596  __ AtomicXor(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6597  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6598  break;
6599  case kExprArrayAtomicExchange:
6600  if (is_reference(elem_kind)) {
6601  __ AtomicExchangeTaggedPointer(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value,
6602  result_reg, pinned);
6603  break;
6604  }
6605  __ AtomicExchange(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6606  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6607  break;
6608  default:
6609  UNREACHABLE();
6610  }
6611  __ PushRegister(elem_kind, result_reg);
6612  }
6613 
6614  void ArrayAtomicCompareExchange(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode,
6615  const Value& array_obj,
6616  const ArrayIndexImmediate& imm,
6617  const Value& index_val,
6618  const Value& expected_val,
6619  const Value& new_val, AtomicMemoryOrder order,
6620  Value* result) {
6621 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6622  // This is an ia32-specific implementation that tries to use as few
6623  // registers as possible, so that it works with i64 values lowered to
6624  // register pairs.
6625  LiftoffRegList pinned;
6626  std::optional<LiftoffRegister> array =
6627  pinned.set(__ PeekToRegister(3, pinned));
6628  DCHECK_EQ(null_check_strategy_, compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit);
6629  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, array->gp(), pinned, array_obj.type);
6630 
6631  std::optional<LiftoffRegister> index =
6632  pinned.set(__ PeekToRegister(2, pinned));
6633 
6634  const bool implicit_null_check = false;
6635  BoundsCheckArray(decoder, implicit_null_check, *array, *index, pinned);
6636  ValueKind elem_kind = imm.array_type->element_type().kind();
6637  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, elem_kind, "array load")) return;
6638 
6639  // As we don't have `PeekToModifiableRegister`, simply allocate a new
6640  // register for the array + index and then "free" the array and
6641  // index registers.
6642  LiftoffRegister mem_location =
6643  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
6644  int elem_size_shift = value_kind_size_log2(elem_kind);
6645  if (elem_size_shift != 0) {
6646  __ emit_i32_shli(mem_location.gp(), index->gp(), elem_size_shift);
6647  __ emit_i32_add(mem_location.gp(), mem_location.gp(), array->gp());
6648  } else {
6649  __ emit_i32_add(mem_location.gp(), array->gp(), index->gp());
6650  }
6651  pinned.clear(*array);
6652  pinned.clear(*index);
6653  array = {};
6654  index = {};
6655 
6656  LiftoffRegister new_value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6657  LiftoffRegister expected_value =
6658  pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
6659  __ DropValues(2); // index, array.
6660 
6661  LiftoffRegister result_reg = expected_value;
6662  const int offset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize);
6663  if (is_reference(elem_kind)) {
6664  UNIMPLEMENTED();
6665  } else {
6666  __ AtomicCompareExchange(mem_location.gp(), no_reg, offset,
6667  expected_value, new_value, result_reg,
6668  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6669  }
6670  __ PushRegister(elem_kind, result_reg);
6671 #else
6672  LiftoffRegList pinned;
6673  LiftoffRegister new_value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6674  LiftoffRegister expected_value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6675  LiftoffRegister index = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
6676  LiftoffRegister array = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
6677  if (null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit) {
6678  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, array.gp(), pinned, array_obj.type);
6679  }
6680  bool implicit_null_check =
6681  array_obj.type.is_nullable() &&
6682  null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler;
6683  BoundsCheckArray(decoder, implicit_null_check, array, index, pinned);
6684  ValueKind elem_kind = imm.array_type->element_type().kind();
6685  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, elem_kind, "array load")) return;
6686  int elem_size_shift = value_kind_size_log2(elem_kind);
6687  if (elem_size_shift != 0) {
6688  __ emit_i32_shli(index.gp(), index.gp(), elem_size_shift);
6689  }
6690 
6691  // Special implementation for unshared objects which don't guarantee aligned
6692  // i64 values.
6693  if (!array_obj.type.is_shared() && elem_kind == ValueKind::kI64) {
6694  LiftoffRegister result_reg =
6695  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(elem_kind), pinned));
6696  LoadObjectField(decoder, result_reg, array.gp(), index.gp(),
6697  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize),
6698  elem_kind, true, false, pinned);
6699  {
6700  Label end;
6701  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
6702  if constexpr (Is64()) {
6703  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &end, elem_kind, result_reg.gp(),
6704  expected_value.gp(), frozen);
6705  } else {
6706  DCHECK(result_reg.is_gp_pair());
6707  DCHECK(expected_value.is_gp_pair());
6708  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &end, kI32, result_reg.high_gp(),
6709  expected_value.high_gp(), frozen);
6710  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &end, kI32, result_reg.low_gp(),
6711  expected_value.low_gp(), frozen);
6712  }
6713  StoreObjectField(decoder, array.gp(), index.gp(),
6714  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize),
6715  new_value, false, pinned, elem_kind);
6716  __ bind(&end);
6717  }
6718  __ PushRegister(elem_kind, result_reg);
6719  return;
6720  }
6721 
6722  LiftoffRegister result_reg =
6723  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(elem_kind), pinned));
6724  const int offset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize);
6725  if (is_reference(elem_kind)) {
6726  UNIMPLEMENTED();
6727  } else {
6728  Register offset_reg = index.gp();
6729  __ AtomicCompareExchange(array.gp(), offset_reg, offset, expected_value,
6730  new_value, result_reg,
6731  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6732  }
6733  __ PushRegister(elem_kind, result_reg);
6734 #endif
6735  }
6736 
6737  // Pop a VarState and if needed transform it to an intptr.
6738  // When truncating from u64 to u32, the {*high_word} is updated to contain
6739  // the ORed combination of all high words.
6740  VarState PopIndexToVarState(Register* high_word, LiftoffRegList* pinned) {
6741  VarState slot = __ PopVarState();
6742  const bool is_64bit_value = slot.kind() == kI64;
6743  // For memory32 on a 32-bit system or memory64 on a 64-bit system, there is
6744  // nothing to do.
6745  if (Is64() == is_64bit_value) {
6746  if (slot.is_reg()) pinned->set(slot.reg());
6747  return slot;
6748  }
6749 
6750  // {kI64} constants will be stored as 32-bit integers in the {VarState} and
6751  // will be sign-extended later. Hence we can return constants if they are
6752  // positive (such that sign-extension and zero-extension are identical).
6753  if (slot.is_const() && (kIntPtrKind == kI32 || slot.i32_const() >= 0)) {
6754  return {kIntPtrKind, slot.i32_const(), 0};
6755  }
6756 
6757  // For memory32 on 64-bit hosts, zero-extend.
6758  if constexpr (Is64()) {
6759  DCHECK(!is_64bit_value); // Handled above.
6760  LiftoffRegister reg = __ LoadToModifiableRegister(slot, *pinned);
6761  __ emit_u32_to_uintptr(reg.gp(), reg.gp());
6762  pinned->set(reg);
6763  return {kIntPtrKind, reg, 0};
6764  }
6765 
6766  // For memory64 on 32-bit systems, combine all high words for a zero-check
6767  // and only use the low words afterwards. This keeps the register pressure
6768  // manageable.
6769  DCHECK(is_64bit_value && !Is64()); // Other cases are handled above.
6770  LiftoffRegister reg = __ LoadToRegister(slot, *pinned);
6771  pinned->set(reg.low());
6772  if (*high_word == no_reg) {
6773  // Choose a register to hold the (combination of) high word(s). It cannot
6774  // be one of the pinned registers, and it cannot be used in the value
6775  // stack.
6776  *high_word =
6777  !pinned->has(reg.high()) && __ cache_state()->is_free(reg.high())
6778  ? reg.high().gp()
6779  : __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, *pinned).gp();
6780  pinned->set(*high_word);
6781  if (*high_word != reg.high_gp()) {
6782  __ Move(*high_word, reg.high_gp(), kI32);
6783  }
6784  } else if (*high_word != reg.high_gp()) {
6785  // Combine the new high word into existing high words.
6786  __ emit_i32_or(*high_word, *high_word, reg.high_gp());
6787  }
6788  return {kIntPtrKind, reg.low(), 0};
6789  }
6790 
6791  // This is a helper function that traps with TableOOB if any bit is set in
6792  // `high_word`. It is meant to be used after `PopIndexToVarState()` to check
6793  // if the conversion was valid.
6794  // Note that this is suboptimal as we add an OOL code for this special
6795  // condition, and there's also another conditional trap in the caller builtin.
6796  // However, it only applies for the rare case of 32-bit platforms with
6797  // table64.
6798  void CheckHighWordEmptyForTableType(FullDecoder* decoder,
6799  const Register high_word,
6800  LiftoffRegList* pinned) {
6801  if constexpr (Is64()) {
6802  DCHECK_EQ(no_reg, high_word);
6803  return;
6804  }
6805  if (high_word == no_reg) return;
6806 
6807  OolTrapLabel trap =
6808  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapTableOutOfBounds);
6809  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotZero, trap.label(), kI32, high_word, no_reg,
6810  trap.frozen());
6811  // Clearing `high_word` is safe because this never aliases with another
6812  // in-use register, see `PopIndexToVarState()`.
6813  pinned->clear(high_word);
6814  }
6815 
6816  // Same as {PopIndexToVarState}, but can take a VarState in the middle of the
6817  // stack without popping it.
6818  // For 64-bit values on 32-bit systems, the resulting VarState will contain a
6819  // single register whose value will be kMaxUint32 if the high word had any
6820  // bits set.
6821  VarState IndexToVarStateSaturating(int stack_index, LiftoffRegList* pinned) {
6822  DCHECK_LE(0, stack_index);
6823  DCHECK_LT(stack_index, __ cache_state()->stack_height());
6824  VarState& slot = __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1 - stack_index];
6825  const bool is_mem64 = slot.kind() == kI64;
6826  // For memory32 on a 32-bit system or memory64 on a 64-bit system, there is
6827  // nothing to do.
6828  if ((kSystemPointerSize == kInt64Size) == is_mem64) {
6829  if (slot.is_reg()) pinned->set(slot.reg());
6830  return slot;
6831  }
6832 
6833  // {kI64} constants will be stored as 32-bit integers in the {VarState} and
6834  // will be sign-extended later. Hence we can return constants if they are
6835  // positive (such that sign-extension and zero-extension are identical).
6836  if (slot.is_const() && (kIntPtrKind == kI32 || slot.i32_const() >= 0)) {
6837  return {kIntPtrKind, slot.i32_const(), 0};
6838  }
6839 
6840  LiftoffRegister reg = __ LoadToModifiableRegister(slot, *pinned);
6841  // For memory32 on 64-bit hosts, zero-extend.
6842  if constexpr (Is64()) {
6843  DCHECK(!is_mem64); // Handled above.
6844  __ emit_u32_to_uintptr(reg.gp(), reg.gp());
6845  pinned->set(reg);
6846  return {kIntPtrKind, reg, 0};
6847  }
6848 
6849  // For memory64 on 32-bit systems, saturate the low word.
6850  DCHECK(is_mem64); // Other cases are handled above.
6851  DCHECK_EQ(kSystemPointerSize, kInt32Size);
6852  pinned->set(reg.low());
6853  Label ok;
6854  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
6855  __ emit_cond_jump(kZero, &ok, kI32, reg.high().gp(), no_reg, frozen);
6856  __ LoadConstant(reg.low(), WasmValue{kMaxUInt32});
6857  __ emit_jump(&ok);
6858  __ bind(&ok);
6859  return {kIntPtrKind, reg.low(), 0};
6860  }
6861 
6862  // Same as {PopIndexToVarState}, but saturates 64-bit values on 32-bit
6863  // platforms like {IndexToVarStateSaturating}.
6864  VarState PopIndexToVarStateSaturating(LiftoffRegList* pinned) {
6865  VarState result = IndexToVarStateSaturating(0, pinned);
6866  __ DropValues(1);
6867  return result;
6868  }
6869 
6870  // The following functions are to be used inside a DCHECK. They always return
6871  // true and will fail internally on a detected inconsistency.
6872 #ifdef DEBUG
6873  // Checks that the top-of-stack value matches the declared memory (64-bit or
6874  // 32-bit).
6875  bool MatchingMemTypeOnTopOfStack(const WasmMemory* memory) {
6876  return MatchingAddressTypeOnTopOfStack(memory->is_memory64());
6877  }
6878 
6879  // Checks that the top-of-stack value matches the expected bitness.
6880  bool MatchingAddressTypeOnTopOfStack(bool expect_64bit_value) {
6881  DCHECK_LT(0, __ cache_state()->stack_height());
6882  ValueKind expected_kind = expect_64bit_value ? kI64 : kI32;
6883  DCHECK_EQ(expected_kind, __ cache_state()->stack_state.back().kind());
6884  return true;
6885  }
6886 
6887  bool MatchingMemType(const WasmMemory* memory, int stack_index) {
6888  DCHECK_LE(0, stack_index);
6889  DCHECK_LT(stack_index, __ cache_state()->stack_state.size());
6890  ValueKind expected_kind = memory->is_memory64() ? kI64 : kI32;
6891  DCHECK_EQ(expected_kind,
6892  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1 - stack_index].kind());
6893  return true;
6894  }
6895 #endif
6896 
6897  void MemoryInit(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryInitImmediate& imm,
6898  const Value&, const Value&, const Value&) {
6899  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
6900  Register mem_offsets_high_word = no_reg;
6901  LiftoffRegList pinned;
6902  VarState size = __ PopVarState();
6903  if (size.is_reg()) pinned.set(size.reg());
6904  VarState src = __ PopVarState();
6905  if (src.is_reg()) pinned.set(src.reg());
6906  DCHECK(MatchingMemTypeOnTopOfStack(imm.memory.memory));
6907  VarState dst = PopIndexToVarState(&mem_offsets_high_word, &pinned);
6908 
6909  Register instance_data = __ cache_state() -> cached_instance_data;
6910  if (instance_data == no_reg) {
6911  instance_data = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
6912  __ LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
6913  }
6914  pinned.set(instance_data);
6915 
6916  // TODO(crbug.com/41480344): The stack state in the OOL code should reflect
6917  // the state before popping any values (for a better debugging experience).
6918  if (mem_offsets_high_word != no_reg) {
6919  // If any high word has bits set, jump to the OOB trap.
6920  OolTrapLabel trap =
6921  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapMemOutOfBounds);
6922  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotZero, trap.label(), kI32, mem_offsets_high_word,
6923  no_reg, trap.frozen());
6924  pinned.clear(mem_offsets_high_word);
6925  }
6926 
6927  LiftoffRegister result =
6928  GenerateCCall(kI32,
6929  {{kIntPtrKind, LiftoffRegister{instance_data}, 0},
6930  {kI32, static_cast<int32_t>(imm.memory.index), 0},
6931  dst,
6932  src,
6933  {kI32, static_cast<int32_t>(imm.data_segment.index), 0},
6934  size},
6935  ExternalReference::wasm_memory_init());
6936  OolTrapLabel trap =
6937  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapMemOutOfBounds);
6938  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, trap.label(), kI32, result.gp(), no_reg,
6939  trap.frozen());
6940  }
6941 
6942  void DataDrop(FullDecoder* decoder, const IndexImmediate& imm) {
6943  LiftoffRegList pinned;
6944 
6945  Register seg_size_array =
6946  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
6947  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(seg_size_array, DataSegmentSizes, pinned);
6948 
6949  LiftoffRegister seg_index =
6950  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
6951  // Scale the seg_index for the array access.
6952  __ LoadConstant(
6953  seg_index,
6954  WasmValue(wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedUInt32Array(
6955  imm.index)));
6956 
6957  // Set the length of the segment to '0' to drop it.
6958  LiftoffRegister null_reg = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
6959  __ LoadConstant(null_reg, WasmValue(0));
6960  __ Store(seg_size_array, seg_index.gp(), 0, null_reg, StoreType::kI32Store,
6961  pinned);
6962  }
6963 
6964  void MemoryCopy(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryCopyImmediate& imm,
6965  const Value&, const Value&, const Value&) {
6966  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
6967  Register mem_offsets_high_word = no_reg;
6968  LiftoffRegList pinned;
6969 
6970  // The type of {size} is the min of {src} and {dst} (where {kI32 < kI64}).
6971  DCHECK(
6972  MatchingAddressTypeOnTopOfStack(imm.memory_dst.memory->is_memory64() &&
6973  imm.memory_src.memory->is_memory64()));
6974  VarState size = PopIndexToVarState(&mem_offsets_high_word, &pinned);
6975  DCHECK(MatchingMemTypeOnTopOfStack(imm.memory_src.memory));
6976  VarState src = PopIndexToVarState(&mem_offsets_high_word, &pinned);
6977  DCHECK(MatchingMemTypeOnTopOfStack(imm.memory_dst.memory));
6978  VarState dst = PopIndexToVarState(&mem_offsets_high_word, &pinned);
6979 
6980  Register instance_data = __ cache_state() -> cached_instance_data;
6981  if (instance_data == no_reg) {
6982  instance_data = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
6983  __ LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
6984  }
6985  pinned.set(instance_data);
6986 
6987  // TODO(crbug.com/41480344): The stack state in the OOL code should reflect
6988  // the state before popping any values (for a better debugging experience).
6989  DCHECK_IMPLIES(Is64(), mem_offsets_high_word == no_reg);
6990  if (!Is64() && mem_offsets_high_word != no_reg) {
6991  // If any high word has bits set, jump to the OOB trap.
6992  OolTrapLabel trap =
6993  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapMemOutOfBounds);
6994  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotZero, trap.label(), kI32, mem_offsets_high_word,
6995  no_reg, trap.frozen());
6996  }
6997 
6998  LiftoffRegister result =
6999  GenerateCCall(kI32,
7000  {{kIntPtrKind, LiftoffRegister{instance_data}, 0},
7001  {kI32, static_cast<int32_t>(imm.memory_dst.index), 0},
7002  {kI32, static_cast<int32_t>(imm.memory_src.index), 0},
7003  dst,
7004  src,
7005  size},
7006  ExternalReference::wasm_memory_copy());
7007  OolTrapLabel trap =
7008  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapMemOutOfBounds);
7009  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, trap.label(), kI32, result.gp(), no_reg,
7010  trap.frozen());
7011  }
7012 
7013  void MemoryFill(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryIndexImmediate& imm,
7014  const Value&, const Value&, const Value&) {
7015  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
7016  Register mem_offsets_high_word = no_reg;
7017  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7018  DCHECK(MatchingMemTypeOnTopOfStack(imm.memory));
7019  VarState size = PopIndexToVarState(&mem_offsets_high_word, &pinned);
7020  VarState value = __ PopVarState();
7021  if (value.is_reg()) pinned.set(value.reg());
7022  DCHECK(MatchingMemTypeOnTopOfStack(imm.memory));
7023  VarState dst = PopIndexToVarState(&mem_offsets_high_word, &pinned);
7024 
7025  Register instance_data = __ cache_state() -> cached_instance_data;
7026  if (instance_data == no_reg) {
7027  instance_data = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
7028  __ LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
7029  }
7030  pinned.set(instance_data);
7031 
7032  // TODO(crbug.com/41480344): The stack state in the OOL code should reflect
7033  // the state before popping any values (for a better debugging experience).
7034  if (mem_offsets_high_word != no_reg) {
7035  // If any high word has bits set, jump to the OOB trap.
7036  OolTrapLabel trap =
7037  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapMemOutOfBounds);
7038  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotZero, trap.label(), kI32, mem_offsets_high_word,
7039  no_reg, trap.frozen());
7040  }
7041 
7042  LiftoffRegister result =
7043  GenerateCCall(kI32,
7044  {{kIntPtrKind, LiftoffRegister{instance_data}, 0},
7045  {kI32, static_cast<int32_t>(imm.index), 0},
7046  dst,
7047  value,
7048  size},
7049  ExternalReference::wasm_memory_fill());
7050  OolTrapLabel trap =
7051  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapMemOutOfBounds);
7052  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, trap.label(), kI32, result.gp(), no_reg,
7053  trap.frozen());
7054  }
7055 
7056  void LoadSmi(LiftoffRegister reg, int value) {
7057  Address smi_value = Smi::FromInt(value).ptr();
7058  using smi_type = std::conditional_t<kSmiKind == kI32, int32_t, int64_t>;
7059  __ LoadConstant(reg, WasmValue{static_cast<smi_type>(smi_value)});
7060  }
7061 
7062  VarState LoadSmiConstant(int32_t constant, LiftoffRegList* pinned) {
7063  if constexpr (kSmiKind == kI32) {
7064  int32_t smi_const = static_cast<int32_t>(Smi::FromInt(constant).ptr());
7065  return VarState{kI32, smi_const, 0};
7066  } else {
7067  LiftoffRegister reg = pinned->set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, *pinned));
7068  LoadSmi(reg, constant);
7069  return VarState{kSmiKind, reg, 0};
7070  }
7071  }
7072 
7073  void TableInit(FullDecoder* decoder, const TableInitImmediate& imm,
7074  const Value&, const Value&, const Value&) {
7075  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
7076  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7077 
7078  VarState table_index = LoadSmiConstant(imm.table.index, &pinned);
7079  VarState segment_index =
7080  LoadSmiConstant(imm.element_segment.index, &pinned);
7081  VarState extract_shared_data = LoadSmiConstant(0, &pinned);
7082 
7083  VarState size = __ PopVarState();
7084  if (size.is_reg()) pinned.set(size.reg());
7085  VarState src = __ PopVarState();
7086  if (src.is_reg()) pinned.set(src.reg());
7087  Register index_high_word = no_reg;
7088  VarState dst = PopIndexToVarState(&index_high_word, &pinned);
7089 
7090  // Trap if any bit in high word was set.
7091  CheckHighWordEmptyForTableType(decoder, index_high_word, &pinned);
7092 
7093  CallBuiltin(
7094  Builtin::kWasmTableInit,
7095  MakeSig::Params(kIntPtrKind, kI32, kI32, kSmiKind, kSmiKind, kSmiKind),
7096  {dst, src, size, table_index, segment_index, extract_shared_data},
7097  decoder->position());
7098 
7099  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
7100  }
7101 
7102  void ElemDrop(FullDecoder* decoder, const IndexImmediate& imm) {
7103  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7104  Register element_segments =
7105  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
7106  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(element_segments, ElementSegments, pinned);
7107 
7108  LiftoffRegister seg_index =
7109  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
7110  __ LoadConstant(
7111  seg_index,
7112  WasmValue(
7113  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(imm.index)));
7114 
7115  // Mark the segment as dropped by setting it to the empty fixed array.
7116  Register empty_fixed_array =
7117  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
7118  __ LoadFullPointer(
7119  empty_fixed_array, kRootRegister,
7120  IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
7121 
7122  __ StoreTaggedPointer(element_segments, seg_index.gp(), 0,
7123  empty_fixed_array, pinned);
7124  }
7125 
7126  void TableCopy(FullDecoder* decoder, const TableCopyImmediate& imm,
7127  const Value&, const Value&, const Value&) {
7128  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
7129  Register index_high_word = no_reg;
7130  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7131 
7132  VarState table_src_index = LoadSmiConstant(imm.table_src.index, &pinned);
7133  VarState table_dst_index = LoadSmiConstant(imm.table_dst.index, &pinned);
7134  VarState extract_shared_data = LoadSmiConstant(0, &pinned);
7135 
7136  VarState size = PopIndexToVarState(&index_high_word, &pinned);
7137  VarState src = PopIndexToVarState(&index_high_word, &pinned);
7138  VarState dst = PopIndexToVarState(&index_high_word, &pinned);
7139 
7140  // Trap if any bit in the combined high words was set.
7141  CheckHighWordEmptyForTableType(decoder, index_high_word, &pinned);
7142 
7143  CallBuiltin(
7144  Builtin::kWasmTableCopy,
7145  MakeSig::Params(kIntPtrKind, kIntPtrKind, kIntPtrKind, kSmiKind,
7146  kSmiKind, kSmiKind),
7147  {dst, src, size, table_dst_index, table_src_index, extract_shared_data},
7148  decoder->position());
7149 
7150  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
7151  }
7152 
7153  void TableGrow(FullDecoder* decoder, const TableIndexImmediate& imm,
7154  const Value&, const Value&, Value* result) {
7155  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
7156  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7157 
7158  LiftoffRegister table_index_reg =
7159  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
7160  LoadSmi(table_index_reg, imm.index);
7161  VarState table_index(kSmiKind, table_index_reg, 0);
7162  // If `delta` is, OOB table.grow should return -1.
7163  VarState delta = PopIndexToVarStateSaturating(&pinned);
7164  VarState value = __ PopVarState();
7165  VarState extract_shared_data(kI32, 0, 0);
7166 
7167  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmTableGrow,
7168  MakeSig::Returns(kSmiKind).Params(kSmiKind, kIntPtrKind, kI32,
7169  kRefNull),
7170  {table_index, delta, extract_shared_data, value},
7171  decoder->position());
7172 
7173  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
7174  __ SmiToInt32(kReturnRegister0);
7175  if (imm.table->is_table64()) {
7176  LiftoffRegister result64 = LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0);
7177  if (kNeedI64RegPair) {
7178  result64 = LiftoffRegister::ForPair(kReturnRegister0, kReturnRegister1);
7179  }
7180  __ emit_type_conversion(kExprI64SConvertI32, result64,
7181  LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0), nullptr);
7182  __ PushRegister(kI64, result64);
7183  } else {
7184  __ PushRegister(kI32, LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0));
7185  }
7186  }
7187 
7188  void TableSize(FullDecoder* decoder, const TableIndexImmediate& imm, Value*) {
7189  // We have to look up instance->tables[table_index].length.
7190 
7191  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7192  // Get the number of calls array address.
7193  Register tables = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
7194  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(tables, Tables, pinned);
7195 
7196  Register table = tables;
7197  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
7198  table, tables, no_reg,
7199  ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(imm.index));
7200 
7201  int length_field_size = WasmTableObject::kCurrentLengthOffsetEnd -
7202  WasmTableObject::kCurrentLengthOffset + 1;
7203 
7204  Register result = table;
7205  __ Load(LiftoffRegister(result), table, no_reg,
7206  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTableObject::kCurrentLengthOffset),
7207  length_field_size == 4 ? LoadType::kI32Load : LoadType::kI64Load);
7208 
7209  __ SmiUntag(result);
7210 
7211  if (imm.table->is_table64()) {
7212  LiftoffRegister result64 = LiftoffRegister(result);
7213  if (kNeedI64RegPair) {
7214  result64 = LiftoffRegister::ForPair(
7215  result, __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp());
7216  }
7217  __ emit_type_conversion(kExprI64SConvertI32, result64,
7218  LiftoffRegister(result), nullptr);
7219  __ PushRegister(kI64, result64);
7220  } else {
7221  __ PushRegister(kI32, LiftoffRegister(result));
7222  }
7223  }
7224 
7225  void TableFill(FullDecoder* decoder, const TableIndexImmediate& imm,
7226  const Value&, const Value&, const Value&) {
7227  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
7228  Register high_words = no_reg;
7229  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7230 
7231  VarState table_index = LoadSmiConstant(imm.index, &pinned);
7232  VarState extract_shared_data{kI32, 0, 0};
7233 
7234  VarState count = PopIndexToVarState(&high_words, &pinned);
7235  VarState value = __ PopVarState();
7236  if (value.is_reg()) pinned.set(value.reg());
7237  VarState start = PopIndexToVarState(&high_words, &pinned);
7238  // Trap if any bit in the combined high words was set.
7239  CheckHighWordEmptyForTableType(decoder, high_words, &pinned);
7240 
7241  CallBuiltin(
7242  Builtin::kWasmTableFill,
7243  MakeSig::Params(kIntPtrKind, kIntPtrKind, kI32, kSmiKind, kRefNull),
7244  {start, count, extract_shared_data, table_index, value},
7245  decoder->position());
7246 
7247  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
7248  }
7249 
7250  LiftoffRegister GetRtt(FullDecoder* decoder, ModuleTypeIndex index,
7251  const TypeDefinition& type,
7252  const Value& descriptor_value) {
7253  if (!type.has_descriptor()) return RttCanon(decoder, index, {});
7254  return GetRttFromDescriptorOnStack(decoder, descriptor_value);
7255  }
7256 
7257  LiftoffRegister GetRttFromDescriptorOnStack(FullDecoder* decoder,
7258  const Value& descriptor_value) {
7259  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7260  LiftoffRegister descriptor = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister({}));
7261  auto [explicit_check, implicit_check] =
7262  null_checks_for_struct_op(descriptor_value.type, 0);
7263  if (explicit_check) {
7264  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, descriptor.gp(), pinned,
7265  descriptor_value.type);
7266  }
7267  LiftoffRegister rtt = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
7268  LoadObjectField(decoder, rtt, descriptor.gp(), no_reg,
7269  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmStruct::kHeaderSize), kRef,
7270  false, implicit_check, pinned);
7271  return rtt;
7272  }
7273 
7274  VarState GetFirstFieldIfPrototype(const StructType* struct_type,
7275  bool initial_values_on_stack,
7276  LiftoffRegList pinned) {
7277  // If the first field might be a DescriptorOptions containing a
7278  // JS prototype, we must pass it along. Otherwise, to satisfy the
7279  // parameter count, we pass Smi(0).
7280  if (initial_values_on_stack &&
7281  struct_type->first_field_can_be_prototype()) {
7282  int slot = -struct_type->field_count();
7283  return __ cache_state() -> stack_state.end()[slot];
7284  }
7285  LiftoffRegister reg = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
7286  LoadSmi(reg, 0);
7287  return VarState{kRef, reg, 0};
7288  }
7289 
7290  void StructNew(FullDecoder* decoder, const StructIndexImmediate& imm,
7291  const Value& descriptor, bool initial_values_on_stack) {
7292  const TypeDefinition& type = decoder->module_->type(imm.index);
7293  LiftoffRegister rtt = GetRtt(decoder, imm.index, type, descriptor);
7294 
7295  if (type.is_descriptor()) {
7296  VarState first_field = GetFirstFieldIfPrototype(
7297  imm.struct_type, initial_values_on_stack, LiftoffRegList{rtt});
7298  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmAllocateDescriptorStruct,
7299  MakeSig::Returns(kRef).Params(kRef, kI32, kRef),
7300  {VarState{kRef, rtt, 0},
7301  VarState{kI32, static_cast<int32_t>(imm.index.index), 0},
7302  first_field},
7303  decoder->position());
7304  } else {
7305  bool is_shared = type.is_shared;
7306  CallBuiltin(is_shared ? Builtin::kWasmAllocateSharedStructWithRtt
7307  : Builtin::kWasmAllocateStructWithRtt,
7308  MakeSig::Returns(kRef).Params(kRef, kI32),
7309  {VarState{kRef, rtt, 0},
7310  VarState{kI32, WasmStruct::Size(imm.struct_type), 0}},
7311  decoder->position());
7312  }
7313 
7314  LiftoffRegister obj(kReturnRegister0);
7315  LiftoffRegList pinned{obj};
7316 
7317  for (uint32_t i = imm.struct_type->field_count(); i > 0;) {
7318  i--;
7319  int offset = StructFieldOffset(imm.struct_type, i);
7320  ValueType field_type = imm.struct_type->field(i);
7321  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(
7322  initial_values_on_stack
7323  ? __ PopToRegister(pinned)
7324  : __ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(field_type.kind()), pinned));
7325  if (!initial_values_on_stack) {
7326  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, field_type.kind(), "default value")) {
7327  return;
7328  }
7329  SetDefaultValue(value, field_type);
7330  }
7331  // Skipping the write barrier is safe as long as:
7332  // (1) {obj} is freshly allocated, and
7333  // (2) {obj} is in new-space (not pretenured).
7334  StoreObjectField(decoder, obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, value, false, pinned,
7335  field_type.kind(),
7336  type.is_shared ? LiftoffAssembler::kNoSkipWriteBarrier
7337  : LiftoffAssembler::kSkipWriteBarrier);
7338  pinned.clear(value);
7339  }
7340  // If this assert fails then initialization of padding field might be
7341  // necessary.
7342  static_assert(Heap::kMinObjectSizeInTaggedWords == 2 &&
7343  WasmStruct::kHeaderSize == 2 * kTaggedSize,
7344  "empty struct might require initialization of padding field");
7345  __ PushRegister(kRef, obj);
7346  }
7347 
7348  void StructNew(FullDecoder* decoder, const StructIndexImmediate& imm,
7349  const Value& descriptor, const Value args[], Value* result) {
7350  StructNew(decoder, imm, descriptor, true);
7351  }
7352 
7353  void StructNewDefault(FullDecoder* decoder, const StructIndexImmediate& imm,
7354  const Value& descriptor, Value* result) {
7355  StructNew(decoder, imm, descriptor, false);
7356  }
7357 
7358  void StructGet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& struct_obj,
7359  const FieldImmediate& field, bool is_signed, Value* result) {
7360  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
7361  ValueKind field_kind = struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index).kind();
7362  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, field_kind, "field load")) return;
7363  int offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, field.field_imm.index);
7364  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7365  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7366 
7367  auto [explicit_check, implicit_check] =
7368  null_checks_for_struct_op(struct_obj.type, field.field_imm.index);
7369 
7370  if (explicit_check) {
7371  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, obj.gp(), pinned, struct_obj.type);
7372  }
7373  LiftoffRegister value =
7374  __ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(field_kind), pinned);
7375  LoadObjectField(decoder, value, obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, field_kind,
7376  is_signed, implicit_check, pinned);
7377  __ PushRegister(unpacked(field_kind), value);
7378  }
7379 
7380  void StructAtomicGet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& struct_obj,
7381  const FieldImmediate& field, bool is_signed,
7382  AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order, Value* result) {
7383  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
7384  ValueKind field_kind = struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index).kind();
7385  int offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, field.field_imm.index);
7386  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7387  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7388 
7389  auto [explicit_check, implicit_check] =
7390  null_checks_for_struct_op(struct_obj.type, field.field_imm.index);
7391  if (implicit_check) {
7392  // TODO(mliedtke): Support implicit null checks for atomic loads.
7393  // Note that we can't do implicit null checks for i64 due to WasmNull not
7394  // being 8-byte-aligned!
7395  implicit_check = false;
7396  explicit_check = true;
7397  }
7398 
7399  if (explicit_check) {
7400  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, obj.gp(), pinned, struct_obj.type);
7401  }
7402  LiftoffRegister value =
7403  __ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(field_kind), pinned);
7404  LoadAtomicObjectField(decoder, value, obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, field_kind,
7405  is_signed, implicit_check, memory_order, pinned);
7406  __ PushRegister(unpacked(field_kind), value);
7407  }
7408 
7409  void StructSet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& struct_obj,
7410  const FieldImmediate& field, const Value& field_value) {
7411  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
7412  ValueKind field_kind = struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index).kind();
7413  int offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, field.field_imm.index);
7414  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7415  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7416  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7417 
7418  auto [explicit_check, implicit_check] =
7419  null_checks_for_struct_op(struct_obj.type, field.field_imm.index);
7420 
7421  if (explicit_check) {
7422  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, obj.gp(), pinned, struct_obj.type);
7423  }
7424 
7425  StoreObjectField(decoder, obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, value, implicit_check,
7426  pinned, field_kind);
7427  }
7428 
7429  void StructAtomicSet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& struct_obj,
7430  const FieldImmediate& field, const Value& field_value,
7431  AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order) {
7432  // TODO(mliedtke): Merge this with the StructSet (same question for similar
7433  // atomic operations)?
7434  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
7435  ValueKind field_kind = struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index).kind();
7436  int offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, field.field_imm.index);
7437  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7438  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7439  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7440 
7441  auto [explicit_check, implicit_check] =
7442  null_checks_for_struct_op(struct_obj.type, field.field_imm.index);
7443  if (implicit_check) {
7444  // TODO(mliedtke): Support implicit null checks for atomic loads.
7445  // Note that we can't do implicit null checks for i64 due to WasmNull not
7446  // being 8-byte-aligned!
7447  implicit_check = false;
7448  explicit_check = true;
7449  }
7450 
7451  if (explicit_check) {
7452  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, obj.gp(), pinned, struct_obj.type);
7453  }
7454 
7455  StoreAtomicObjectField(decoder, obj.gp(), no_reg, offset, value,
7456  implicit_check, pinned, field_kind, memory_order);
7457  }
7458 
7459  void ArrayNew(FullDecoder* decoder, const ArrayIndexImmediate& imm,
7460  bool initial_value_on_stack) {
7461  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
7462  // Max length check.
7463  {
7464  LiftoffRegister length =
7465  __ LoadToRegister(__ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1], {});
7466  OolTrapLabel trap =
7467  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapArrayTooLarge);
7468  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedGreaterThan, trap.label(), length.gp(),
7469  WasmArray::MaxLength(imm.array_type),
7470  trap.frozen());
7471  }
7472  ValueType elem_type = imm.array_type->element_type();
7473  ValueKind elem_kind = elem_type.kind();
7474  int elem_size = value_kind_size(elem_kind);
7475  const bool is_shared = decoder->module_->type(imm.index).is_shared;
7476 
7477  // Allocate the array.
7478  {
7479  LiftoffRegister rtt = RttCanon(decoder, imm.index, {});
7480  CallBuiltin(is_shared ? Builtin::kWasmAllocateSharedArray_Uninitialized
7481  : Builtin::kWasmAllocateArray_Uninitialized,
7482  MakeSig::Returns(kRef).Params(kRef, kI32, kI32),
7483  {VarState{kRef, rtt, 0},
7484  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1], // length
7485  VarState{kI32, elem_size, 0}},
7486  decoder->position());
7487  }
7488 
7489  LiftoffRegister obj(kReturnRegister0);
7490  LiftoffRegList pinned{obj};
7491  LiftoffRegister length = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
7492  LiftoffRegister value =
7493  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(elem_kind), pinned));
7494  if (initial_value_on_stack) {
7495  __ PopToFixedRegister(value);
7496  } else {
7497  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, elem_kind, "default value")) return;
7498  SetDefaultValue(value, elem_type);
7499  }
7500 
7501  LiftoffRegister index = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
7502  __ LoadConstant(index, WasmValue(int32_t{0}));
7503 
7504  // Initialize the array's elements.
7505  // Skipping the write barrier is safe as long as:
7506  // (1) {obj} is freshly allocated, and
7507  // (2) {obj} is in new-space (not pretenured).
7508  // TODO(mliedtke): Only emit write barriers for reference types.
7509  ArrayFillImpl(decoder, pinned, obj, index, value, length, elem_kind,
7510  is_shared ? LiftoffAssembler::kNoSkipWriteBarrier
7511  : LiftoffAssembler::kSkipWriteBarrier);
7512 
7513  __ PushRegister(kRef, obj);
7514  }
7515 
7516  void ArrayNew(FullDecoder* decoder, const ArrayIndexImmediate& imm,
7517  const Value& length_value, const Value& initial_value,
7518  Value* result) {
7519  ArrayNew(decoder, imm, true);
7520  }
7521 
7522  void ArrayNewDefault(FullDecoder* decoder, const ArrayIndexImmediate& imm,
7523  const Value& length, Value* result) {
7524  ArrayNew(decoder, imm, false);
7525  }
7526 
7527  void ArrayFill(FullDecoder* decoder, ArrayIndexImmediate& imm,
7528  const Value& array, const Value& /* index */,
7529  const Value& /* value */, const Value& /* length */) {
7530  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
7531  {
7532  // Null check.
7533  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7534  LiftoffRegister array_reg = pinned.set(__ PeekToRegister(3, pinned));
7535  if (null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit) {
7536  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, array_reg.gp(), pinned, array.type);
7537  }
7538 
7539  // Bounds checks.
7540  LiftoffRegister array_length =
7541  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
7542  bool implicit_null_check =
7543  array.type.is_nullable() &&
7544  null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler;
7545  LoadObjectField(decoder, array_length, array_reg.gp(), no_reg,
7546  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kLengthOffset), kI32,
7547  false, implicit_null_check, pinned);
7548  LiftoffRegister index = pinned.set(__ PeekToRegister(2, pinned));
7549  LiftoffRegister length = pinned.set(__ PeekToRegister(0, pinned));
7550  LiftoffRegister index_plus_length =
7551  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
7552  DCHECK(index_plus_length != array_length);
7553  __ emit_i32_add(index_plus_length.gp(), length.gp(), index.gp());
7554  OolTrapLabel trap =
7555  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapArrayOutOfBounds);
7556  __ emit_cond_jump(kUnsignedGreaterThan, trap.label(), kI32,
7557  index_plus_length.gp(), array_length.gp(),
7558  trap.frozen());
7559  // Guard against overflow.
7560  __ emit_cond_jump(kUnsignedGreaterThan, trap.label(), kI32, index.gp(),
7561  index_plus_length.gp(), trap.frozen());
7562  }
7563 
7564  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7565  LiftoffRegister length = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
7566  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7567  LiftoffRegister index = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
7568  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7569 
7570  ArrayFillImpl(decoder, pinned, obj, index, value, length,
7571  imm.array_type->element_type().kind(),
7572  LiftoffAssembler::kNoSkipWriteBarrier);
7573  }
7574 
7575  void ArrayGet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& array_obj,
7576  const ArrayIndexImmediate& imm, const Value& index_val,
7577  bool is_signed, Value* result) {
7578  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7579  LiftoffRegister index = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
7580  LiftoffRegister array = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7581  if (null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit) {
7582  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, array.gp(), pinned, array_obj.type);
7583  }
7584  bool implicit_null_check =
7585  array_obj.type.is_nullable() &&
7586  null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler;
7587  BoundsCheckArray(decoder, implicit_null_check, array, index, pinned);
7588  ValueKind elem_kind = imm.array_type->element_type().kind();
7589  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, elem_kind, "array load")) return;
7590  int elem_size_shift = value_kind_size_log2(elem_kind);
7591  if (elem_size_shift != 0) {
7592  __ emit_i32_shli(index.gp(), index.gp(), elem_size_shift);
7593  }
7594  LiftoffRegister value =
7595  __ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(elem_kind), pinned);
7596  LoadObjectField(decoder, value, array.gp(), index.gp(),
7597  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize),
7598  elem_kind, is_signed, false, pinned);
7599  __ PushRegister(unpacked(elem_kind), value);
7600  }

7602  void ArrayAtomicGet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& array_obj,
7603  const ArrayIndexImmediate& imm, const Value& index_val,
7604  bool is_signed, AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order,
7605  Value* result) {
7606  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7607  LiftoffRegister index = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
7608  LiftoffRegister array = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7609  if (null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit) {
7610  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, array.gp(), pinned, array_obj.type);
7611  }
7612  bool implicit_null_check =
7613  array_obj.type.is_nullable() &&
7614  null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler;
7615  BoundsCheckArray(decoder, implicit_null_check, array, index, pinned);
7616  ValueKind elem_kind = imm.array_type->element_type().kind();
7617  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, elem_kind, "array load")) return;
7618  int elem_size_shift = value_kind_size_log2(elem_kind);
7619  if (elem_size_shift != 0) {
7620  __ emit_i32_shli(index.gp(), index.gp(), elem_size_shift);
7621  }
7622  LiftoffRegister value =
7623  __ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(elem_kind), pinned);
7624  LoadAtomicObjectField(decoder, value, array.gp(), index.gp(),
7625  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize),
7626  elem_kind, is_signed, false, memory_order, pinned);
7627  __ PushRegister(unpacked(elem_kind), value);
7628  }

7630  void ArraySet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& array_obj,
7631  const ArrayIndexImmediate& imm, const Value& index_val,
7632  const Value& value_val) {
7633  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7634  LiftoffRegister value = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7635  DCHECK_EQ(reg_class_for(imm.array_type->element_type().kind()),
7636  value.reg_class());
7637  LiftoffRegister index = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
7638  LiftoffRegister array = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7639  if (null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit) {
7640  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, array.gp(), pinned, array_obj.type);
7641  }
7642  bool implicit_null_check =
7643  array_obj.type.is_nullable() &&
7644  null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler;
7645  BoundsCheckArray(decoder, implicit_null_check, array, index, pinned);
7646  ValueKind elem_kind = imm.array_type->element_type().kind();
7647  int elem_size_shift = value_kind_size_log2(elem_kind);
7648  if (elem_size_shift != 0) {
7649  __ emit_i32_shli(index.gp(), index.gp(), elem_size_shift);
7650  }
7651  StoreObjectField(decoder, array.gp(), index.gp(),
7652  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize),
7653  value, false, pinned, elem_kind);
7654  }

7667  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, array.gp(), pinned, array_obj.type);
7668  }

7670  array_obj.type.is_nullable() &&
7671  null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler;

7683  void ArrayLen(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& array_obj, Value* result) {
7684  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7685  LiftoffRegister obj = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7686  if (null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit) {
7687  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, obj.gp(), pinned, array_obj.type);
7688  }

7690  int kLengthOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kLengthOffset);
7691  bool implicit_null_check =
7692  array_obj.type.is_nullable() &&
7693  null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler;

7695  false /* is_signed */, implicit_null_check, pinned);
7696  __ PushRegister(kI32, len);

7699  void ArrayCopy(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& dst, const Value& dst_index,
7700  const Value& src, const Value& src_index,
7701  const ArrayIndexImmediate& src_imm, const Value& length) {
7702  // TODO(14034): Unify implementation with TF: Implement this with
7703  // GenerateCCallWithStackBuffer. Remove runtime function and builtin in
7704  // wasm.tq.
7705  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmArrayCopy,
7706  MakeSig::Params(kI32, kI32, kI32, kRefNull, kRefNull),
7707  // Builtin parameter order:
7708  // [dst_index, src_index, length, dst, src].
7709  {__ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-4],
7710  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-2],
7711  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1],
7712  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-5],
7713  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-3]},
7714  decoder->position());
7715  __ DropValues(5);
7716  }
7717 
7718  void ArrayNewFixed(FullDecoder* decoder, const ArrayIndexImmediate& array_imm,
7719  const IndexImmediate& length_imm,
7720  const Value* /* elements */, Value* /* result */) {
7721  LiftoffRegister rtt = RttCanon(decoder, array_imm.index, {});
7722  ValueKind elem_kind = array_imm.array_type->element_type().kind();
7723  int32_t elem_count = length_imm.index;
7724  // Allocate the array.
7725  const bool is_shared = decoder->module_->type(array_imm.index).is_shared;
7726  CallBuiltin(is_shared ? Builtin::kWasmAllocateSharedArray_Uninitialized
7727  : Builtin::kWasmAllocateArray_Uninitialized,
7728  MakeSig::Returns(kRef).Params(kRef, kI32, kI32),
7729  {VarState{kRef, rtt, 0}, VarState{kI32, elem_count, 0},
7730  VarState{kI32, value_kind_size(elem_kind), 0}},
7731  decoder->position());
7732 
7733  // Initialize the array with stack arguments.
7734  LiftoffRegister array(kReturnRegister0);
7735  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, elem_kind, "array.new_fixed")) return;
7736  for (int i = elem_count - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
7737  LiftoffRegList pinned{array};
7738  LiftoffRegister element = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
7739  int offset =
7740  WasmArray::kHeaderSize + (i << value_kind_size_log2(elem_kind));
7741  // Skipping the write barrier is safe as long as:
7742  // (1) {array} is freshly allocated, and
7743  // (2) {array} is in new-space (not pretenured).
7744  StoreObjectField(decoder, array.gp(), no_reg,
7745  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(offset), element, false,
7746  pinned, elem_kind,
7747  is_shared ? LiftoffAssembler::kNoSkipWriteBarrier
7748  : LiftoffAssembler::kSkipWriteBarrier);
7749  }
7750 
7751  // Push the array onto the stack.
7752  __ PushRegister(kRef, array);
7753  }
7754 
7755  void ArrayNewSegment(FullDecoder* decoder,
7756  const ArrayIndexImmediate& array_imm,
7757  const IndexImmediate& segment_imm,
7758  const Value& /* offset */, const Value& /* length */,
7759  Value* /* result */) {
7760  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
7761  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7762 
7763  LiftoffRegister rtt =
7764  pinned.set(RttCanon(decoder, array_imm.index, pinned));
7765 
7766  LiftoffRegister is_element_reg =
7767  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
7768  LoadSmi(is_element_reg,
7769  array_imm.array_type->element_type().is_reference());
7770 
7771  LiftoffRegister extract_shared_data_reg =
7772  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
7773  LoadSmi(extract_shared_data_reg, 0);
7774 
7775  CallBuiltin(
7776  Builtin::kWasmArrayNewSegment,
7777  MakeSig::Returns(kRef).Params(kI32, kI32, kI32, kSmiKind, kSmiKind,
7778  kRef),
7779  {
7780  VarState{kI32, static_cast<int>(segment_imm.index), 0}, // segment
7781  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-2], // offset
7782  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1], // length
7783  VarState{kSmiKind, is_element_reg, 0}, // is_element
7784  VarState{kSmiKind, extract_shared_data_reg, 0}, // shared
7785  VarState{kRef, rtt, 0} // rtt
7786  },
7787  decoder->position());
7788 
7789  // Pop parameters from the value stack.
7790  __ DropValues(2);
7791  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
7792 
7793  LiftoffRegister result(kReturnRegister0);
7794  __ PushRegister(kRef, result);
7795  }
7796 
7797  void ArrayInitSegment(FullDecoder* decoder,
7798  const ArrayIndexImmediate& array_imm,
7799  const IndexImmediate& segment_imm,
7800  const Value& /* array */,
7801  const Value& /* array_index */,
7802  const Value& /* segment_offset*/,
7803  const Value& /* length */) {
7804  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
7805  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7806 
7807  LiftoffRegister segment_index_reg =
7808  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
7809  LoadSmi(segment_index_reg, static_cast<int32_t>(segment_imm.index));
7810 
7811  LiftoffRegister is_element_reg =
7812  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
7813  LoadSmi(is_element_reg,
7814  array_imm.array_type->element_type().is_reference());
7815 
7816  LiftoffRegister extract_shared_data_reg =
7817  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
7818  LoadSmi(extract_shared_data_reg, 0);
7819 
7820  // Builtin parameter order: array_index, segment_offset, length,
7821  // segment_index, array.
7822  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmArrayInitSegment,
7823  MakeSig::Params(kI32, kI32, kI32, kSmiKind, kSmiKind, kSmiKind,
7824  kRefNull),
7825  {__ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-3],
7826  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-2],
7827  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1],
7828  VarState{kSmiKind, segment_index_reg, 0},
7829  VarState{kSmiKind, is_element_reg, 0},
7830  VarState{kSmiKind, extract_shared_data_reg, 0},
7831  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-4]},
7832  decoder->position());
7833  __ DropValues(4);
7834  }
7835 
7836  void RefI31(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& input, Value* result) {
7837  LiftoffRegister src = __ PopToRegister();
7838  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {src}, {});
7839  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
7840  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
7841  __ emit_i32_shli(dst.gp(), src.gp(), kSmiTagSize);
7842  } else {
7843  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits());
7844  // Set the topmost bit to sign-extend the second bit. This way,
7845  // interpretation in JS (if this value escapes there) will be the same as
7846  // i31.get_s.
7847  __ emit_i64_shli(dst, src, kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize + 1);
7848  __ emit_i64_sari(dst, dst, 1);
7849  }
7850  __ PushRegister(kRef, dst);
7851  }
7852 
7853  void I31GetS(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& input, Value* result) {
7854  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7855  LiftoffRegister src = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister());
7856  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, src.gp(), pinned, input.type);
7857  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {src}, {});
7858  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
7859  __ emit_i32_sari(dst.gp(), src.gp(), kSmiTagSize);
7860  } else {
7861  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits());
7862  // The topmost bit is already sign-extended.
7863  // Liftoff expects that the upper half of any i32 value in a register
7864  // is zeroed out, not sign-extended from the lower half.
7865  __ emit_i64_shri(dst, src, kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize);
7866  }
7867  __ PushRegister(kI32, dst);
7868  }
7869 
7870  void I31GetU(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& input, Value* result) {
7871  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7872  LiftoffRegister src = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister());
7873  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, src.gp(), pinned, input.type);
7874  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {src}, {});
7875  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
7876  __ emit_i32_shri(dst.gp(), src.gp(), kSmiTagSize);
7877  } else {
7878  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits());
7879  // Remove topmost bit.
7880  __ emit_i64_shli(dst, src, 1);
7881  __ emit_i64_shri(dst, dst, kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize + 1);
7882  }
7883  __ PushRegister(kI32, dst);
7884  }
7885 
7886  void RefGetDesc(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& ref_val, Value* desc_val) {
7887  LiftoffRegList pinned;
7888  LiftoffRegister ref = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister());
7889 
7890  // Implicit null checks don't cover the map load.
7891  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, ref.gp(), pinned, ref_val.type);
7892 
7893  LiftoffRegister value = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
7894  __ LoadMap(value.gp(), ref.gp());
7895  LoadObjectField(
7896  decoder, value, value.gp(), no_reg,
7897  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(Map::kInstanceDescriptorsOffset), kRef,
7898  false, false, pinned);
7899  __ PushRegister(kRef, value);
7900  }
7901 
7902  LiftoffRegister RttCanon(FullDecoder* decoder, ModuleTypeIndex type_index,
7903  LiftoffRegList pinned) {
7904  bool is_shared = decoder->module_->type(type_index).is_shared;
7905  LiftoffRegister rtt = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
7906  if (is_shared) {
7907  LOAD_PROTECTED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(rtt.gp(), SharedPart, pinned);
7908  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_FROM_INSTANCE(rtt.gp(), ManagedObjectMaps, rtt.gp())
7909  } else {
7910  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(rtt.gp(), ManagedObjectMaps, pinned);
7911  }
7912  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
7913  rtt.gp(), rtt.gp(), no_reg,
7914  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(type_index.index));
7915  return rtt;
7916  }
7917 
7918  enum NullSucceeds : bool { // --
7919  kNullSucceeds = true,
7920  kNullFails = false
7921  };
7922 
7923  // Falls through on match (=successful type check).
7924  // Returns the register containing the object.
7925  void SubtypeCheck(const WasmModule* module, Register obj_reg,
7926  ValueType obj_type, Register rtt_reg, HeapType target_type,
7927  Register scratch_null, Register scratch2, Label* no_match,
7928  NullSucceeds null_succeeds,
7929  const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
7930  Label match;
7931  bool is_cast_from_any = obj_type.is_reference_to(HeapType::kAny);
7932 
7933  // Skip the null check if casting from any and not {null_succeeds}.
7934  // In that case the instance type check will identify null as not being a
7935  // wasm object and fail.
7936  if (obj_type.is_nullable() && (!is_cast_from_any || null_succeeds)) {
7937  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, null_succeeds ? &match : no_match,
7938  obj_type.kind(), obj_reg, scratch_null, frozen);
7939  }
7940  Register tmp1 = scratch_null; // Done with null checks.
7941 
7942  // Add Smi check if the source type may store a Smi (i31ref or JS Smi).
7943  if (IsSubtypeOf(kWasmRefI31, obj_type.AsNonShared(), module)) {
7944  __ emit_smi_check(obj_reg, no_match, LiftoffAssembler::kJumpOnSmi,
7945  frozen);
7946  }
7947 
7948  __ LoadMap(tmp1, obj_reg);
7949  // {tmp1} now holds the object's map.
7950 
7951  if (module->type(target_type.ref_index()).is_final ||
7952  target_type.is_exact()) {
7953  // In this case, simply check for map equality.
7954  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, no_match, ValueKind::kRef, tmp1, rtt_reg,
7955  frozen);
7956  } else {
7957  // Check for rtt equality, and if not, check if the rtt is a struct/array
7958  // rtt.
7959  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &match, ValueKind::kRef, tmp1, rtt_reg, frozen);
7960 
7961  if (is_cast_from_any) {
7962  // Check for map being a map for a wasm object (struct, array, func).
7963  __ Load(LiftoffRegister(scratch2), tmp1, no_reg,
7964  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(Map::kInstanceTypeOffset),
7965  LoadType::kI32Load16U);
7966  __ emit_i32_subi(scratch2, scratch2, FIRST_WASM_OBJECT_TYPE);
7967  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedGreaterThan, no_match, scratch2,
7968  LAST_WASM_OBJECT_TYPE - FIRST_WASM_OBJECT_TYPE,
7969  frozen);
7970  }
7971 
7972  // Constant-time subtyping check: load exactly one candidate RTT from the
7973  // supertypes list.
7974  // Step 1: load the WasmTypeInfo into {tmp1}.
7975  constexpr int kTypeInfoOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
7976  Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
7977  __ LoadTaggedPointer(tmp1, tmp1, no_reg, kTypeInfoOffset);
7978  // Step 2: check the list's length if needed.
7979  uint32_t rtt_depth = GetSubtypingDepth(module, target_type.ref_index());
7980  if (rtt_depth >= kMinimumSupertypeArraySize) {
7981  LiftoffRegister list_length(scratch2);
7982  int offset =
7983  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTypeInfo::kSupertypesLengthOffset);
7984  __ LoadSmiAsInt32(list_length, tmp1, offset);
7985  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedLessThanEqual, no_match,
7986  list_length.gp(), rtt_depth, frozen);
7987  }
7988  // Step 3: load the candidate list slot into {tmp1}, and compare it.
7989  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
7990  tmp1, tmp1, no_reg,
7991  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTypeInfo::kSupertypesOffset +
7992  rtt_depth * kTaggedSize));
7993  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, no_match, ValueKind::kRef, tmp1, rtt_reg,
7994  frozen);
7995  }
7996 
7997  // Fall through to {match}.
7998  __ bind(&match);
7999  }
8000 
8001  void RefTest(FullDecoder* decoder, HeapType target_type, const Value& obj,
8002  Value* /* result_val */, bool null_succeeds) {
8003  Label return_false, done;
8004  LiftoffRegList pinned;
8005  LiftoffRegister rtt_reg =
8006  pinned.set(RttCanon(decoder, target_type.ref_index(), pinned));
8007  LiftoffRegister obj_reg = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
8008  Register scratch_null =
8009  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
8010  LiftoffRegister result = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
8011  if (obj.type.is_nullable()) {
8012  LoadNullValueForCompare(scratch_null, pinned, obj.type);
8013  }
8014 
8015  {
8016  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
8017  SubtypeCheck(decoder->module_, obj_reg.gp(), obj.type, rtt_reg.gp(),
8018  target_type, scratch_null, result.gp(), &return_false,
8019  null_succeeds ? kNullSucceeds : kNullFails, frozen);
8020 
8021  __ LoadConstant(result, WasmValue(1));
8022  // TODO(jkummerow): Emit near jumps on platforms that have them.
8023  __ emit_jump(&done);
8024 
8025  __ bind(&return_false);
8026  __ LoadConstant(result, WasmValue(0));
8027  __ bind(&done);
8028  }
8029  __ PushRegister(kI32, result);
8030  }
8031 
8032  void CallBuiltinUnsharedTestFromAny(FullDecoder* decoder, Builtin builtin,
8033  bool null_succeeds) {
8034  LiftoffRegister null_succeeds_reg = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {});
8035  __ LoadConstant(null_succeeds_reg, WasmValue{int32_t{null_succeeds}});
8036  CallBuiltin(builtin, MakeSig::Returns(kI32).Params(kRefNull, kI32),
8037  {
8038  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1],
8039  VarState{kI32, null_succeeds_reg, 0},
8040  },
8041  decoder->position());
8042  __ DropValues(1);
8043  __ PushRegister(kI32, LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0));
8044  }
