8046  void RefTestAbstract(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& obj, HeapType type,
8047  Value* result_val, bool null_succeeds) {
8048  switch (type.representation()) {
8049  case HeapType::kEq:
8050  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_shared &&
8051  obj.type.heap_representation() == wasm::HeapType::kAny) {
8052  return CallBuiltinUnsharedTestFromAny(
8053  decoder, Builtin::kWasmLiftoffIsEqRefUnshared, null_succeeds);
8054  }
8055  [[fallthrough]];
8056  case HeapType::kEqShared:
8057  return AbstractTypeCheck<&LiftoffCompiler::EqCheck>(decoder, obj,
8058  null_succeeds);
8059  case HeapType::kI31:
8060  case HeapType::kI31Shared:
8061  return AbstractTypeCheck<&LiftoffCompiler::I31Check>(decoder, obj,
8062  null_succeeds);
8063  case HeapType::kStruct:
8064  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_shared &&
8065  obj.type.heap_representation() == wasm::HeapType::kAny) {
8066  return CallBuiltinUnsharedTestFromAny(
8067  decoder, Builtin::kWasmLiftoffIsStructRefUnshared, null_succeeds);
8068  }
8069  [[fallthrough]];
8070  case HeapType::kStructShared:
8071  return AbstractTypeCheck<&LiftoffCompiler::StructCheck>(decoder, obj,
8072  null_succeeds);
8073  case HeapType::kArray:
8074  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_shared &&
8075  obj.type.heap_representation() == wasm::HeapType::kAny) {
8076  return CallBuiltinUnsharedTestFromAny(
8077  decoder, Builtin::kWasmLiftoffIsArrayRefUnshared, null_succeeds);
8078  }
8079  [[fallthrough]];
8080  case HeapType::kArrayShared:
8081  return AbstractTypeCheck<&LiftoffCompiler::ArrayCheck>(decoder, obj,
8082  null_succeeds);
8083  case HeapType::kString:
8084  return AbstractTypeCheck<&LiftoffCompiler::StringCheck>(decoder, obj,
8085  null_succeeds);
8086  case HeapType::kNone:
8087  case HeapType::kNoExtern:
8088  case HeapType::kNoFunc:
8089  case HeapType::kNoExn:
8090  case HeapType::kNoneShared:
8091  case HeapType::kNoExternShared:
8092  case HeapType::kNoFuncShared:
8093  case HeapType::kNoExnShared:
8094  DCHECK(null_succeeds);
8095  return EmitIsNull(kExprRefIsNull, obj.type);
8096  case HeapType::kAny:
8097  case HeapType::kAnyShared:
8098  // Any may never need a cast as it is either implicitly convertible or
8099  // never convertible for any given type.
8100  default:
8101  UNREACHABLE();
8102  }
8103  }

8105  void RefCast(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& obj, Value* result) {
8106  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_assume_ref_cast_succeeds) return;
8107  LiftoffRegister rtt = RttCanon(decoder, result->type.ref_index(), {});
8108  return RefCastImpl(decoder, result->type, obj, rtt);
8109  }
8110 
8111  void RefCastDesc(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& obj, const Value& desc,
8112  Value* result) {
8113  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_assume_ref_cast_succeeds) {
8114  __ DropValues(1); // Drop the descriptor, pretend it was consumed.
8115  return;
8116  }
8117  LiftoffRegister rtt = GetRttFromDescriptorOnStack(decoder, desc);
8118  // Pretending that the target type is exact skips the supertype check.
8119  return RefCastImpl(decoder, result->type.AsExact(), obj, rtt);
8120  }
8121 
8122  void RefCastImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, ValueType target_type,
8123  const Value& obj, LiftoffRegister rtt) {
8124  LiftoffRegList pinned{rtt};
8125  LiftoffRegister obj_reg = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
8126  Register scratch_null =
8127  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
8128  Register scratch2 = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
8129  if (obj.type.is_nullable()) {
8130  LoadNullValueForCompare(scratch_null, pinned, obj.type);
8131  }
8132 
8133  {
8134  NullSucceeds on_null =
8135  target_type.is_nullable() ? kNullSucceeds : kNullFails;
8136  OolTrapLabel trap =
8137  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapIllegalCast);
8138  SubtypeCheck(decoder->module_, obj_reg.gp(), obj.type, rtt.gp(),
8139  target_type.heap_type(), scratch_null, scratch2,
8140  trap.label(), on_null, trap.frozen());
8141  }
8142  __ PushRegister(obj.type.kind(), obj_reg);
8143  }

8148  __ LoadConstant(null_succeeds_reg, WasmValue{int32_t{null_succeeds}});
8149  CallBuiltin(builtin, MakeSig::Returns(kI32).Params(kRefNull, kI32),
8150  {
8151  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1],
8152  VarState{kI32, null_succeeds_reg, 0},
8153  },
8154  decoder->position());
8155  }

8166  [[fallthrough]];
8167  case HeapType::kEqShared:
8168  return AbstractTypeCast<&LiftoffCompiler::EqCheck>(obj, decoder,
8169  null_succeeds);
8170  case HeapType::kI31:
8171  case HeapType::kI31Shared:
8172  return AbstractTypeCast<&LiftoffCompiler::I31Check>(obj, decoder,
8173  null_succeeds);
8174  case HeapType::kStruct:
8175  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_shared &&
8176  obj.type.heap_representation() == wasm::HeapType::kAny) {
8177  return CallBuiltinUnsharedCastFromAny(
8178  decoder, Builtin::kWasmLiftoffCastStructRefUnshared,
8179  null_succeeds);
8180  }
8181  [[fallthrough]];
8182  case HeapType::kStructShared:
8183  return AbstractTypeCast<&LiftoffCompiler::StructCheck>(obj, decoder,
8184  null_succeeds);
8185  case HeapType::kArray:
8186  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_shared &&
8187  obj.type.heap_representation() == wasm::HeapType::kAny) {
8188  return CallBuiltinUnsharedCastFromAny(

8190  null_succeeds);

8194  return AbstractTypeCast<&LiftoffCompiler::ArrayCheck>(obj, decoder,
8195  null_succeeds);
8196  case HeapType::kString:
8197  return AbstractTypeCast<&LiftoffCompiler::StringCheck>(obj, decoder,
8198  null_succeeds);
8199  case HeapType::kNone:
8200  case HeapType::kNoExtern:
8201  case HeapType::kNoFunc:
8202  case HeapType::kNoExn:
8203  case HeapType::kNoneShared:
8204  case HeapType::kNoExternShared:
8205  case HeapType::kNoFuncShared:
8206  case HeapType::kNoExnShared:
8207  DCHECK(null_succeeds);
8208  return AssertNullTypecheck(decoder, obj, result_val);
8209  case HeapType::kAny:
8210  case HeapType::kAnyShared:
8211  // Any may never need a cast as it is either implicitly convertible or
8212  // never convertible for any given type.
8213  default:
8214  UNREACHABLE();

8218  void BrOnCast(FullDecoder* decoder, HeapType target_type, const Value& obj,
8219  Value* /* result_on_branch */, uint32_t depth,
8220  bool null_succeeds) {

8222  return BrOnCastImpl(decoder, target_type, obj, rtt, depth, null_succeeds);

8225  void BrOnCastDesc(FullDecoder* decoder, HeapType target_type,
8226  const Value& obj, const Value& descriptor,
8227  Value* /* result_on_branch */, uint32_t depth,
8228  bool null_succeeds) {
8229  LiftoffRegister rtt = GetRttFromDescriptorOnStack(decoder, descriptor);
8230  // Pretending that the target type is exact skips the supertype check.
8231  return BrOnCastImpl(decoder, target_type.AsExact(), obj, rtt, depth,
8232  null_succeeds);
8233  }
8234  void BrOnCastImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, HeapType target_type,
8235  const Value& obj, LiftoffRegister rtt, uint32_t depth,
8236  bool null_succeeds) {
8237  LiftoffRegList pinned{rtt};
8238  // Avoid having sequences of branches do duplicate work.
8239  if (depth != decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
8240  __ PrepareForBranch(decoder->control_at(depth)->br_merge()->arity,
8241  pinned);
8242  }
8243 
8244  Label cont_false;
8245  LiftoffRegister obj_reg = pinned.set(__ PeekToRegister(0, pinned));
8246  Register scratch_null =
8247  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
8248  Register scratch2 = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
8249  if (obj.type.is_nullable()) {
8250  LoadNullValue(scratch_null, kWasmAnyRef);
8251  }
8252  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
8253 
8254  NullSucceeds null_handling = null_succeeds ? kNullSucceeds : kNullFails;
8255  SubtypeCheck(decoder->module_, obj_reg.gp(), obj.type, rtt.gp(),
8256  target_type, scratch_null, scratch2, &cont_false,
8257  null_handling, frozen);
8258 
8259  BrOrRet(decoder, depth);
8260 
8261  __ bind(&cont_false);
8262  }

8269  null_succeeds);

8282  void BrOnCastFailImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, HeapType target_type,
8283  const Value& obj, LiftoffRegister rtt, uint32_t depth,
8284  bool null_succeeds) {
8285  LiftoffRegList pinned{rtt};
8286  // Avoid having sequences of branches do duplicate work.
8287  if (depth != decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
8288  __ PrepareForBranch(decoder->control_at(depth)->br_merge()->arity,
8289  pinned);
8290  }
8291 
8292  Label cont_branch, fallthrough;
8293 
8294  LiftoffRegister obj_reg = pinned.set(__ PeekToRegister(0, pinned));
8295  Register scratch_null =
8296  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
8297  Register scratch2 = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
8298  if (obj.type.is_nullable()) {
8299  LoadNullValue(scratch_null, kWasmAnyRef);
8300  }
8301  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
8302 
8303  NullSucceeds null_handling = null_succeeds ? kNullSucceeds : kNullFails;
8304  SubtypeCheck(decoder->module_, obj_reg.gp(), obj.type, rtt.gp(),
8305  target_type, scratch_null, scratch2, &cont_branch,
8306  null_handling, frozen);
8307  __ emit_jump(&fallthrough);
8308 
8309  __ bind(&cont_branch);
8310  BrOrRet(decoder, depth);
8311 
8312  __ bind(&fallthrough);
8313  }

8315  void BrOnCastAbstractFromAnyRejectShared(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t depth,
8316  bool null_succeeds, Builtin builtin,
8317  bool inverted) {
8318  // Avoid having sequences of branches do duplicate work.
8319  if (depth != decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
8320  __ PrepareForBranch(decoder->control_at(depth)->br_merge()->arity, {});
8321  }
8322 
8323  LiftoffRegister null_succeeds_reg = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {});
8324  __ LoadConstant(null_succeeds_reg, WasmValue{int32_t{null_succeeds}});
8325  CallBuiltin(builtin, MakeSig::Returns(kI32).Params(kRefNull, kI32),
8326  {
8327  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1],
8328  VarState{kI32, null_succeeds_reg, 0},
8329  },
8330  decoder->position());
8331  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
8332  Label no_match;
8333  __ emit_cond_jump(inverted ? kNotZero : kZero, &no_match, kI32,
8334  kReturnRegister0, no_reg, frozen);
8335  BrOrRet(decoder, depth);
8336  __ bind(&no_match);
8337  }

8339  void BrOnCastAbstract(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& obj, HeapType type,
8340  Value* result_on_branch, uint32_t depth,
8341  bool null_succeeds) {
8342  switch (type.representation()) {
8343  case HeapType::kEq:

8357  null_succeeds);
8358  case HeapType::kStruct:

8364  }
8365  [[fallthrough]];
8366  case HeapType::kStructShared:
8367  return BrOnAbstractType<&LiftoffCompiler::StructCheck>(
8368  obj, decoder, depth, null_succeeds);
8369  case HeapType::kArray:
8370  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_shared &&
8371  obj.type.heap_representation() == wasm::HeapType::kAny) {
8372  return BrOnCastAbstractFromAnyRejectShared(
8373  decoder, depth, null_succeeds,

8376  [[fallthrough]];
8377  case HeapType::kArrayShared:
8378  return BrOnAbstractType<&LiftoffCompiler::ArrayCheck>(
8379  obj, decoder, depth, null_succeeds);
8380  case HeapType::kString:
8381  return BrOnAbstractType<&LiftoffCompiler::StringCheck>(

8383  case HeapType::kNone:
8384  case HeapType::kNoExtern:
8385  case HeapType::kNoFunc:
8386  case HeapType::kNoExn:
8387  case HeapType::kNoneShared:
8388  case HeapType::kNoExternShared:
8389  case HeapType::kNoFuncShared:
8390  case HeapType::kNoExnShared:
8391  DCHECK(null_succeeds);
8392  return BrOnNull(decoder, obj, depth, /*pass_null_along_branch*/ true,
8393  nullptr);
8394  case HeapType::kAny:
8395  case HeapType::kAnyShared:
8396  // Any may never need a cast as it is either implicitly convertible or
8397  // never convertible for any given type.
8398  default:
8399  UNREACHABLE();
8400  }

8403  void BrOnCastFailAbstract(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& obj,
8404  HeapType type, Value* result_on_fallthrough,
8405  uint32_t depth, bool null_succeeds) {
8406  switch (type.representation()) {
8407  case HeapType::kEq:
8408  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_shared &&
8409  obj.type.heap_representation() == wasm::HeapType::kAny) {
8410  return BrOnCastAbstractFromAnyRejectShared(

8414  [[fallthrough]];
8415  case HeapType::kEqShared:
8416  return BrOnNonAbstractType<&LiftoffCompiler::EqCheck>(
8417  obj, decoder, depth, null_succeeds);
8418  case HeapType::kI31:
8419  case HeapType::kI31Shared:
8420  return BrOnNonAbstractType<&LiftoffCompiler::I31Check>(
8421  obj, decoder, depth, null_succeeds);
8422  case HeapType::kStruct:
8423  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_shared &&
8424  obj.type.heap_representation() == wasm::HeapType::kAny) {
8425  return BrOnCastAbstractFromAnyRejectShared(
8426  decoder, depth, null_succeeds,
8427  Builtin::kWasmLiftoffIsStructRefUnshared, true);
8428  }
8429  [[fallthrough]];
8430  case HeapType::kStructShared:
8431  return BrOnNonAbstractType<&LiftoffCompiler::StructCheck>(
8432  obj, decoder, depth, null_succeeds);
8433  case HeapType::kArray:
8434  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_shared &&
8435  obj.type.heap_representation() == wasm::HeapType::kAny) {
8436  return BrOnCastAbstractFromAnyRejectShared(
8437  decoder, depth, null_succeeds,
8438  Builtin::kWasmLiftoffIsArrayRefUnshared, true);
8439  }
8440  [[fallthrough]];
8441  case HeapType::kArrayShared:
8442  return BrOnNonAbstractType<&LiftoffCompiler::ArrayCheck>(
8443  obj, decoder, depth, null_succeeds);
8444  case HeapType::kString:
8445  return BrOnNonAbstractType<&LiftoffCompiler::StringCheck>(
8446  obj, decoder, depth, null_succeeds);
8447  case HeapType::kNone:
8448  case HeapType::kNoExtern:
8449  case HeapType::kNoFunc:
8450  case HeapType::kNoExn:
8451  case HeapType::kNoneShared:
8452  case HeapType::kNoExternShared:
8453  case HeapType::kNoFuncShared:
8454  case HeapType::kNoExnShared:
8455  DCHECK(null_succeeds);
8456  return BrOnNonNull(decoder, obj, nullptr, depth,
8457  /*drop_null_on_fallthrough*/ false);
8458  case HeapType::kAny:
8459  case HeapType::kAnyShared:
8460  // Any may never need a cast as it is either implicitly convertible or
8461  // never convertible for any given type.
8462  default:
8463  UNREACHABLE();
8464  }
8465  }
8466 
8467  struct TypeCheck {
8468  Register obj_reg = no_reg;
8469  ValueType obj_type;
8470  Register tmp = no_reg;
8471  Label* no_match;
8472  Builtin no_match_trap;
8473  std::optional<OolTrapLabel> trap;
8474  bool null_succeeds;
8475 
8476  TypeCheck(ValueType obj_type, Label* no_match, bool null_succeeds,
8477  Builtin no_match_trap = Builtin::kNoBuiltinId)
8478  : obj_type(obj_type),
8479  no_match(no_match),
8480  no_match_trap(no_match_trap),
8481  null_succeeds(null_succeeds) {
8482  // Either a non-trapping no_match label needs to be provided or a builtin
8483  // to trap with in case the type check fails.
8484  DCHECK_NE(no_match == nullptr, no_match_trap == Builtin::kNoBuiltinId);
8485  }
8486 
8487  Register null_reg() { return tmp; } // After {Initialize}.
8488  Register instance_type() { return tmp; } // After {LoadInstanceType}.
8489  };
8490 
8491  enum PopOrPeek { kPop, kPeek };
8492 
8493  void Initialize(TypeCheck& check, FullDecoder* decoder, PopOrPeek pop_or_peek,
8494  ValueType type) {
8495  LiftoffRegList pinned;
8496  if (pop_or_peek == kPop) {
8497  check.obj_reg = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned)).gp();
8498  } else {
8499  check.obj_reg = pinned.set(__ PeekToRegister(0, pinned)).gp();
8500  }
8501  check.tmp = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
8502  if (check.obj_type.is_nullable()) {
8503  LoadNullValue(check.null_reg(), type);
8504  }
8505  if (check.no_match == nullptr) {
8506  check.trap.emplace(AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, check.no_match_trap));
8507  check.no_match = check.trap->label();
8508  }
8509  }
8510  void LoadInstanceType(TypeCheck& check, const FreezeCacheState& frozen,
8511  Label* on_smi) {
8512  // The check for null_succeeds == true has to be handled by the caller!
8513  // TODO(mliedtke): Reiterate the null_succeeds case once all generic cast
8514  // instructions are implemented.
8515  if (!check.null_succeeds && check.obj_type.is_nullable()) {
8516  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, check.no_match, kRefNull, check.obj_reg,
8517  check.null_reg(), frozen);
8518  }
8519  __ emit_smi_check(check.obj_reg, on_smi, LiftoffAssembler::kJumpOnSmi,
8520  frozen);
8521  __ LoadMap(check.instance_type(), check.obj_reg);
8522  __ Load(LiftoffRegister(check.instance_type()), check.instance_type(),
8523  no_reg, wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(Map::kInstanceTypeOffset),
8524  LoadType::kI32Load16U);
8525  }
8526 
8527  // Abstract type checkers. They all fall through on match.
8528  void StructCheck(TypeCheck& check, const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
8529  LoadInstanceType(check, frozen, check.no_match);
8530  LiftoffRegister instance_type(check.instance_type());
8531  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kNotEqual, check.no_match, check.instance_type(),
8532  WASM_STRUCT_TYPE, frozen);
8533  }
8534 
8535  void ArrayCheck(TypeCheck& check, const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
8536  LoadInstanceType(check, frozen, check.no_match);
8537  LiftoffRegister instance_type(check.instance_type());
8538  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kNotEqual, check.no_match, check.instance_type(),
8539  WASM_ARRAY_TYPE, frozen);
8540  }
8541 
8542  void I31Check(TypeCheck& check, const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
8543  __ emit_smi_check(check.obj_reg, check.no_match,
8544  LiftoffAssembler::kJumpOnNotSmi, frozen);
8545  }
8546 
8547  void EqCheck(TypeCheck& check, const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
8548  Label match;
8549  LoadInstanceType(check, frozen, &match);
8550  // We're going to test a range of WasmObject instance types with a single
8551  // unsigned comparison.
8552  Register tmp = check.instance_type();
8553  __ emit_i32_subi(tmp, tmp, FIRST_WASM_OBJECT_TYPE);
8554  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedGreaterThan, check.no_match, tmp,
8555  LAST_WASM_OBJECT_TYPE - FIRST_WASM_OBJECT_TYPE,
8556  frozen);
8557  __ bind(&match);
8558  }
8559 
8560  void StringCheck(TypeCheck& check, const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
8561  LoadInstanceType(check, frozen, check.no_match);
8562  LiftoffRegister instance_type(check.instance_type());
8563  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, check.no_match,
8564  check.instance_type(), FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE, frozen);
8565  }
8566 
8567  using TypeChecker = void (LiftoffCompiler::*)(TypeCheck& check,
8568  const FreezeCacheState& frozen);
8569 
8570  template <TypeChecker type_checker>
8571  void AbstractTypeCheck(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& object,
8572  bool null_succeeds) {
8573  Label match, no_match, done;
8574  TypeCheck check(object.type, &no_match, null_succeeds);
8575  Initialize(check, decoder, kPop, object.type);
8576  LiftoffRegister result(check.tmp);
8577  {
8578  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
8579 
8580  if (null_succeeds && check.obj_type.is_nullable()) {
8581  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &match, kRefNull, check.obj_reg,
8582  check.null_reg(), frozen);
8583  }
8584 
8585  (this->*type_checker)(check, frozen);
8586 
8587  __ bind(&match);
8588  __ LoadConstant(result, WasmValue(1));
8589  // TODO(jkummerow): Emit near jumps on platforms that have them.
8590  __ emit_jump(&done);
8591 
8592  __ bind(&no_match);
8593  __ LoadConstant(result, WasmValue(0));
8594  __ bind(&done);
8595  }
8596  __ PushRegister(kI32, result);
8597  }
8598 
8599  template <TypeChecker type_checker>
8600  void AbstractTypeCast(const Value& object, FullDecoder* decoder,
8601  bool null_succeeds) {
8602  Label match;
8603  TypeCheck check(object.type, nullptr, null_succeeds,
8604  Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapIllegalCast);
8605  Initialize(check, decoder, kPeek, object.type);
8606  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
8607 
8608  if (null_succeeds && check.obj_type.is_nullable()) {
8609  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &match, kRefNull, check.obj_reg,
8610  check.null_reg(), frozen);
8611  }
8612  (this->*type_checker)(check, frozen);
8613  __ bind(&match);
8614  }
8615 
8616  template <TypeChecker type_checker>
8617  void BrOnAbstractType(const Value& object, FullDecoder* decoder,
8618  uint32_t br_depth, bool null_succeeds) {
8619  // Avoid having sequences of branches do duplicate work.
8620  if (br_depth != decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
8621  __ PrepareForBranch(decoder->control_at(br_depth)->br_merge()->arity, {});
8622  }
8623 
8624  Label no_match, match;
8625  TypeCheck check(object.type, &no_match, null_succeeds);
8626  Initialize(check, decoder, kPeek, object.type);
8627  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
8628 
8629  if (null_succeeds && check.obj_type.is_nullable()) {
8630  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &match, kRefNull, check.obj_reg,
8631  check.null_reg(), frozen);
8632  }
8633 
8634  (this->*type_checker)(check, frozen);
8635  __ bind(&match);
8636  BrOrRet(decoder, br_depth);
8637 
8638  __ bind(&no_match);
8639  }
8640 
8641  template <TypeChecker type_checker>
8642  void BrOnNonAbstractType(const Value& object, FullDecoder* decoder,
8643  uint32_t br_depth, bool null_succeeds) {
8644  // Avoid having sequences of branches do duplicate work.
8645  if (br_depth != decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
8646  __ PrepareForBranch(decoder->control_at(br_depth)->br_merge()->arity, {});
8647  }
8648 
8649  Label no_match, end;
8650  TypeCheck check(object.type, &no_match, null_succeeds);
8651  Initialize(check, decoder, kPeek, object.type);
8652  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
8653 
8654  if (null_succeeds && check.obj_type.is_nullable()) {
8655  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &end, kRefNull, check.obj_reg, check.null_reg(),
8656  frozen);
8657  }
8658 
8659  (this->*type_checker)(check, frozen);
8660  __ emit_jump(&end);
8661 
8662  __ bind(&no_match);
8663  BrOrRet(decoder, br_depth);
8664 
8665  __ bind(&end);
8666  }

8668  void StringNewWtf8(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryIndexImmediate& imm,
8669  const unibrow::Utf8Variant variant, const Value& offset,
8670  const Value& size, Value* result) {
8671  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
8672  LiftoffRegList pinned;
8673 
8674  VarState memory_var{kI32, static_cast<int>(imm.index), 0};
8675 
8676  LiftoffRegister variant_reg =
8677  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
8678  LoadSmi(variant_reg, static_cast<int32_t>(variant));
8679  VarState variant_var(kSmiKind, variant_reg, 0);
8680 
8681  VarState& size_var = __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1];
8682 
8683  DCHECK(MatchingMemType(imm.memory, 1));
8684  VarState address = IndexToVarStateSaturating(1, &pinned);
8685 
8686  CallBuiltin(
8687  Builtin::kWasmStringNewWtf8,
8688  MakeSig::Returns(kRefNull).Params(kIntPtrKind, kI32, kI32, kSmiKind),
8689  {address, size_var, memory_var, variant_var}, decoder->position());
8690  __ DropValues(2);
8691  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
8692 
8693  LiftoffRegister result_reg(kReturnRegister0);
8694  __ PushRegister(kRef, result_reg);
8695  }

8697  void StringNewWtf8Array(FullDecoder* decoder,
8698  const unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
8699  const Value& array, const Value& start,
8700  const Value& end, Value* result) {
8701  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
8702  LiftoffRegList pinned;
8703 
8704  LiftoffRegister array_reg = pinned.set(
8705  __ LoadToRegister(__ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-3], pinned));
8706  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, array_reg.gp(), pinned, array.type);
8707  VarState array_var(kRef, array_reg, 0);
8708 
8709  LiftoffRegister variant_reg =
8710  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
8711  LoadSmi(variant_reg, static_cast<int32_t>(variant));
8712  VarState variant_var(kSmiKind, variant_reg, 0);
8713 
8714  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmStringNewWtf8Array,
8715  MakeSig::Returns(kRefNull).Params(kI32, kI32, kRef, kSmiKind),
8716  {
8717  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-2], // start
8718  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1], // end
8719  array_var,
8720  variant_var,
8721  },
8722  decoder->position());
8723  __ cache_state()->stack_state.pop_back(3);
8724  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
8725 
8726  LiftoffRegister result_reg(kReturnRegister0);
8727  __ PushRegister(kRef, result_reg);
8728  }

8790  void StringMeasureWtf8(FullDecoder* decoder,
8791  const unibrow::Utf8Variant variant, const Value& str,
8792  Value* result) {
8793  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
8794  LiftoffRegList pinned;
8795  LiftoffRegister string_reg = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
8796  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, string_reg.gp(), pinned, str.type);
8797  VarState string_var(kRef, string_reg, 0);
8798 
8799  Builtin builtin;
8800  switch (variant) {
8801  case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8:
8802  builtin = Builtin::kWasmStringMeasureUtf8;
8803  break;
8804  case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8:
8805  case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8:
8806  builtin = Builtin::kWasmStringMeasureWtf8;
8807  break;
8808  case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap:
8809  UNREACHABLE();
8810  }
8811  CallBuiltin(builtin, MakeSig::Returns(kI32).Params(kRef),
8812  {
8813  string_var,
8814  },
8815  decoder->position());
8816  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
8817 
8818  LiftoffRegister result_reg(kReturnRegister0);
8819  __ PushRegister(kI32, result_reg);
8820  }

8826  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, string_reg.gp(), pinned, str.type);
8827  LiftoffRegister value = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
8828  LoadObjectField(decoder, value, string_reg.gp(), no_reg,
8829  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
8830  compiler::AccessBuilder::ForStringLength().offset),
8831  ValueKind::kI32, false /* is_signed */,
8832  false /* trapping */, pinned);
8833  __ PushRegister(kI32, value);
8834  }

8953  },

8955  __ DropValues(3);
8956  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
8957 
8958  LiftoffRegister result_reg(kReturnRegister0);
8959  __ PushRegister(kI32, result_reg);
8960  }

8962  void StringConcat(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& head, const Value& tail,
8963  Value* result) {
8964  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION; // Fast, but may create very long strings.
8965  LiftoffRegList pinned;
8966 
8967  LiftoffRegister tail_reg = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
8968  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, tail_reg.gp(), pinned, tail.type);
8969  VarState tail_var(kRef, tail_reg, 0);
8970 
8971  LiftoffRegister head_reg = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
8972  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, head_reg.gp(), pinned, head.type);
8973  VarState head_var(kRef, head_reg, 0);
8974 
8975  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmStringConcat,
8976  MakeSig::Returns(kRef).Params(kRef, kRef),
8977  {
8978  head_var,
8979  tail_var,
8980  },
8981  decoder->position());
8982  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
8983 
8984  LiftoffRegister result_reg(kReturnRegister0);
8985  __ PushRegister(kRef, result_reg);
8986  }
8987 
8988  void StringEq(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& a, const Value& b,
8989  Value* result) {
8990  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION; // Slow path is linear in string length.
8991  LiftoffRegister result_reg(kReturnRegister0);
8992  LiftoffRegList pinned{result_reg};
8993  LiftoffRegister b_reg = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
8994  LiftoffRegister a_reg = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
8995 
8996  __ SpillAllRegisters();
8997 
8998  Label done;
8999 
9000  {
9001  LiftoffRegister null = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
9002  bool check_for_null = a.type.is_nullable() || b.type.is_nullable();
9003  if (check_for_null) {
9004  LoadNullValueForCompare(null.gp(), pinned, kWasmStringRef);
9005  }
9006 
9007  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
9008 
9009  // If values pointer-equal, result is 1.
9010  __ LoadConstant(result_reg, WasmValue(int32_t{1}));
9011  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &done, kRefNull, a_reg.gp(), b_reg.gp(),
9012  frozen);
9013 
9014  // Otherwise if either operand is null, result is 0.
9015  if (check_for_null) {
9016  __ LoadConstant(result_reg, WasmValue(int32_t{0}));
9017  if (a.type.is_nullable()) {
9018  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &done, kRefNull, a_reg.gp(), null.gp(),
9019  frozen);
9020  }
9021  if (b.type.is_nullable()) {
9022  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &done, kRefNull, b_reg.gp(), null.gp(),
9023  frozen);
9024  }
9025  }
9026 
9027  // Ending the frozen state here is fine, because we already spilled the
9028  // rest of the cache, and the subsequent runtime call will reset the cache
9029  // state anyway.
9030  }
9031 
9032  // Operands are pointer-distinct and neither is null; call out to the
9033  // runtime.
9034  VarState a_var(kRef, a_reg, 0);
9035  VarState b_var(kRef, b_reg, 0);
9036  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmStringEqual,
9037  MakeSig::Returns(kI32).Params(kRef, kRef),
9038  {
9039  a_var,
9040  b_var,
9041  },
9042  decoder->position());
9043  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
9044 
9045  __ bind(&done);
9046 
9047  __ PushRegister(kI32, result_reg);
9048  }
9049

9119  void StringViewWtf8Encode(FullDecoder* decoder,
9120  const MemoryIndexImmediate& imm,
9121  const unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
9122  const Value& view, const Value& addr,
9123  const Value& pos, const Value& bytes,
9124  Value* next_pos, Value* bytes_written) {
9125  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;

9127 
9128  VarState& bytes_var = __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-1];
9129  VarState& pos_var = __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-2];
9130 
9131  DCHECK(MatchingMemType(imm.memory, 2));
9132  VarState addr_var = IndexToVarStateSaturating(2, &pinned);
9133 
9134  LiftoffRegister view_reg = pinned.set(
9135  __ LoadToRegister(__ cache_state()->stack_state.end()[-4], pinned));
9136  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, view_reg.gp(), pinned, view.type);
9137  VarState view_var(kRef, view_reg, 0);

9140  // directly; avoid requesting a register.

9142  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
9143  LoadSmi(memory_reg, imm.index);
9144  VarState memory_var(kSmiKind, memory_reg, 0);

9147  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));

9154  .Params(kIntPtrKind, kI32, kI32, kRef, kSmiKind, kSmiKind),
9155  {addr_var, pos_var, bytes_var, view_var, memory_var, variant_var},
9156  decoder->position());
9157  __ DropValues(4);
9158  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
9159 
9160  LiftoffRegister next_pos_reg(kReturnRegister0);
9161  __ PushRegister(kI32, next_pos_reg);
9162  LiftoffRegister bytes_written_reg(kReturnRegister1);
9163  __ PushRegister(kI32, bytes_written_reg);

9466 
9467  private:
9468  void CallDirect(FullDecoder* decoder, const CallFunctionImmediate& imm,
9469  const Value args[], Value returns[],
9470  CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
9471  MostlySmallValueKindSig sig(zone_, imm.sig);
9472  for (ValueKind ret : sig.returns()) {
9473  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, ret, "return")) return;
9474  }
9475 
9476  bool needs_indirect_call = imm.index < env_->module->num_imported_functions;
9477  auto call_descriptor = compiler::GetWasmCallDescriptor(
9478  zone_, imm.sig,
9479  needs_indirect_call ? compiler::kWasmIndirectFunction
9480  : compiler::kWasmFunction);
9481  call_descriptor = GetLoweredCallDescriptor(zone_, call_descriptor);
9482 
9483  // One slot would be enough for call_direct, but would make index
9484  // computations much more complicated.
9485  size_t vector_slot = encountered_call_instructions_.size() * 2;
9486  if (v8_flags.wasm_inlining) {
9487  encountered_call_instructions_.push_back(imm.index);
9488  }
9489 
9490  if (needs_indirect_call) {
9491  // A direct call to an imported function.
9492  FUZZER_HEAVY_INSTRUCTION;
9493  LiftoffRegList pinned;
9494  Register implicit_arg =
9495  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
9496  Register target = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
9497 
9498  {
9499  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("Load ref and target for imported function");
9500  Register dispatch_table = target;
9501  LOAD_PROTECTED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(dispatch_table,
9502  DispatchTableForImports, pinned);
9503  __ LoadProtectedPointer(
9504  implicit_arg, dispatch_table,
9505  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmDispatchTable::OffsetOf(imm.index) +
9506  WasmDispatchTable::kImplicitArgBias));
9507 
9508  __ LoadCodePointer(
9509  target, dispatch_table,
9510  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmDispatchTable::OffsetOf(imm.index) +
9511  WasmDispatchTable::kTargetBias));
9512  }
9513 
9514  __ PrepareCall(&sig, call_descriptor, &target, implicit_arg);
9515  if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
9516  __ PrepareTailCall(
9517  static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount()),
9518  static_cast<int>(
9519  call_descriptor->GetStackParameterDelta(descriptor_)));
9520  __ TailCallIndirect(call_descriptor, target);
9521  } else {
9522  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
9523  __ pc_offset(), SourcePosition(decoder->position()), true);
9524  __ CallIndirect(&sig, call_descriptor, target);
9525  FinishCall(decoder, &sig, call_descriptor);
9526  }
9527  } else {
9528  // Update call counts for inlining.
9529  if (v8_flags.wasm_inlining) {
9530  LiftoffRegister vector = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {});
9531  __ Fill(vector, WasmLiftoffFrameConstants::kFeedbackVectorOffset,
9532  kIntPtrKind);
9533  __ IncrementSmi(vector,
9534  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(
9535  static_cast<int>(vector_slot)));
9536  // Warning: {vector} may be clobbered by {IncrementSmi}!
9537  }
9538  // A direct call within this module just gets the current instance.
9539  __ PrepareCall(&sig, call_descriptor);
9540  // Just encode the function index. This will be patched at instantiation.
9541  Address addr = static_cast<Address>(imm.index);
9542  if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
9543  DCHECK(descriptor_->CanTailCall(call_descriptor));
9544  __ PrepareTailCall(
9545  static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount()),
9546  static_cast<int>(
9547  call_descriptor->GetStackParameterDelta(descriptor_)));
9548  __ TailCallNativeWasmCode(addr);
9549  } else {
9550  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
9551  __ pc_offset(), SourcePosition(decoder->position()), true);
9552  __ CallNativeWasmCode(addr);
9553  FinishCall(decoder, &sig, call_descriptor);
9554  }
9555  }
9556  }
9557 
9558  void CallIndirectImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, const CallIndirectImmediate& imm,
9559  CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
9560  MostlySmallValueKindSig sig(zone_, imm.sig);
9561  for (ValueKind ret : sig.returns()) {
9562  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, ret, "return")) return;
9563  }
9564  const WasmTable* table = imm.table_imm.table;
9565 
9566  if (deopt_info_bytecode_offset_ == decoder->pc_offset() &&
9567  deopt_location_kind_ == LocationKindForDeopt::kEagerDeopt) {
9568  CHECK(v8_flags.wasm_deopt);
9569  EmitDeoptPoint(decoder);
9570  }
9571 
9572  LiftoffRegList pinned;
9573  VarState index_slot = IndexToVarStateSaturating(0, &pinned);
9574 
9575  const bool is_static_index = index_slot.is_const();
9576  Register index_reg =
9577  is_static_index
9578  ? no_reg
9579  : pinned.set(__ LoadToRegister(index_slot, pinned).gp());
9580 
9581  static_assert(kV8MaxWasmTableSize <= kMaxUInt32);
9582  const uint32_t max_table_size = static_cast<uint32_t>(
9583  table->has_maximum_size
9584  ? std::min<uint64_t>(table->maximum_size, wasm::max_table_size())
9585  : wasm::max_table_size());
9586  const bool statically_oob =
9587  is_static_index &&
9588  static_cast<uint32_t>(index_slot.i32_const()) >= max_table_size;
9589 
9590  TempRegisterScope temps;
9591  pinned |= temps.AddTempRegisters(3, kGpReg, &asm_, pinned);
9592 
9593  ScopedTempRegister dispatch_table{temps, kGpReg};
9594  if (imm.table_imm.index == 0) {
9595  // Load the dispatch table directly.
9596  LOAD_PROTECTED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(dispatch_table.gp_reg(), DispatchTable0,
9597  pinned);
9598  } else {
9599  // Load the dispatch table from the ProtectedFixedArray of all dispatch
9600  // tables.
9601  Register dispatch_tables = dispatch_table.gp_reg();
9602  LOAD_PROTECTED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(dispatch_tables, DispatchTables,
9603  pinned);
9604  __ LoadProtectedPointer(dispatch_table.gp_reg(), dispatch_tables,
9605  ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInProtectedFixedArray(
9606  imm.table_imm.index));
9607  }
9608 
9609  {
9610  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("Check index is in-bounds");
9611  // Bounds check against the table size: Compare against the dispatch table
9612  // size, or a constant if the size is statically known.
9613  const bool needs_dynamic_size =
9614  !table->has_maximum_size ||
9615  table->maximum_size != table->initial_size;
9616 
9617  ScopedTempRegister table_size{temps, kGpReg};
9618  OolTrapLabel out_of_bounds =
9619  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapTableOutOfBounds);
9620 
9621  if (statically_oob) {
9622  __ emit_jump(out_of_bounds.label());
9623  // This case is unlikely to happen in production. Thus we just continue
9624  // generating code afterwards, to make sure that the stack is in a
9625  // consistent state for following instructions.
9626  } else if (needs_dynamic_size) {
9627  __ Load(table_size.reg(), dispatch_table.gp_reg(), no_reg,
9628  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmDispatchTable::kLengthOffset),
9629  LoadType::kI32Load);
9630 
9631  if (is_static_index) {
9632  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedLessThanEqual, out_of_bounds.label(),
9633  table_size.gp_reg(), index_slot.i32_const(),
9634  out_of_bounds.frozen());
9635  } else {
9636  ValueKind comparison_type = kI32;
9637  if (Is64() && table->is_table64()) {
9638  // {index_reg} is a uintptr, so do a ptrsize comparison.
9639  __ emit_u32_to_uintptr(table_size.gp_reg(), table_size.gp_reg());
9640  comparison_type = kIntPtrKind;
9641  }
9642  __ emit_cond_jump(kUnsignedLessThanEqual, out_of_bounds.label(),
9643  comparison_type, table_size.gp_reg(), index_reg,
9644  out_of_bounds.frozen());
9645  }
9646  } else {
9647  DCHECK_EQ(max_table_size, table->initial_size);
9648  if (is_static_index) {
9649  DCHECK_LT(index_slot.i32_const(), max_table_size);
9650  } else if (Is64() && table->is_table64()) {
9651  // On 32-bit, this is the same as below, so include the `Is64()` test
9652  // to statically tell the compiler to skip this branch.
9653  // Note: {max_table_size} will be sign-extended, which is fine because
9654  // the MSB is known to be 0 (asserted by the static_assert below).
9655  static_assert(kV8MaxWasmTableSize <= kMaxInt);
9656  __ emit_ptrsize_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual,
9657  out_of_bounds.label(), index_reg,
9658  max_table_size, out_of_bounds.frozen());
9659  } else {
9660  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual,
9661  out_of_bounds.label(), index_reg,
9662  max_table_size, out_of_bounds.frozen());
9663  }
9664  }
9665  }
9666 
9667  // If the function index is dynamic, compute a pointer to the dispatch table
9668  // entry. Otherwise remember the static offset from the dispatch table to
9669  // add it to later loads from that table.
9670  ScopedTempRegister dispatch_table_base{std::move(dispatch_table)};
9671  int dispatch_table_offset = 0;
9672  if (is_static_index) {
9673  // Avoid potential integer overflow here by excluding too large
9674  // (statically OOB) indexes. This code is not reached for statically OOB
9675  // indexes anyway.
9676  dispatch_table_offset =
9677  statically_oob
9678  ? 0
9679  : wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
9680  WasmDispatchTable::OffsetOf(index_slot.i32_const()));
9681  } else {
9682  // TODO(clemensb): Produce better code for this (via more specialized
9683  // platform-specific methods?).
9684 
9685  Register entry_offset = index_reg;
9686  // After this computation we don't need the index register any more. If
9687  // there is no other user we can overwrite it.
9688  bool index_reg_still_used =
9689  __ cache_state() -> get_use_count(LiftoffRegister{index_reg}) > 1;
9690  if (index_reg_still_used) entry_offset = temps.Acquire(kGpReg).gp();
9691 
9692  __ emit_u32_to_uintptr(entry_offset, index_reg);
9693  index_reg = no_reg;
9694  __ emit_ptrsize_muli(entry_offset, entry_offset,
9695  WasmDispatchTable::kEntrySize);
9696  __ emit_ptrsize_add(dispatch_table_base.gp_reg(),
9697  dispatch_table_base.gp_reg(), entry_offset);
9698  if (index_reg_still_used) temps.Return(std::move(entry_offset));
9699  dispatch_table_offset =
9700  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmDispatchTable::kEntriesOffset);
9701  }
9702 
9703  bool needs_type_check = !EquivalentTypes(
9704  table->type.AsNonNull(), ValueType::Ref(imm.sig_imm.heap_type()),
9705  decoder->module_);
9706  bool needs_null_check = table->type.is_nullable();
9707 
9708  // We do both the type check and the null check by checking the signature,
9709  // so this shares most code. For the null check we then only check if the
9710  // stored signature is != -1.
9711  if (needs_type_check || needs_null_check) {
9712  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT(needs_type_check ? "Check signature"
9713  : "Check for null entry");
9714  ScopedTempRegister real_sig_id{temps, kGpReg};
9715 
9716  // Load the signature from the dispatch table.
9717  __ Load(real_sig_id.reg(), dispatch_table_base.gp_reg(), no_reg,
9718  dispatch_table_offset + WasmDispatchTable::kSigBias,
9719  LoadType::kI32Load);
9720 
9721  // Compare against expected signature.
9722  // Since Liftoff code is never serialized (hence not reused across
9723  // isolates / processes) the canonical signature ID is a static integer.
9724  CanonicalTypeIndex canonical_sig_id =
9725  decoder->module_->canonical_sig_id(imm.sig_imm.index);
9726  OolTrapLabel sig_mismatch =
9727  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapFuncSigMismatch);
9728  __ DropValues(1);
9729 
9730  if (!needs_type_check) {
9731  DCHECK(needs_null_check);
9732  // Only check for -1 (nulled table entry).
9733  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kEqual, sig_mismatch.label(),
9734  real_sig_id.gp_reg(), -1, sig_mismatch.frozen());
9735  } else if (!decoder->module_->type(imm.sig_imm.index).is_final) {
9736  Label success_label;
9737  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kEqual, &success_label, real_sig_id.gp_reg(),
9738  canonical_sig_id.index, sig_mismatch.frozen());
9739  if (needs_null_check) {
9740  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kEqual, sig_mismatch.label(),
9741  real_sig_id.gp_reg(), -1,
9742  sig_mismatch.frozen());
9743  }
9744  ScopedTempRegister real_rtt{temps, kGpReg};
9745  __ LoadFullPointer(
9746  real_rtt.gp_reg(), kRootRegister,
9747  IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kWasmCanonicalRtts));
9748  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
9749  real_rtt.gp_reg(), real_rtt.gp_reg(), real_sig_id.gp_reg(),
9750  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(WeakFixedArray)),
9751  nullptr, true);
9752  // real_sig_id is not used any more.
9753  real_sig_id.Reset();
9754  // Remove the weak reference tag.
9755  if constexpr (kSystemPointerSize == 4) {
9756  __ emit_i32_andi(real_rtt.gp_reg(), real_rtt.gp_reg(),
9757  static_cast<int32_t>(~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
9758  } else {
9759  __ emit_i64_andi(real_rtt.reg(), real_rtt.reg(),
9760  static_cast<int32_t>(~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
9761  }
9762  // Constant-time subtyping check: load exactly one candidate RTT from
9763  // the supertypes list.
9764  // Step 1: load the WasmTypeInfo.
9765  constexpr int kTypeInfoOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
9766  Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
9767  ScopedTempRegister type_info{std::move(real_rtt)};
9768  __ LoadTaggedPointer(type_info.gp_reg(), type_info.gp_reg(), no_reg,
9769  kTypeInfoOffset);
9770  // Step 2: check the list's length if needed.
9771  uint32_t rtt_depth =
9772  GetSubtypingDepth(decoder->module_, imm.sig_imm.index);
9773  if (rtt_depth >= kMinimumSupertypeArraySize) {
9774  ScopedTempRegister list_length{temps, kGpReg};
9775  int offset =
9776  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTypeInfo::kSupertypesLengthOffset);
9777  __ LoadSmiAsInt32(list_length.reg(), type_info.gp_reg(), offset);
9778  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedLessThanEqual, sig_mismatch.label(),
9779  list_length.gp_reg(), rtt_depth,
9780  sig_mismatch.frozen());
9781  }
9782  // Step 3: load the candidate list slot, and compare it.
9783  ScopedTempRegister maybe_match{std::move(type_info)};
9784  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
9785  maybe_match.gp_reg(), maybe_match.gp_reg(), no_reg,
9786  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTypeInfo::kSupertypesOffset +
9787  rtt_depth * kTaggedSize));
9788  ScopedTempRegister formal_rtt{temps, kGpReg};
9789  // Instead of {pinned}, we use {kGpCacheRegList} as the list of pinned
9790  // registers, to prevent any attempt to cache the instance, which would
9791  // be incompatible with the {FREEZE_STATE} that is in effect here.
9792  LOAD_TAGGED_PTR_INSTANCE_FIELD(formal_rtt.gp_reg(), ManagedObjectMaps,
9793  kGpCacheRegList);
9794  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
9795  formal_rtt.gp_reg(), formal_rtt.gp_reg(), no_reg,
9796  wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(
9797  imm.sig_imm.index.index));
9798  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, sig_mismatch.label(), kRef,
9799  formal_rtt.gp_reg(), maybe_match.gp_reg(),
9800  sig_mismatch.frozen());
9801 
9802  __ bind(&success_label);
9803  } else {
9804  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kNotEqual, sig_mismatch.label(),
9805  real_sig_id.gp_reg(), canonical_sig_id.index,
9806  sig_mismatch.frozen());
9807  }
9808  } else {
9809  __ DropValues(1);
9810  }
9811 
9812  {
9813  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("Execute indirect call");
9814 
9815  // The first parameter will be either a WasmTrustedInstanceData or a
9816  // WasmImportData.
9817  Register implicit_arg = temps.Acquire(kGpReg).gp();
9818  Register target = temps.Acquire(kGpReg).gp();
9819 
9820  {
9821  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("Load implicit arg and target from dispatch table");
9822  __ LoadProtectedPointer(
9823  implicit_arg, dispatch_table_base.gp_reg(),
9824  dispatch_table_offset + WasmDispatchTable::kImplicitArgBias);
9825  __ LoadCodePointer(
9826  target, dispatch_table_base.gp_reg(),
9827  dispatch_table_offset + WasmDispatchTable::kTargetBias);
9828  }
9829 
9830  if (v8_flags.wasm_inlining_call_indirect) {
9831  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("Feedback collection for speculative inlining");
9832 
9833  ScopedTempRegister vector{std::move(dispatch_table_base)};
9834  __ Fill(vector.reg(), WasmLiftoffFrameConstants::kFeedbackVectorOffset,
9835  kRef);
9836  VarState vector_var{kRef, vector.reg(), 0};
9837 
9838  // A constant `uint32_t` is sufficient for the vector slot index.
9839  // The number of call instructions (and hence feedback vector slots) is
9840  // capped by the number of instructions, which is capped by the maximum
9841  // function body size.
9842  static_assert(kV8MaxWasmFunctionSize <
9843  std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() / 2);
9844  uint32_t vector_slot =
9845  static_cast<uint32_t>(encountered_call_instructions_.size()) * 2;
9846  encountered_call_instructions_.push_back(
9847  FunctionTypeFeedback::kCallIndirect);
9848  VarState index_var(kI32, vector_slot, 0);
9849 
9850  // Thread the target and ref through the builtin call (i.e., pass them
9851  // as parameters and return them unchanged) as `CallBuiltin` otherwise
9852  // clobbers them. (The spilling code in `SpillAllRegisters` is only
9853  // aware of registers used on Liftoff's abstract value stack, not the
9854  // ones manually allocated above.)
9855  // TODO(335082212): We could avoid this and reduce the code size for
9856  // each call_indirect by moving the target and ref lookup into the
9857  // builtin as well.
9858  // However, then we would either (a) need to replicate the optimizations
9859  // above for static indices etc., which increases code duplication and
9860  // maintenance cost, or (b) regress performance even more than the
9861  // builtin call itself already does.
9862  // All in all, let's keep it simple at first, i.e., share the maximum
9863  // amount of code when inlining is enabled vs. not.
9864  VarState target_var(kI32, LiftoffRegister(target), 0);
9865  VarState implicit_arg_var(kRef, LiftoffRegister(implicit_arg), 0);
9866 
9867  // CallIndirectIC(vector: FixedArray, vectorIndex: int32,
9868  // target: WasmCodePointer (== uint32),
9869  // implicitArg: WasmTrustedInstanceData|WasmImportData)
9870  // -> <target, implicit_arg>
9871  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallIndirectIC,
9872  MakeSig::Returns(kIntPtrKind, kIntPtrKind)
9873  .Params(kRef, kI32, kI32, kRef),
9874  {vector_var, index_var, target_var, implicit_arg_var},
9875  decoder->position());
9876  target = kReturnRegister0;
9877  implicit_arg = kReturnRegister1;
9878  }
9879 
9880  auto call_descriptor = compiler::GetWasmCallDescriptor(
9881  zone_, imm.sig, compiler::WasmCallKind::kWasmIndirectFunction);
9882  call_descriptor = GetLoweredCallDescriptor(zone_, call_descriptor);
9883 
9884  __ PrepareCall(&sig, call_descriptor, &target, implicit_arg);
9885  if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
9886  __ PrepareTailCall(
9887  static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount()),
9888  static_cast<int>(
9889  call_descriptor->GetStackParameterDelta(descriptor_)));
9890  __ TailCallIndirect(call_descriptor, target);
9891  } else {
9892  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
9893  __ pc_offset(), SourcePosition(decoder->position()), true);
9894  __ CallIndirect(&sig, call_descriptor, target);
9895  FinishCall(decoder, &sig, call_descriptor);
9896  }
9897  }
9898  }
9899 
9900  void StoreFrameDescriptionForDeopt(
9901  FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t adapt_shadow_stack_pc_offset = 0) {
9902  DCHECK(v8_flags.wasm_deopt);
9903  DCHECK(!frame_description_);
9904 
9905  frame_description_ = std::make_unique<LiftoffFrameDescriptionForDeopt>(
9906  LiftoffFrameDescriptionForDeopt{
9907  decoder->pc_offset(), static_cast<uint32_t>(__ pc_offset()),
9908 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CET_SHADOW_STACK
9909  adapt_shadow_stack_pc_offset,
9910 #endif // V8_ENABLE_CET_SHADOW_STACK
9911  std::vector<LiftoffVarState>(__ cache_state()->stack_state.begin(),
9912  __ cache_state()->stack_state.end()),
9913  __ cache_state()->cached_instance_data});
9914  }
9915 
9916  void EmitDeoptPoint(FullDecoder* decoder) {
9917 #if defined(DEBUG) and !defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
9918  // Liftoff may only use "allocatable registers" as defined by the
9919  // RegisterConfiguration. (The deoptimizer will not handle non-allocatable
9920  // registers).
9921  // Note that this DCHECK is skipped for arm 32 bit as its deoptimizer
9922  // decides to handle all available double / simd registers.
9923  const RegisterConfiguration* config = RegisterConfiguration::Default();
9924  DCHECK_LE(kLiftoffAssemblerFpCacheRegs.Count(),
9925  config->num_allocatable_simd128_registers());
9926  for (DoubleRegister reg : kLiftoffAssemblerFpCacheRegs) {
9927  const int* end = config->allocatable_simd128_codes() +
9928  config->num_allocatable_simd128_registers();
9929  DCHECK(std::find(config->allocatable_simd128_codes(), end, reg.code()) !=
9930  end);
9931  }
9932 #endif
9933 
9934  LiftoffAssembler::CacheState initial_state(zone_);
9935  initial_state.Split(*__ cache_state());
9936  // TODO(mliedtke): The deopt point should be in out-of-line-code.
9937  Label deopt_point;
9938  Label callref;
9939  __ emit_jump(&callref);
9940  __ bind(&deopt_point);
9941  uint32_t adapt_shadow_stack_pc_offset = __ pc_offset();
9942 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CET_SHADOW_STACK
9943  if (v8_flags.cet_compatible) {
9944  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAdaptShadowStackForDeopt);
9945  }
9946 #endif // V8_ENABLE_CET_SHADOW_STACK
9947  StoreFrameDescriptionForDeopt(decoder, adapt_shadow_stack_pc_offset);
9948  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmLiftoffDeoptFinish, MakeSig(), {},
9949  kNoSourcePosition);
9950  __ MergeStackWith(initial_state, 0, LiftoffAssembler::kForwardJump);
9951  __ cache_state() -> Steal(initial_state);
9952  __ bind(&callref);
9953  }
9954 
9955  void CallRefImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, ValueType func_ref_type,
9956  const FunctionSig* type_sig, CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
9957  MostlySmallValueKindSig sig(zone_, type_sig);
9958  for (ValueKind ret : sig.returns()) {
9959  if (!CheckSupportedType(decoder, ret, "return")) return;
9960  }
9961  compiler::CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = compiler::GetWasmCallDescriptor(
9962  zone_, type_sig, compiler::WasmCallKind::kWasmIndirectFunction);
9963  call_descriptor = GetLoweredCallDescriptor(zone_, call_descriptor);
9964 
9965  Register target_reg = no_reg;
9966  Register implicit_arg_reg = no_reg;
9967 
9968  if (v8_flags.wasm_inlining) {
9969  if (deopt_info_bytecode_offset_ == decoder->pc_offset() &&
9970  deopt_location_kind_ == LocationKindForDeopt::kEagerDeopt) {
9971  CHECK(v8_flags.wasm_deopt);
9972  EmitDeoptPoint(decoder);
9973  }
9974  LiftoffRegList pinned;
9975  LiftoffRegister func_ref = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
9976  LiftoffRegister vector = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
9977  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, func_ref.gp(), pinned, func_ref_type);
9978  VarState func_ref_var(kRef, func_ref, 0);
9979 
9980  __ Fill(vector, WasmLiftoffFrameConstants::kFeedbackVectorOffset, kRef);
9981  VarState vector_var{kRef, vector, 0};
9982  // A constant `uint32_t` is sufficient for the vector slot index.
9983  // The number of call instructions (and hence feedback vector slots) is
9984  // capped by the number of instructions, which is capped by the maximum
9985  // function body size.
9986  static_assert(kV8MaxWasmFunctionSize <
9987  std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() / 2);
9988  uint32_t vector_slot =
9989  static_cast<uint32_t>(encountered_call_instructions_.size()) * 2;
9990  encountered_call_instructions_.push_back(FunctionTypeFeedback::kCallRef);
9991  VarState index_var(kI32, vector_slot, 0);
9992 
9993  // CallRefIC(vector: FixedArray, vectorIndex: int32,
9994  // funcref: WasmFuncRef) -> <target, implicit_arg>
9995  CallBuiltin(
9996  Builtin::kCallRefIC,
9997  MakeSig::Returns(kIntPtrKind, kIntPtrKind).Params(kRef, kI32, kRef),
9998  {vector_var, index_var, func_ref_var}, decoder->position());
9999  target_reg = LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0).gp();
10000  implicit_arg_reg = kReturnRegister1;
10001  } else { // v8_flags.wasm_inlining
10002  // Non-feedback-collecting version.
10003  // Executing a write barrier needs temp registers; doing this on a
10004  // conditional branch confuses the LiftoffAssembler's register management.
10005  // Spill everything up front to work around that.
10006  __ SpillAllRegisters();
10007 
10008  LiftoffRegList pinned;
10009  Register func_ref = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned)).gp();
10010  MaybeEmitNullCheck(decoder, func_ref, pinned, func_ref_type);
10011  implicit_arg_reg = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
10012  target_reg = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
10013 
10014  // Load the WasmInternalFunction from the WasmFuncRef.
10015  Register internal_function = func_ref;
10016  __ LoadTrustedPointer(
10017  internal_function, func_ref,
10018  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmFuncRef::kTrustedInternalOffset),
10019  kWasmInternalFunctionIndirectPointerTag);
10020 
10021  // Load the implicit argument (WasmTrustedInstanceData or WasmImportData)
10022  // and target.
10023  __ LoadProtectedPointer(
10024  implicit_arg_reg, internal_function,
10025  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
10026  WasmInternalFunction::kProtectedImplicitArgOffset));
10027 
10028  __ LoadFullPointer(target_reg, internal_function,
10029  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
10030  WasmInternalFunction::kRawCallTargetOffset));
10031 
10032  // Now the call target is in {target_reg} and the first parameter
10033  // (WasmTrustedInstanceData or WasmImportData) is in
10034  // {implicit_arg_reg}.
10035  } // v8_flags.wasm_inlining
10036 
10037  __ PrepareCall(&sig, call_descriptor, &target_reg, implicit_arg_reg);
10038  if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
10039  __ PrepareTailCall(
10040  static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount()),
10041  static_cast<int>(
10042  call_descriptor->GetStackParameterDelta(descriptor_)));
10043  __ TailCallIndirect(call_descriptor, target_reg);
10044  } else {
10045  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
10046  __ pc_offset(), SourcePosition(decoder->position()), true);
10047  __ CallIndirect(&sig, call_descriptor, target_reg);
10048  FinishCall(decoder, &sig, call_descriptor);
10049  }
10050  }
10051 
10052  void LoadNullValue(Register null, ValueType type) {
10053  __ LoadFullPointer(
10054  null, kRootRegister,
10055  type.use_wasm_null()
10056  ? IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kWasmNull)
10057  : IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kNullValue));
10058  }
10059 
10060  // Stores the null value representation in the passed register.
10061  // If pointer compression is active, only the compressed tagged pointer
10062  // will be stored. Any operations with this register therefore must
10063  // not compare this against 64 bits using quadword instructions.
10064  void LoadNullValueForCompare(Register null, LiftoffRegList pinned,
10065  ValueType type) {
10066 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
10067  uint32_t value = type.use_wasm_null() ? StaticReadOnlyRoot::kWasmNull
10068  : StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNullValue;
10069  __ LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(null),
10070  WasmValue(static_cast<uint32_t>(value)));
10071 #else
10072  LoadNullValue(null, type);
10073 #endif
10074  }
10075 
10076  void LoadExceptionSymbol(Register dst, LiftoffRegList pinned,
10077  RootIndex root_index) {
10078  __ LoadFullPointer(dst, kRootRegister,
10079  IsolateData::root_slot_offset(root_index));
10080  }
10081 
10082  void MaybeEmitNullCheck(FullDecoder* decoder, Register object,
10083  LiftoffRegList pinned, ValueType type) {
10084  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_skip_null_checks || !type.is_nullable()) {
10085  return;
10086  }
10087  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("null check");
10088  LiftoffRegister null = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
10089  LoadNullValueForCompare(null.gp(), pinned, type);
10090  OolTrapLabel trap =
10091  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapNullDereference);
10092  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, trap.label(), kRefNull, object, null.gp(),
10093  trap.frozen());
10094  }
10095 
10096  void BoundsCheckArray(FullDecoder* decoder, bool implicit_null_check,
10097  LiftoffRegister array, LiftoffRegister index,
10098  LiftoffRegList pinned) {
10099  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.experimental_wasm_skip_bounds_checks)) return;
10100  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("array bounds check");
10101  LiftoffRegister length = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
10102  constexpr int kLengthOffset =
10103  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kLengthOffset);
10104  uint32_t protected_instruction_pc = 0;
10105  __ Load(length, array.gp(), no_reg, kLengthOffset, LoadType::kI32Load,
10106  implicit_null_check ? &protected_instruction_pc : nullptr);
10107  if (implicit_null_check) {
10108  RegisterProtectedInstruction(decoder, protected_instruction_pc);
10109  }
10110  OolTrapLabel trap =
10111  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapArrayOutOfBounds);
10112  __ emit_cond_jump(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, trap.label(), kI32, index.gp(),
10113  length.gp(), trap.frozen());
10114  }

10116  int StructFieldOffset(const StructType* struct_type, int field_index) {
10117  return wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmStruct::kHeaderSize +
10118  struct_type->field_offset(field_index));
10119  }

10121  std::pair<bool, bool> null_checks_for_struct_op(ValueType struct_type,
10122  int field_index) {
10123  bool explicit_null_check =
10124  struct_type.is_nullable() &&
10125  (null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit ||
10126  field_index > wasm::kMaxStructFieldIndexForImplicitNullCheck);
10127  bool implicit_null_check =
10128  struct_type.is_nullable() && !explicit_null_check;
10129  return {explicit_null_check, implicit_null_check};
10130  }

10132  void LoadObjectField(FullDecoder* decoder, LiftoffRegister dst, Register src,
10133  Register offset_reg, int offset, ValueKind kind,
10134  bool is_signed, bool trapping, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
10135  uint32_t protected_load_pc = 0;
10136  if (is_reference(kind)) {
10137  __ LoadTaggedPointer(dst.gp(), src, offset_reg, offset,
10138  trapping ? &protected_load_pc : nullptr);
10139  } else {
10140  // Primitive kind.
10141  LoadType load_type = LoadType::ForValueKind(kind, is_signed);
10142  __ Load(dst, src, offset_reg, offset, load_type,
10143  trapping ? &protected_load_pc : nullptr);
10144  }
10145  if (trapping) RegisterProtectedInstruction(decoder, protected_load_pc);
10146  }
10147 
10148  void LoadAtomicObjectField(FullDecoder* decoder, LiftoffRegister dst,
10149  Register src, Register offset_reg, int offset,
10150  ValueKind kind, bool is_signed, bool trapping,
10151  AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order,
10152  LiftoffRegList pinned) {
10153  uint32_t protected_load_pc = 0;
10154  if (is_reference(kind)) {
10155  __ AtomicLoadTaggedPointer(dst.gp(), src, offset_reg, offset,
10156  memory_order,
10157  trapping ? &protected_load_pc : nullptr);
10158  } else {
10159  // Primitive kind.
10160  LoadType load_type = LoadType::ForValueKind(kind, is_signed);
10161  // TODO(mliedtke): Mark load trapping if trapping
10162  if (trapping) UNIMPLEMENTED();
10163  // TODO(mliedtke): Can we emit something better if the memory order is
10164  // acqrel?
10165  __ AtomicLoad(dst, src, offset_reg, offset, load_type, pinned, false);
10166  }
10167  if (trapping) RegisterProtectedInstruction(decoder, protected_load_pc);
10168  }
10169 
10170  void StoreObjectField(FullDecoder* decoder, Register obj, Register offset_reg,
10171  int offset, LiftoffRegister value, bool trapping,
10172  LiftoffRegList pinned, ValueKind kind,
10173  LiftoffAssembler::SkipWriteBarrier skip_write_barrier =
10174  LiftoffAssembler::kNoSkipWriteBarrier) {
10175  uint32_t protected_load_pc = 0;
10176  if (is_reference(kind)) {
10177  __ StoreTaggedPointer(obj, offset_reg, offset, value.gp(), pinned,
10178  trapping ? &protected_load_pc : nullptr,
10179  skip_write_barrier);
10180  } else {
10181  // Primitive kind.
10182  StoreType store_type = StoreType::ForValueKind(kind);
10183  __ Store(obj, offset_reg, offset, value, store_type, pinned,
10184  trapping ? &protected_load_pc : nullptr);
10185  }
10186  if (trapping) RegisterProtectedInstruction(decoder, protected_load_pc);
10187  }
10188 
10189  void StoreAtomicObjectField(FullDecoder* decoder, Register obj,
10190  Register offset_reg, int offset,
10191  LiftoffRegister value, bool trapping,
10192  LiftoffRegList pinned, ValueKind kind,
10193  AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order) {
10194  uint32_t protected_load_pc = 0;
10195  if (is_reference(kind)) {
10196  __ AtomicStoreTaggedPointer(obj, offset_reg, offset, value.gp(), pinned,
10197  memory_order,
10198  trapping ? &protected_load_pc : nullptr);
10199  } else {
10200  // Primitive kind.
10201  StoreType store_type = StoreType::ForValueKind(kind);
10202  // TODO(mliedtke): Mark load trapping if trapping
10203  if (trapping) UNIMPLEMENTED();
10204  __ AtomicStore(obj, offset_reg, offset, value, store_type, pinned, false);
10205  }
10206  if (trapping) RegisterProtectedInstruction(decoder, protected_load_pc);
10207  }

10209  void SetDefaultValue(LiftoffRegister reg, ValueType type) {
10210  DCHECK(type.is_defaultable());
10211  switch (type.kind()) {
10212  case kI8:
10213  case kI16:
10214  case kI32:
10215  return __ LoadConstant(reg, WasmValue(int32_t{0}));
10216  case kI64:
10217  return __ LoadConstant(reg, WasmValue(int64_t{0}));
10218  case kF16:
10219  case kF32:
10220  return __ LoadConstant(reg, WasmValue(float{0.0}));
10221  case kF64:
10222  return __ LoadConstant(reg, WasmValue(double{0.0}));
10223  case kS128:
10224  DCHECK(CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128());
10225  return __ emit_s128_xor(reg, reg, reg);
10226  case kRefNull:
10227  return LoadNullValue(reg.gp(), type);
10228  case kVoid:
10229  case kTop:
10230  case kBottom:
10231  case kRef:
10232  UNREACHABLE();
10233  }
10234  }

10236  void MaybeOSR() {
10237  if (V8_UNLIKELY(for_debugging_)) {
10238  __ MaybeOSR();
10239  }
10240  }
10241 
10242  void FinishCall(FullDecoder* decoder, ValueKindSig* sig,
10243  compiler::CallDescriptor* call_descriptor) {
10244  DefineSafepoint();
10245  RegisterDebugSideTableEntry(decoder, DebugSideTableBuilder::kDidSpill);
10246 
10247  if (deopt_info_bytecode_offset_ == decoder->pc_offset() &&
10248  deopt_location_kind_ == LocationKindForDeopt::kInlinedCall) {
10249  CHECK(v8_flags.wasm_deopt);
10250  uint32_t adapt_shadow_stack_pc_offset = 0;
10251 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CET_SHADOW_STACK
10252  if (v8_flags.cet_compatible) {
10253  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("deopt entry for kAdaptShadowStackForDeopt");
10254  // AdaptShadowStackForDeopt is be called to build shadow stack after
10255  // deoptimization. Deoptimizer will directly jump to
10256  // `call AdaptShadowStackForDeopt`. But, in any other case, it should be
10257  // ignored.
10258  Label deopt_point;
10259  __ emit_jump(&deopt_point);
10260  adapt_shadow_stack_pc_offset = __ pc_offset();
10261  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAdaptShadowStackForDeopt);
10262  __ bind(&deopt_point);
10263  }
10264 #endif // V8_ENABLE_CET_SHADOW_STACK
10265  StoreFrameDescriptionForDeopt(decoder, adapt_shadow_stack_pc_offset);
10266  }
10267 
10268  int pc_offset = __ pc_offset();
10269  MaybeOSR();
10270  EmitLandingPad(decoder, pc_offset);
10271  __ FinishCall(sig, call_descriptor);
10272  }

10274  void CheckNan(LiftoffRegister src, LiftoffRegList pinned, ValueKind kind) {
10275  DCHECK(kind == ValueKind::kF32 || kind == ValueKind::kF64);
10276  auto nondeterminism_addr = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
10277  __ LoadConstant(nondeterminism_addr,
10278  WasmValue::ForUintPtr(WasmEngine::GetNondeterminismAddr()));
10279  __ emit_store_nonzero_if_nan(nondeterminism_addr.gp(), src.fp(), kind);
10280  }

10282  void CheckS128Nan(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegList pinned,
10283  ValueKind lane_kind) {
10284  RegClass rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
10285  LiftoffRegister tmp_gp = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
10286  LiftoffRegister tmp_s128 = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(rc, pinned));
10287  LiftoffRegister nondeterminism_addr =
10288  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned));
10289  __ LoadConstant(nondeterminism_addr,
10290  WasmValue::ForUintPtr(WasmEngine::GetNondeterminismAddr()));

10292  tmp_gp.gp(), tmp_s128, lane_kind);
10293  }
10294 
10295  void ArrayFillImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, LiftoffRegList pinned,
10296  LiftoffRegister obj, LiftoffRegister index,
10297  LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister length,
10298  ValueKind elem_kind,
10299  LiftoffAssembler::SkipWriteBarrier skip_write_barrier) {
10300  // initial_offset = WasmArray::kHeaderSize + index * elem_size.
10301  LiftoffRegister offset = index;
10302  if (value_kind_size_log2(elem_kind) != 0) {
10303  __ emit_i32_shli(offset.gp(), index.gp(),
10304  value_kind_size_log2(elem_kind));
10305  }
10306  __ emit_i32_addi(offset.gp(), offset.gp(),
10307  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize));
10308 
10309  // end_offset = initial_offset + length * elem_size.
10310  LiftoffRegister end_offset = length;
10311  if (value_kind_size_log2(elem_kind) != 0) {
10312  __ emit_i32_shli(end_offset.gp(), length.gp(),
10313  value_kind_size_log2(elem_kind));
10314  }
10315  __ emit_i32_add(end_offset.gp(), end_offset.gp(), offset.gp());
10316 
10317  FREEZE_STATE(frozen_for_conditional_jumps);
10318  Label loop, done;
10319  __ bind(&loop);
10320  __ emit_cond_jump(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, &done, kI32, offset.gp(),
10321  end_offset.gp(), frozen_for_conditional_jumps);
10322  StoreObjectField(decoder, obj.gp(), offset.gp(), 0, value, false, pinned,
10323  elem_kind, skip_write_barrier);
10324  __ emit_i32_addi(offset.gp(), offset.gp(), value_kind_size(elem_kind));
10325  __ emit_jump(&loop);
10326 
10327  __ bind(&done);
10328  }
10329 
10330  void RegisterProtectedInstruction(FullDecoder* decoder,
10331  uint32_t protected_instruction_pc) {
10332  protected_instructions_.emplace_back(
10333  trap_handler::ProtectedInstructionData{protected_instruction_pc});
10334  source_position_table_builder_.AddPosition(
10335  protected_instruction_pc, SourcePosition(decoder->position()), true);
10336  if (for_debugging_) {
10337  DefineSafepoint(protected_instruction_pc);
10338  }
10339  }

10341  bool has_outstanding_op() const {
10342  return outstanding_op_ != kNoOutstandingOp;
10343  }
10344 
10345  bool test_and_reset_outstanding_op(WasmOpcode opcode) {
10346  DCHECK_NE(kNoOutstandingOp, opcode);
10347  if (outstanding_op_ != opcode) return false;
10348  outstanding_op_ = kNoOutstandingOp;
10349  return true;
10350  }

10352  void TraceCacheState(FullDecoder* decoder) const {
10353  if (!v8_flags.trace_liftoff) return;
10354  StdoutStream os;
10355  for (int control_depth = decoder->control_depth() - 1; control_depth >= -1;
10356  --control_depth) {
10357  auto* cache_state =
10358  control_depth == -1 ? __ cache_state()
10359  : &decoder->control_at(control_depth)
10360  ->label_state;
10361  os << PrintCollection(cache_state->stack_state);
10362  if (control_depth != -1) PrintF("; ");
10363  }
10364  os << "\n";
10365  }
10366 
10367  void DefineSafepoint(int pc_offset = 0) {
10368  if (pc_offset == 0) pc_offset = __ pc_offset_for_safepoint();
10369  if (pc_offset == last_safepoint_offset_) return;
10370  last_safepoint_offset_ = pc_offset;
10371  auto safepoint = safepoint_table_builder_.DefineSafepoint(&asm_, pc_offset);
10372  __ cache_state()->DefineSafepoint(safepoint);
10373  }
10374 
10375  void DefineSafepointWithCalleeSavedRegisters() {
10376  int pc_offset = __ pc_offset_for_safepoint();
10377  if (pc_offset == last_safepoint_offset_) return;
10378  last_safepoint_offset_ = pc_offset;
10379  auto safepoint = safepoint_table_builder_.DefineSafepoint(&asm_, pc_offset);
10380  __ cache_state()->DefineSafepointWithCalleeSavedRegisters(safepoint);
10381  }
10382 
10383  // Return a register holding the instance, populating the "cached instance"
10384  // register if possible. If no free register is available, the cache is not
10385  // set and we use {fallback} instead. This can be freely overwritten by the
10386  // caller then.
10387  V8_INLINE Register LoadInstanceIntoRegister(LiftoffRegList pinned,
10388  Register fallback) {
10389  Register instance = __ cache_state() -> cached_instance_data;
10390  if (V8_UNLIKELY(instance == no_reg)) {
10391  instance = LoadInstanceIntoRegister_Slow(pinned, fallback);
10392  }
10393  return instance;
10394  }
10395 
10396  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST Register
10397  LoadInstanceIntoRegister_Slow(LiftoffRegList pinned, Register fallback) {
10398  DCHECK_EQ(no_reg, __ cache_state()->cached_instance_data);
10399  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT("load instance");
10400  Register instance = __ cache_state()->TrySetCachedInstanceRegister(
10401  pinned | LiftoffRegList{fallback});
10402  if (instance == no_reg) instance = fallback;
10403  __ LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance);
10404  return instance;
10405  }

10408  static constexpr base::EnumSet<ValueKind> kUnconditionallySupported{
10409  // MVP:
10410  kI32, kI64, kF32, kF64,
10411  // Extern ref:
10412  kRef, kRefNull, kI8, kI16};
10413 
10414  LiftoffAssembler asm_;
10415 
10416  // Used for merging code generation of subsequent operations (via look-ahead).
10417  // Set by the first opcode, reset by the second.
10418  WasmOpcode outstanding_op_ = kNoOutstandingOp;
10419 
10420  // {supported_types_} is updated in {MaybeBailoutForUnsupportedType}.
10421  base::EnumSet<ValueKind> supported_types_ = kUnconditionallySupported;
10422  compiler::CallDescriptor* const descriptor_;
10423  CompilationEnv* const env_;
10424  DebugSideTableBuilder* const debug_sidetable_builder_;
10425  base::OwnedVector<ValueType> stack_value_types_for_debugging_;
10426  const ForDebugging for_debugging_;
10427  LiftoffBailoutReason bailout_reason_ = kSuccess;
10428  const int func_index_;
10429  ZoneVector<OutOfLineCode> out_of_line_code_;
10430  SourcePositionTableBuilder source_position_table_builder_;
10431  ZoneVector<trap_handler::ProtectedInstructionData> protected_instructions_;
10432  // Zone used to store information during compilation. The result will be
10433  // stored independently, such that this zone can die together with the
10434  // LiftoffCompiler after compilation.
10435  Zone* zone_;
10436  SafepointTableBuilder safepoint_table_builder_;
10437  // The pc offset of the instructions to reserve the stack frame. Needed to
10438  // patch the actually needed stack size in the end.
10439  uint32_t pc_offset_stack_frame_construction_ = 0;
10440  // For emitting breakpoint, we store a pointer to the position of the next
10441  // breakpoint, and a pointer after the list of breakpoints as end marker.
10442  // A single breakpoint at offset 0 indicates that we should prepare the
10443  // function for stepping by flooding it with breakpoints.
10444  const int* next_breakpoint_ptr_ = nullptr;
10445  const int* next_breakpoint_end_ = nullptr;
10446 
10447  // A precalculated set of code ranges that define the basic blocks in the
10448  // current function. Note that the NativeModule can be deleted during the
10449  // compilation, but these code ranges are kept alive via a shared_ptr in the
10450  // CompilationEnv.
10451  base::Vector<const WasmCodeRange> coverage_code_ranges_;
10452 
10453  // Points to the current WasmCodeRange during compilation, it's used to decide
10454  // whether we are in a new basic block and we need to emit coverage
10455  // instrumentation.
10456  const WasmCodeRange* coverage_current_code_range_ = nullptr;
10457 
10458  // Points to the start of an array of uint32_t counters that represent the
10459  // coverage count for each basic block in the function. We emit
10460  // instrumentation code to increase the counter with {emit_inc_i32_at}.
10461  Address coverage_count_array_addr_ = 0;
10462 
10463  // Introduce a dead breakpoint to ensure that the calculation of the return
10464  // address in OSR is correct.
10465  int dead_breakpoint_ = 0;
10466 
10467  // Remember whether the did function-entry break checks (for "hook on function
10468  // call" and "break on entry" a.k.a. instrumentation breakpoint). This happens
10469  // at the first breakable opcode in the function (if compiling for debugging).
10470  bool did_function_entry_break_checks_ = false;
10471

10474  int pc_offset;
10475  };
10476 
10477  ZoneVector<HandlerInfo> handlers_;

10480  // Current number of exception refs on the stack.
10481  int num_exceptions_ = 0;
10482 
10483  // The pc_offset of the last defined safepoint. -1 if no safepoint has been
10484  // defined yet.
10485  int last_safepoint_offset_ = -1;

10490  // {FunctionTypeFeedback::kCallIndirect} / {FunctionTypeFeedback::kCallRef}.
10491  // After compilation, this is transferred into {WasmModule::type_feedback}.
10492  std::vector<uint32_t> encountered_call_instructions_;
10493 
10494  // Pointer to information passed from the fuzzer. The pointer will be
10495  // embedded in generated code, which will update the value at runtime.
10496  int32_t* const max_steps_;

10498  const bool detect_nondeterminism_;

10503

10507  trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled() && V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
10508  ? compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler
10509  : compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit;
10510 
10511  DISALLOW_IMPLICIT_CONSTRUCTORS(LiftoffCompiler);
10512 };

10515 constexpr WasmOpcode LiftoffCompiler::kNoOutstandingOp;
