10517 constexpr base::EnumSet<ValueKind> LiftoffCompiler::kUnconditionallySupported;
10518 
10519 std::unique_ptr<AssemblerBuffer> NewLiftoffAssemblerBuffer(int func_body_size) {
10520  size_t code_size_estimate =
10521  WasmCodeManager::EstimateLiftoffCodeSize(func_body_size);
10522  // Allocate the initial buffer a bit bigger to avoid reallocation during code
10523  // generation. Overflows when casting to int are fine, as we will allocate at
10524  // least {AssemblerBase::kMinimalBufferSize} anyway, so in the worst case we
10525  // have to grow more often.
10526  int initial_buffer_size = static_cast<int>(128 + code_size_estimate * 4 / 3);
10527 
10528  return NewAssemblerBuffer(initial_buffer_size);
10529 }
10530 
10531 } // namespace
10532 
10533 WasmCompilationResult ExecuteLiftoffCompilation(
10534  CompilationEnv* env, const FunctionBody& func_body,
10535  const LiftoffOptions& compiler_options) {
10536  DCHECK(compiler_options.is_initialized());
10537  // Liftoff does not validate the code, so that should have run before.
10538  DCHECK(env->module->function_was_validated(compiler_options.func_index));
10539  base::TimeTicks start_time;
10540  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_compilation_times)) {
10541  start_time = base::TimeTicks::Now();
10542  }
10543  int func_body_size = static_cast<int>(func_body.end - func_body.start);
10544  TRACE_EVENT2(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.wasm.detailed"),
10545  "wasm.CompileBaseline", "funcIndex", compiler_options.func_index,
10546  "bodySize", func_body_size);
10547 
10548  Zone zone(GetWasmEngine()->allocator(), "LiftoffCompilationZone");
10549  auto call_descriptor = compiler::GetWasmCallDescriptor(&zone, func_body.sig);
10550 
10551  std::unique_ptr<DebugSideTableBuilder> debug_sidetable_builder;
10552  if (compiler_options.debug_sidetable) {
10553  debug_sidetable_builder = std::make_unique<DebugSideTableBuilder>();
10554  }
10555  DCHECK_IMPLIES(compiler_options.max_steps,
10556  compiler_options.for_debugging == kForDebugging);
10557  WasmDetectedFeatures unused_detected_features;
10558 
10559  WasmFunctionCoverageData* function_coverage_data = nullptr;
10560  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.wasm_code_coverage)) {
10561  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(env->module_coverage_data);
10562  int declared_function_index =
10563  compiler_options.func_index - env->module->num_imported_functions;
10564  function_coverage_data = env->module_coverage_data->GetFunctionCoverageData(
10565  declared_function_index);
10566  if (!function_coverage_data) {
10567  // There can be a race here, if another thread finds that
10568  // GetFunctionCoverageData() returns nullptr, but in that case we would
10569  // just waste some time calling ComputeBasicBlocks().
10570  BasicBlockCalculator basic_block_calculator(
10571  &zone, {func_body.start, static_cast<size_t>(func_body_size)});
10572  basic_block_calculator.ComputeBasicBlocks();
10573  function_coverage_data = env->module_coverage_data->InstallCoverageData(
10574  declared_function_index, basic_block_calculator.GetCodeRanges());
10575  }
10576  }
10577 
10578  WasmFullDecoder<Decoder::NoValidationTag, LiftoffCompiler> decoder(
10579  &zone, env->module, env->enabled_features,
10580  compiler_options.detected_features ? compiler_options.detected_features
10581  : &unused_detected_features,
10582  func_body, call_descriptor, env, &zone,
10583  NewLiftoffAssemblerBuffer(func_body_size), debug_sidetable_builder.get(),
10584  compiler_options, function_coverage_data);
10585  decoder.Decode();
10586  LiftoffCompiler* compiler = &decoder.interface();
10587  if (decoder.failed()) compiler->OnFirstError(&decoder);
10588 
10589  if (auto* counters = compiler_options.counters) {
10590  // Check that the histogram for the bailout reasons has the correct size.
10591  DCHECK_EQ(0, counters->liftoff_bailout_reasons()->min());
10592  DCHECK_EQ(kNumBailoutReasons - 1,
10593  counters->liftoff_bailout_reasons()->max());
10594  DCHECK_EQ(kNumBailoutReasons,
10595  counters->liftoff_bailout_reasons()->num_buckets());
10596  // Register the bailout reason (can also be {kSuccess}).
10597  counters->liftoff_bailout_reasons()->AddSample(
10598  static_cast<int>(compiler->bailout_reason()));
10599  }
10600 
10601  if (compiler->did_bailout()) return WasmCompilationResult{};
10602 
10603  WasmCompilationResult result;
10604  compiler->GetCode(&result.code_desc);
10605  result.instr_buffer = compiler->ReleaseBuffer();
10606  result.source_positions = compiler->GetSourcePositionTable();
10607  result.protected_instructions_data = compiler->GetProtectedInstructionsData();
10608  result.frame_slot_count = compiler->GetTotalFrameSlotCountForGC();
10609  result.ool_spill_count = compiler->OolSpillCount();
10610  auto* lowered_call_desc = GetLoweredCallDescriptor(&zone, call_descriptor);
10611  result.tagged_parameter_slots = lowered_call_desc->GetTaggedParameterSlots();
10612  result.func_index = compiler_options.func_index;
10613  result.result_tier = ExecutionTier::kLiftoff;
10614  result.for_debugging = compiler_options.for_debugging;
10615  result.frame_has_feedback_slot = v8_flags.wasm_inlining;
10616  result.liftoff_frame_descriptions = compiler->ReleaseFrameDescriptions();
10617  if (auto* debug_sidetable = compiler_options.debug_sidetable) {
10618  *debug_sidetable = debug_sidetable_builder->GenerateDebugSideTable();
10619  }
10620 
10621  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_compilation_times)) {
10622  base::TimeDelta time = base::TimeTicks::Now() - start_time;
10623  int codesize = result.code_desc.body_size();
10624  StdoutStream{} << "Compiled function "
10625  << reinterpret_cast<const void*>(env->module) << "#"
10626  << compiler_options.func_index << " using Liftoff, took "
10627  << time.InMilliseconds() << " ms and "
10628  << zone.allocation_size() << " bytes; bodysize "
10629  << func_body_size << " codesize " << codesize << std::endl;
10630  }
10631 
10632  DCHECK(result.succeeded());
10633 
10634  return result;
10635 }
10636 
10637 std::unique_ptr<DebugSideTable> GenerateLiftoffDebugSideTable(
10638  const WasmCode* code) {
10639  auto* native_module = code->native_module();
10640  auto* function = &native_module->module()->functions[code->index()];
10641  ModuleWireBytes wire_bytes{native_module->wire_bytes()};
10642  base::Vector<const uint8_t> function_bytes =
10643  wire_bytes.GetFunctionBytes(function);
10644  CompilationEnv env = CompilationEnv::ForModule(native_module);
10645  bool is_shared = native_module->module()->type(function->sig_index).is_shared;
10646  FunctionBody func_body{function->sig, 0, function_bytes.begin(),
10647  function_bytes.end(), is_shared};
10648 
10649  Zone zone(GetWasmEngine()->allocator(), "LiftoffDebugSideTableZone");
10650  auto call_descriptor = compiler::GetWasmCallDescriptor(&zone, function->sig);
10651  DebugSideTableBuilder debug_sidetable_builder;
10652  WasmDetectedFeatures detected;
10653  constexpr int kSteppingBreakpoints[] = {0};
10654  DCHECK(code->for_debugging() == kForDebugging ||
10655  code->for_debugging() == kForStepping);
10656  base::Vector<const int> breakpoints =
10657  code->for_debugging() == kForStepping
10658  ? base::ArrayVector(kSteppingBreakpoints)
10659  : base::Vector<const int>{};
10660  WasmFullDecoder<Decoder::NoValidationTag, LiftoffCompiler> decoder(
10661  &zone, native_module->module(), env.enabled_features, &detected,
10662  func_body, call_descriptor, &env, &zone,
10663  NewAssemblerBuffer(AssemblerBase::kDefaultBufferSize),
10664  &debug_sidetable_builder,
10665  LiftoffOptions{}
10666  .set_func_index(code->index())
10667  .set_for_debugging(code->for_debugging())
10668  .set_breakpoints(breakpoints),
10669  nullptr);
10670  decoder.Decode();
10671  DCHECK(decoder.ok());
10672  DCHECK(!decoder.interface().did_bailout());
10673  return debug_sidetable_builder.GenerateDebugSideTable();
10674 }
10675
